title: broccoli, ham and cheese casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Mix with hands.
Make into small balls and flatten with fork. Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet at 300° for 10 to 15 minutes until light brown.

title: banana blueberry muffins
directions: Puree bananas in blender.
In medium bowl, combine bananas, eggs, sugar and butter until well blended.
Stir in blueberries and vanilla.
In large bowl, combine flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
Stir banana mixture into flour mixture until evenly moistened.
Spoon batter into well-greased 2 1/2-inch muffin cups. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.

title: granny cake
directions: Mix well. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with 1/2 cup brown sugar. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: city chicken
directions: Beat eggs and milk together. Place fine crumbs in shallow container. Roll skewered meat in flour seasoned with the salt, pepper and seasoning salt. Dip in egg wash. Coat with crumbs. Single layer sticks on 26 x 18 x 1-inch trays. Spray tops of sticks with Pam spray. Brown in convection oven at 400° for approximately 30 minutes with blower high. Place browned meat in three 12 x 20 x 6-inch pans (2 layers). Add hot gravy to each pan, enough to cover sticks completely. Cover pan with foil and bake in convection oven at 275° with blower low until serving time. Makes 250 servings.

title: mama's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 375°. Makes 2 medium size loaves.

title: preserving children
directions: Mix children with dogs and empty into field, stirring constantly. Sprinkle with wild flowers.
Pour brook gently over pebbles.
Cover with a blue sky and bake in hot sun.
When children are well browned, they may be removed and set in a cool bathtub.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Cover.
Blend on high until smooth.
Serve immediately.

title: annie frost's sweet potato casserole
directions: Sprinkle a little nutmeg in mixture.
Mix an put in baking dish.
Add Topping.

title: easy chocolate icing
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and melted butter together. Then add milk. If not creamy, add more milk.

title: classic cocoa pudding
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a medium saucepan. Add milk gradually and blend in. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Blend in margarine and vanilla.
Pour into
individual serving dishes. Chill. Garnish and top as desired.

title: beef roast
directions: Melt shortening in pressure pot, salt and pepper beef and rub flour well on all 4 sides.
Put in pot and brown on all sides.
Add soup mix blended with water and pour over roast.
Simmer until tender.
Cook at 15 pounds of pressure for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: diced mcintosh apple cake
directions: Add sugar to diced apples and let stand 10 minutes.
Sift flour, soda and spices.
Blend oil and egg into apple mixture. Add flour mixture all at once and beat with wooden spoon until well blended.
Bake in well-greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
When cold, cut into squares and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: peach cloud pie
directions: Combine marshmallows and milk in top of double boiler.
Melt marshmallows over hot water.
Set aside to cool completely, but do not chill to gel stage.
Beat out lumps and fold in cream that has been whipped, vanilla and salt.
Layer peaches and marshmallows mixture in crust.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: delicious dip
directions: Mix cottage cheese and cheddar cheese together.
Add dill weed, worchestershire sauce and salt and mash with a fork.
Dip raw vegetables in and eat.

title: fried dried apple pies
directions: Cook the dried apples in the water until tender.
Drain off any excess liquid.
Mash apples with the sugar, lemon juice, spices and flour.

title: party mix
directions: Pour wet ingredients over dry mix.
Mix well.
Bake in roaster or big pan at 200° for 1 1/2 hours, stirring every 1/2 hour.

title: baked limas
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together and add to cooked limas. Pour in casserole dish and top with bacon slices.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mildred's potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes; cut up and salt. Cook done. Boil eggs and chip up. Mix together, then add onions, pickles, mayonnaise and black pepper. Put in bowl.

title: perfect chocolate cake
directions: Combine cocoa and boiling water, stirring until smooth; set aside.
Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder and salt in a medium bowl; add to creamed mixture alternately with cocoa mixture, beating at low speed of electric mixer, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Do not overbeat. Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool completely on wire racks.
Spread Whipped Cream Filling between layers; spread top and sides of cake with Perfect Chocolate Frosting.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes one 3 layer cake.

title: shepherds pie
directions: In saucepan, cook onion with thyme in butter until tender; add remaining ingredients except potatoes.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Spoon potatoes around edges of casserole.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until hot.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: scalloped cabbage #1
directions: Cook cabbage in salt water until tender and drain.
Meanwhile, melt butter.
Add flour and salt.
Stir and cook approximately 5 minutes.
Add flour.
Stir until thickened.
Pour over cabbage. Top with sliced Velveeta.
Heat in oven until cheese melts.

title: lentil salad
directions: Wash thoroughly 1 pound lentils.
Put in a pot; cover with water and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 5 minutes; turn off heat. Let stand for over an hour (until cool).
Drain off water.
Add the chopped parsley, cilantro (chopped), celery, spring onions and red or sweet onions.

title: spicy carrot cake
directions: Add eggs, oil, sugar and carrots and mix well.
Combine remaining ingredients together and then add to first mixture. Pour in tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: scallop potatoes
directions: Stir milk and cheese soup until smooth.
Layer potatoes and onion.
Pour soup mixture on layer.
Salt and pepper as you go. Put a sprinkle of turmeric, if you want to.
Bake in oven at 350° until potatoes are done.

title: mexican fruitcake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, eggs, pineapple and nuts together.
Mix well.
Pour in a 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
In a bowl, combine cheese, butter, vanilla and sugar.
Blend until smooth.
Pour on top of cake while it is still hot.

title: stewed (sherried) apples - microwave
directions: Put apples in micro-safe covered casserole (a 2-quart dish is adequate since apples cook down quickly). Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons sugar if apples are tart.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes. Stir or fold gently; return to oven and cook 3 minutes on High power.
At this point, the firmer, crisper apples like Granny Smith will need more cooking. You want fork-tender, but not mushy, slices.
Continue to cook 2 to 3 minutes on High power and check and stir again.
Most apples will be tender at 9 to 10 minutes cooking. Yields about 6 servings.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream all ingredients together.
Roll on floured board.
Cut and bake at 350° until light brown.

title: baked beans
directions: In cold water, soak beans overnight in a Dutch oven size pan. The next morning, set on stove (just as they are) and parboil for about 1 hour.
Add salt pork (cut up into several pieces), dry mustard, onion (cut up into about 4 pieces), molasses, sugar and clove of garlic (cut up).
Cover all with water.
Bake at 350° until beans are tender and not mushy, approximately 4 to 5 hours. Keep checking and add water to keep beans covered.
Stir each time you check.

title: chicken pecan salad
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine chicken and celery.
In another bowl, combine mayonnaise, sour cream, lemon juice and salt.
Pour over chicken; toss to coat well.
Refrigerate.
Just before serving, toss with bacon and pecans.
Serve on lettuce with tomato garnish.

title: fresh apple nut cake
directions: Mix together first three ingredients.
Add next three ingredients that have been sifted together.
Then add apples, nuts, coconut and vanilla.
Pour into a well-greased Bundt pan (floured). Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: barbecue venison(deer)
directions: Pressure cook the deer meat for 25 minutes.
Shred meat.
Add the onion, salt, pepper and barbecue sauce to taste.
Slow cook in crock stew cooker overnight or for 5 to 6 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Serve on buns with sweet Spanish onions and dill pickle slices.
Enjoy!

title: super seafood salad
directions: Cut Crab Delights flakes in half or shred.
Combine with celery, onion and mayonnaise.
Serve as a sandwich or on lettuce.

title: supper baked beans
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put mixture in a casserole dish, top with bacon and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Boil sugar, vinegar and spices for 20 minutes.
Drop peeled fruit in, a few at a time; cook until tender.
Pack in hot, sterilized jars, adding syrup to 1/2 inch of the top.
Seal. Yields 5 quarts.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs only until mixed.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Pour scalded milk over crumbs and soak well.
Stir in egg mixture and butter.
Pour in greased baking dish.
Set dish in a pan containing 1 inch hot water.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 75 minutes.
Test as for baked custard.
Cake crumbs may be used instead of bread.
Nuts, raisins, dates or melted chocolate may be added if desired.

title: oatmeal date cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Stir in remaining ingredients in the order given.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: c & r snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs. Sift together flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar. Add to creamed mixture. Chill dough. Roll into walnut size balls. Then roll in a mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon. Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook and drain vegetables.
Place in a flat 9 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with salt and garlic powder.
Cook butter, flour and water together.
Cool and add sour cream, cheese and optional spices, if desired.
Pour over the vegetables and top with buttered crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Can be made a day ahead and baked the next day.

title: cabbage salad(can be frozen)
directions: In large bowl, combine the above.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Grease (diet margarine) 1-quart casserole.
Beat egg yolks (reserve whites).
Blend in lemon peel, milk and lemon juice; add sugar, flour and salt and beat until smooth.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into yolk mixture carefully, but thoroughly. Pour into casserole.
Set in another pan with 1/2-inch hot water. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm or cool.

title: texas style beans
directions: Wash beans before soaking.
In 2-quart pot or casserole, cover beans with water; soak overnight.
Do not drain.
Add salt pork, onion, garlic, salt and pepper to beans.
Simmer, covered, for 2 hours.
Add tomatoes, green pepper, sugar and hot pepper sauce. Cover and simmer 3 hours more.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: rancho baked beans
directions: Heat a small amount of oil over medium heat in skillet.
Add sliced apples (with or without peel). Sweeten to taste with half brown sugar and half white granulated sugar.
Cook, covered, until sugar is melted. Uncover and cook until apples are tender and most of the liquid evaporated.
Do not overcook or apples will be mushy.

title: debbie's dressing
directions: Make corn bread according to directions. Brown beef and sausage. Crumble in skillet. Add onion.
Cook until clear.
Add soups and all ingredients together.
Pour in greased pan. Bake at 325° until brown.

title: saucy italian fish
directions: Arrange fillets in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with oregano and pepper. Pour spaghetti sauce over top; sprinkle with parsley.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° gas oven 18 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over top; bake 5 minutes longer until cheese melts.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: sourdough banana bran muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg; beat until light and fluffy.
Stir soda into sourdough starter and add to creamed mixture.
Crush All-Bran cereal and fold into batter with mashed bananas and salt.
Fill buttered muffin tins 2/3 full and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: apple butter
directions: Cut up apples and seed.
Put in pot and cover with water.
Cook until mushy.
Run through sieve.
Place apple mush, sugar and cinnamon together and cook until thick.
(Low heat is better.)
Get out your jelly jars and fill.
Put hot lids on jars and seal.

title: chicken or turkey enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken; remove skin and bones and shred.
Mix the sour cream, soup, chilies and enough milk to create pourable consistency.
Flavor with taco sauce to taste.
Pour small amount of sauce into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread to cover.
Form enchiladas by placing chicken and grated cheese in a tortilla roll.
Place seam side down in dish.
Continue with enchiladas until chicken and cheese are gone.
Cover with remaining sauce; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: strawberry pie
directions: In saucepan,
mix
cornstarch with sugar and add water. Boil until clear.
Then
add
jello.
Cool,
but do not let it set. Arrange berries in baked pie shell and pour cooled jello mixture over berries.
Let chill until firm.

title: lumpia
directions: Chop all vegetable ingredients fine.
In deep frying pan or wok, add 1 tablespoon oil.
Brown meat and drain excess oil. Break meat into small pieces (no lumps).
Mix in vegetables and saute with meat until carrots are cooked.
Sprinkle a few times with soy sauce for flavor.
Simmer until vegetables are cooked. Let cool 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: cream cheese crescents
directions: Mix shortening and cream cheese together. Add sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Mix flour in until desired consistency to form crescents of desired size.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned. Roll in powdered sugar when cooled.

title: creamy slaw
directions: In a medium-sized bowl, combine the yogurt, sour cream, mustard, sugar, vinegar, celery seed, salt and pepper.
Add the cabbage and carrot and toss well to mix.
Cover and chill in the refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours, tossing occasionally.

title: baklava
directions: Using a shallow cookie sheet with sides that are the size of a pastry sheet, spread dough one sheet at a time, brushing each leaf thoroughly with butter.
When process is complete with 1 pound of phyllo, mix walnuts, sugar and mazzaher, and spread mixture over completely.
Cover with remaining pastry dough, being sure to brush each leaf with butter.
Using a small sharp knife, cut down lengthwise in 1 1/2-inch rows, then cut each row diagonally to make diamond shapes.
Bake at 200° for 1 1/2 hours until pale brown. Pour syrup over while pastry is hot.

title: hotel roanoke spoon bread
directions: Combine cornmeal, cold milk and salt.
Pour into hot milk in heavy pan, stirring constantly.
Cook about 5 minutes, until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in butter.
Cool slightly. Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Stir small amount of cornmeal mixture into egg yolks and add egg mixture to cornmeal, stirring constantly.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into ungreased 1 1/2-quart dish.
Bake, uncovered, about 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Mix onions and cheese.
Layer tortillas and onion and cheese mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with Enchilada Sauce.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes in 400° oven.

title: all-purpose bread stuffing
directions: Cook the onion and celery for 15 minutes in margarine and 1/2 cup water.
Save the water from the celery and the margarine.
Mix bread cubes, celery, onion, salt and pepper with 1/2 cup of the reserved liquid to moisten.
Bake 35 minutes in a covered casserole pan or use as a stuffing in fish, beef roll-ups, poultry, etc.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Line (8-inch) new flower pot completely with foil and set aside.
Crush the cookies until they resemble potting soil. Place 1 cup crumbs (or more) in flower pot and set aside.
Cream the cream cheese, margarine, sugar and vanilla together until blended and set aside.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Trim all fat and bone from meat.
Slice into strips 1/4-inch wide by 2 inches long.
In large skillet, melt butter and brown meat.
Place meat in slow cooker.
Add all other ingredients, except the mushrooms, flour and sour cream.
Cover; cook on low for 6 to 7 hours.
The last 30 minutes, cook on high and add mushrooms.
Combine flour and sour cream; add to meat.
Stir often.
Serve over hot noodles or rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: melt in your mouth chicken pie
directions: Remove chicken from bone.
Cut in bite-sized pieces and place in large casserole dish.
Bring broth and chicken soup to a boil and pour over chicken.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except crackers and pour into oblong baking dish.
Crush 1 pack of Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top.
Melt 1 stick of butter and pour over crackers.
Place in oven and bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mincemeat
directions: Bake pie until very lightly browned.
Cool and freeze uncovered.
Remove from freezer and let set at room temperature for 30 minutes.
Finish baking at 350°.
Pies will stay good in freezer from 4 to 6 months.

title: bread or rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup of warm water.
Set aside.
Combine shortening, sugar, salt and dried milk.
Add hot water and 5 cups of flour.
Add dissolved yeast.
Add 6 cups of flour.
Blend well. Put on floured breadboard.
Let rise 10 minutes.
Knead.
Let rise in a covered pan in a warm place for 2 hours.
Punch down. Roll out on breadboard in sections.
Spread rolled dough with butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up.
Slice and place in pans. Let rise 1 hour.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Frost when slightly cool.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
In large bowl put shortening, sugar and salt.
Pour boiling water over and stir until shortening is dissolved and mixture is just warm.
Add flour and yeast.
Stir until all flour is mixed well.
Place in a greased bowl.
Cover, let rise.
Roll out on floured paper or pinch off balls.
Flatten and put in greased pan, let rise.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: Beat egg with sugar until frothy.
Combine apples with remaining ingredients, except butter and cream and blend well. Combine beaten egg with apple mixture and blend well and spread out in a buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Dot with butter and bake in a 350° oven until browned, about 30 minutes.
Slice and serve hot, topped with heavy cream.
Serves 6.

title: marika and marc's grammy's baked beans
directions: Cut bacon in pieces.
Place
in a large pot with chopped onion and green pepper. Cook until crisp bacon.
Drain grease.
Set aside bacon mixture.
Pour beans into same pot as bacon mixture was.
Stir in mustard, vinegar, brown sugar and maple syrup. Continue stirring until mixture comes to a boil, then add bacon mixture. Stir until boils again, then turn off.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Mix flour with sugar well.
Add sweet milk and 3 egg yolks; beat the egg yolks just a little.
Boil until thickened over low heat, stirring constantly, or cook in a double boiler.
When done, add vanilla and oleo.
Put a layer of vanilla wafers in an ovenproof bowl.
Add a layer of strawberries and another layer of vanilla wafers.
Pour pudding over all.

title: apple walnut cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon and nuts. Place apples in bottom of greased 8 1/4 x 1 3/4-inch round baking dish. Sprinkle with cinnamon mixture.
Sift dry ingredients. Combine egg, milk and butter. Add dry ingredients all at once and mix until smooth with egg mixture.
Pour over apples and sprinkle with remaining nuts. Bake at 325° for 55 minutes. Serve warm with ice cream.

title: colorful pasta salad
directions: Boil colored rotini pasta and tube pasta; drain both.
Rinse in cold water and mix together in large bowl.
Mix in vegetables; toss entire mixture with 1 tablespoon of oil.
Coat entire mixture lightly with Feta cheese and Ranch dressing.
Can add crab or shrimp, then chill.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine Cornmeal, flour, eggs, sugar, salt, baking powder, green pepper, onion and tomato juice in large bowl and mix until moistened.
Heat oil 370 in deep fryer.
Drop by tablespoons into hot oil.
Deep Fry until brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: double-cheese potato bake
directions: Sprinkle 1/4 cup bread crumbs in greased shallow baking dish; set aside.
Mix well mashed potatoes, eggs and Parmesan cheese. Spread 1/2 in prepared baking dish.
Top with Mozzarella slices. Spread remaining potato mixture over cheese.
Mix remaining bread crumbs with butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes, until potatoes are firm and crumbs are browned.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate cream delight
directions: Melt margarine in pan and pour over flour and pecans.
Stir until crumbly.
Press in bottom of 9 X 13 cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 15-20 minutes or until golden brown.
Set aside and let cool.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Cook carrots

in sugar and soup mixture until fork tender but not soft. Cool and dice carrots and let them stand overnight. The next day, add remaining ingredients and stir well before serving. Placed in a covered container, this will keep for several weeks in the refrigerator.

title: diet broccoli casserole
directions: Mix everything together.
Bake in a covered casserole, about 30 minutes at 350°.
Don't overbake.
Casserole can become mushy and unappetizing if overbaked.

title: charity's chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and then add desired amount of mayo. Serve on croissant rolls.

title: holiday pineapple ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add peppers, cheese, onions, pineapple, salt and 1 cup pecans.
Shape into balls and roll in remaining pecans.
Chill several hours.
Serve with crackers and/or vegetables.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef, add other ingredients, except for beans, oil and flour.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
In small bowl, mix oil and flour until smooth.
Add beans.
Add this to kettle.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally for about 30 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix together butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and flavorings.
Then add flour, salt, and soda alternating with sour cream.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour 15 minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: Boil water, lemon rinds, sugar, orange rinds, cloves and cinnamon for 15 minutes.
Add tea.
Let stand for 3 minutes. Dilute 2 to 1.
Add juice of oranges and lemons.
Serve.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Drain pickles and cut into chunks.
Pour other ingredients over.
Stir for 4 days.
Put into hot jars.

title: crayfish or shrimp etouffee
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet or pot.
Add all green vegetables and saute well until onions are wilted.
Add 2 cups water and diced shrimp and let simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Dissolve cornstarch in a little water and add to mixture to thicken.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes more.
Serve over a bowl of cooked rice.

title: pecans
directions: Beat egg white and add remaining ingredients.
Pour over pecans.
Stir and coat well.
Pour all onto a foil-lined cookie sheet.
Spray with cooking spray.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes. Stir every 10 minutes.
Cool well, then place in an airtight container.
Can do peanuts, but they require longer baking and more salt.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and use as marinade for meat overnight.

title: nondairy sherbet
directions: Mix and pour into 1-quart freezer.

title: "miss pearl's" egg custard
directions: Melt oleo; add sugar and salt.
Beat 5 eggs just enough to mix well.
Add eggs and milk to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla; pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top and bake at 345° about 40 minutes or until almost firm.

title: basic drop cookie
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Add one-half of the flour at a time, beating well after each addition, then stir chocolate chips into the batter.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Place shortening, sugar, egg, water and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Beat thoroughly, then blend in rest of ingredients.
Drop on cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, Accent, onion, Worcestershire sauce and 1 package chopped beef (finely chopped). Roll into a ball. Cut other package beef into pieces and place on the outside of the cheese ball.

title: file gumbo
directions: Fry sausage for 10 to 12 minutes.
To remove excess fat, drain, slice and set aside.
Cut tips from chicken wings. Sprinkle with salt and brown on all sides; set aside.

title: lemon custard pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten egg yolk and flour; beat well.
Then add milk, lemon juice and grated rind.
Fold in well beaten egg whites.
Turn into pie crust and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: bertie's cool salad
directions: Sprinkle
lime	jello
over cottage cheese and mix well until all
jello	is absorbed.
Drain pineapple and fold into mixture. Fold
in
Cool Whip and oranges.
Chill before serving.

title: swedish shrimp
directions: Saute onion in oil in non-stick skillet to soften; 2 minutes. Add 3/4 cup broth; bring to boiling.
Add shrimp; reduce heat. Simmer, covered, until shrimp are pink; 3 minutes.
Whisk together 1/4 cup broth, sour cream, mustard and cornstarch in cup until smooth.
Whisk into the skillet.
Cook, stirring to thicken.
Add pepper, dill and lemon juice.
Serve over rice and peas.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ham and cheese casserole
directions: Combine butter, pepper, onion, soup and sour cream.
This will make a sauce.
Layer noodles, ham, cheese, mushrooms and sauce in that order, twice.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until bubbly.

title: cold cucumber soup
directions: Peel and seed cucumbers; cut into large chunks.
Place in blender with garlic and chicken broth.
Blend on high speed. Slowly add the sour cream, vinegar and salt.
Blend until mixed well.
Chill well before serving.
May be garnished with lemon or parsley.

title: celery casserole
directions: Parboil celery in salted water for 8 minutes.
Drain celery and add soup, pimento and water chestnuts.
Mix together and put in a buttered casserole.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat; add cheese, tomatoes, onion and chips.
Stir, then add lettuce.
Pour sauce as desired.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Mix all except peanut butter and oats. Heat in pan over low heat until butter melts, then boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Add peanut butter and oats. Beat well. Drop on cookie sheet. Cool and eat!

title: green enchilada casserole
directions: Fry tortillas in hot fat until they bubble; blot excess grease.
Place soup, milk and green chilies in saucepan and warm. Layer tortillas, cheese, onion and chicken.
Top with 1/3 soup mix, then more tortillas, etc. until all ingredients have been put in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Cube chuck roast.
Brown in skillet with flour, salt and pepper.
Bake browned meat in baking dish 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Remove and add remaining ingredients.
Bake 1/2 hour longer or until potatoes are tender.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix in large bowl the sweet potato, sugar, eggs and salt.
Add flavors.
Stir or beat well.
Cook for 45 minutes on 375°.

title: chinese boiled chicken(chow yow gai)
directions: Fill a large kettle with water; bring to a boil.
Place the chicken in the boiling water.
Return to a boil.
Lower heat, cover and cook 1 hour.
Remove and cool.
Debone chicken; tear into small strips.
Place in a large bowl.

title: sun-dried tomato and olive quick bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook juice, onions and garlic about 20 minutes until soft. Add everything else except tomato paste.
Cook 1/2 hour.
Add paste; cook 10 to 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Cold pack 10 minutes.
Heat canning lids before use.

title: holiday pie
directions: Mix sugar and egg yolks.
Add other ingredients.
Beat egg whites and fold into mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water and chill in refrigerator until soft set.
Mix cream cheese and sugar together and whip into chilled mixture.
Then fold in vanilla and whipping cream.
Pour into a graham cracker lined 9-inch pie pan and chill 12 hours.
Can be chilled for 1 hour in freezer.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in large casserole.
In a smaller bowl, mix with wire whip the flour, milk and margarine.
Pour over top of casserole and bake 1 hour at 300° or until lightly browned on top.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Boil chicken.
Debone.
Dice ham or thinly sliced sausage. Cook sausage or ham in melted butter until light brown.
Add tomatoes, water, okra, onions, green pepper, parsley, salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Return chicken to soup.
Discard bay leaf.
Just before serving, sprinkle gumbo file powder lightly over soup, stirring constantly.
Heap hot rice in individual soup bowl. Ladle gumbo over rice.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: dream bars
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and butter.
Put in buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until light brown. Mix together the rest of the ingredients.
Pour over baked mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 25 minutes.

title: waikiki meatballs
directions: Combine beef, oats, onions, egg, salt, ginger and milk.
Shape into balls (50), using one rounded teaspoon for each.
Melt shortening in a skillet; add meatballs.
Brown and cool.
Remove from skillet.
Drain.

title: highlander pancakes
directions: Pour milk over oats and let stand 5 minutes.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Lightly stir eggs into oat mixture.
Add dry ingredients and butter; stir until combined. Cook on hot griddle.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Knead the dough slightly. Make small round balls.
Drop in hot oil; fry until golden brown. Drain on paper towel.
Can be served with honey and syrup.

title: crustings
directions: Mix together and refrigerate. Spread evenly over pan, heavily. Keeps cake from sticking.

title: 24-hour salad
directions: Layer chopped lettuce on bottom of a 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Add water chestnuts, frozen peas (rinsed with hot water), chopped celery and chopped onion.
Spread with the mayonnaise. Sprinkle sugar, Parmesan cheese and bacon bits on top.
Cover with plastic wrap and let set for 12 to 24 hours in refrigerator before serving.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Saute sausage and
set
aside
to cool.
In the sausage pan, saute the celery, bell pepper and onion.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients and pour in casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese and cracker
crumbs
and
bake
at
for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: vegie pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls out onto cookie baking sheet to make crust.
Bake until done.
Cool.

title: poor man's ham salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and keep refrigerated.

title: pastitsio(makes 6 servings)
directions: In a large skillet, melt 2 tablespoons of the butter.
Saute onion and garlic until golden.
Add remaining butter and crumbled ground beef; brown well.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, water, salt, pepper, cinnamon and cloves to meat mixture.
Simmer 20 minutes or until most of the liquid has been absorbed.
Mixture should be thick.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Place chicken in covered baking dish and bake, covered, for 15 to 20 minutes until tender.
Remove and drain dish if necessary. Combine remaining ingredients except Parmesan cheese.
Cook gently until thickened.
Pour over chicken in warm serving dish.
Top with Parmesan cheese and return to oven, uncovered, for another 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms. Cut into small pieces (stems). Cut chipped beef into small pieces.
Take cream cheese, mushroom stems and chipped beef and mix well with fork. Take spoon and fill mushrooms. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Can be reheated in microwave.

title: creamy vegetable casserole
directions: Prepare vegetables according to package.
Drain and place in bowl.
Stir in soup and cream cheese.
Place in baking dish and sprinkle with croutons.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until bubbling.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, peanut butter and sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together the flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Roll in balls; flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or longer to light brown.

title: light yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
In large bowl, slightly beat egg.
Add sugar, salt, shortening and milk; mix well.
Add yeast mixture; mix well.
Add flour; mix well.
Knead well with greased hands.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Knead down and form into small balls size of walnuts.
Turn in oil.
Put 2 per muffin tin for Parker House rolls and 3 per muffin tin for cloverleaf.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 475° until golden brown.

title: minute rice meat balls
directions: Mix soup with water.
Combine remaining ingredients with 1/2 cup of the soup mixture; mix just to blend.
Shape into meat balls.
Place in skillet.
Pour remaining soup mixture over meat balls; bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes, basting occasionally.

title: salmon patties
directions: Flake salmon and combine with other ingredients; blend well and chill for 1 hour.
Shape into patties and dip in additional stuffing mix.
Fry in small amount of oil until golden brown on both sides.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries, sugar and water until well done.
Add marshmallows to hot mixture.
Dissolve cranberry gelatin according to package and cool.
Add nuts, celery, and apples.
Mix and chill.

title: slush punch
directions: Bring to boil water and sugar to make a simple syrup.
Cool. Mix all ingredients except ginger ale and freeze in 3 half gallon milk cartons.
When ready to serve, mix with ginger ale in punch bowl (1 milk carton of punch mixture to 2 or 3 tall bottles ginger ale).
Can be made ahead and used as needed.

title: pumpkin dump cake
directions: Beat eggs; add in all other ingredients except cake mix.
Top with dry cake mix and cut butter into chunks and put on top of cake mix.
Pour into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: diet pineapple pudding
directions: Use a long casserole bowl.
Put one layer of wafers on bottom. Drain juice off of pineapple first.
Put one layer of canned pineapple over wafers.
Pour half of pudding over these ingredients.
Start over.
One layer wafers, one layer pineapple and pour remaining pudding over that.
Cover with wafers.
Then use diet whipped cream over the top.

title: southwestern corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large mixing bowl, combine corn meal, flour, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Set aside.
In medium bowl, stir together egg whites, buttermilk, honey, green chiles, corn and red peppers.
Stir into corn meal mixture and mix until just blended.

title: diabetic baked custard
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Scald milk in double boiler or (I use microwave).
Blend together eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add hot milk gradually, stirring to mix well.
Pour into 4 (6-ounce) individual custard cups.
Sprinkle surface with nutmeg.
Set cups in a deep pan; pour hot water around cup to come to within 1/2 inch of tops of cups.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until a knife tip inserted in center of custard comes out clean.
Remove from heat and water pan.
Chill several hours before serving.
Yields 4 servings (1/2 cup each).
One serving food exchange:
one low-fat milk.

title: marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Marinate meat 1 to 3 hours.

title: brownie bar
directions: *Dried
apricots, candied citron, candied lemon peel and glaced cherries.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt. Beat together the eggs, sugar, vegetable oil and vanilla. Add the two together and beat well. Stir in the apples and pecans with a wooden spoon.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: zupa rybna (fish chowder)(christmas eve soup)
directions: The heads with eyes and gills removed as well as the tail portion of 2 large fish can be used instead, with the choice center slices used for other dishes.

title: pumpkin drop cookies
directions: Mix together the pumpkin, eggs, margarine and sugar.
Sift together the baking powder, flour, cinnamon, salt and baking soda and add.
Stir in the milk, vanilla and bits.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10-15 minutes.
Yields 60 cookies.

title: apple hill cake(from apple hill)
directions: Combine apples and sugar; let stand.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add oil, water and vanilla and beat until blended.
Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to egg mix alternating with apples/sugar mixture, stirring until blended. Coat nuts with a little flour and stir in.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Leave in pan until ready to serve.
Serve warm or with Cool Whip, cream or ice cream.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; cook on low in crock-pot until heated all the way through.
You can cook in oven until heated through.

title: german-style potato salad
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Add potatoes.
Stir gently. Refrigerate and serve cold.

title: venison pot roast
directions: Dust roast in flour and sprinkle well with pepper.
Heat oil in Dutch oven.
Add garlic, onion and all spices except bay leaf and salt.
Cook until onion is soft and transparent, not brown.
Add roast and brown well on all sides.
Add water, bay leaf and salt to taste and simmer over low heat, 1 1/2 to 2 hours until meat is tender.
Add vegetables and simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Remove roast and vegetables to heated plate.
Thicken gravy with 1 tablespoon cornstarch dissolved in 1/2 cup cold water.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Pour everything over cucumbers and onion.
Cover and put in refrigerator overnight.

title: coney island sauce
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a large pan and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
To thicken, add 1/2 cup flour to one cup water; mix.

title: dirt
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth and fluffy; set aside.
Combine pudding mix and milk until well blended, then fold in Cool Whip.
Gently fold the two mixtures together.
Layer 1/2 cookie crumbs followed by pudding/cream cheese mixture.
Can serve in lined clay pots (enough for three 6-inch flower pots); stick in a plastic flower, a couple of gummy worms and a little garden spade.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook until thick, around 3 hours, stirring often to keep it from sticking.
When thick, put in jars and seal.
This recipe is very hot.
You can put less peppers in.

title: drip pan baked potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes.
Cool.
Mix with cheese.
Layer all in a greased dripping pan.
Sprinkle cornflakes over top.
Dot with butter or oleo.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: camp stew
directions: Cook hen and pork until it comes all to pieces.
Mix with other ingredients and simmer.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Thaw and drain frozen vegetables.
Combine, vegetables, soup, sour cream and pepper.
Pour into 1-quart casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese and onions. Bake uncovered an additional 5 minutes.

title: mildew scrub for painted surface
directions: Scrub with brush or cloth; let stand until mildew fades. Rinse thoroughly and let dry.
If first try doesn't succeed, try again.

title: hickory baked carp
directions: You will need a 14-inch green cut hickory plank.

title: cranberry holiday punch
directions: Chill soft drinks.
When ready to serve, pour cranberry juice and carbonated beverages into punch bowl.
Float ice cubes. Garnish with orange slices and mint leaves.
Yields 24 punch-size cups.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream oleo. Add sugar and beat until smooth. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add vanilla wafers which have been crushed alternating with milk. Add coconut and pecans. Put batter into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: salad pizza
directions: Flatten crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown.
Beat cream cheese with salad dressing.
Add dill weed, onion flakes and salt.
Spread on crust.
Place fresh cut vegetables on top.
Chill.

title: potato rolls
directions: Put 6 1/2 cups flour in large bowl (will take more).
Combine mashed potatoes and, while hot, add Crisco, sugar, milk, eggs and salt.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add yeast mixture to rest of ingredients; stir into the flour.
At first, stir with a spoon. Add more flour and knead to make a softer dough.
Let rise in a warm place until double in size.
Make into rolls and let rise. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes (depending on size of rolls).
Usually makes 5 dozen rolls.
Space them like cookies on a cookie sheet. These freeze well.

title: corn bread
directions: Heat oil in iron pan you are going to bake bread in.
Mix other ingredients and put into pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fresh apple pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in apples. Turn into pie shell.
Dot with margarine.
Cover with top crust. Seal and flute.
Bake at 425° until crust is brown and juice begins to bubble through slits in crust, about 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pumpkin nut bars(heritage recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine all ingredients except nuts.
Beat for 2 minutes with electric mixer at medium speed. Fold in nuts.
Spread evenly in a 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan.
Bake in a moderate oven 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pineapple-cheese boats
directions: Select a pineapple with fresh leaves. Cut lengthwise into quarters through green top. Cut off core. Remove fruit from outside skin. Cut fruit into chunks. Save outside skin to use as "boats."
Drain fruit and invert shells to drain.
Place pineapple chunks, halved strawberries and melon balls in bowl. Sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon ginger and lime juice.
Toss. Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Stir in cheese. Spoon mixture into shells.
Sprinkle with almonds and ginger.
Spoon yogurt on top.
Yields 4 servings.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add vanilla, salt and eggs. Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add oatmeal, coconut, nuts and cereal.
Mix and form into balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Saute onions and celery.
Add other ingredients.
Top with onion rings and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: roasted vegetables
directions: Place vegetables in Corning dish with cover.
Sprinkle with Mrs. Dash and small amount of salt and pepper.
Pour oil over vegetables and toss until all the vegetables are covered.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: golden cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease an 8 or 9-inch square pan. Combine all ingredients in order listed; stir until smooth.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
Makes about 9 servings.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning mix together with an electric mixer until well blended.
Spread mixture on bottom of a pizza pan.
Chill mixture for 2 hours.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese until smooth, then add other ingredients.
Place in refrigerator.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and butter. Add eggs, vanilla and milk. Sift together remaining ingredients. Add flour slowly to sugar/egg/milk mixture. Chill for at least 4 hours. Roll out and cut into desired shapes.

title: easy hot dogs
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: mud cake
directions: Bake cake by directions on box for 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Poke holes in cake while it is still hot from oven.
Pour milk over cake; let it soak in holes.
When cake has cooled, spread Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with crushed candy bars on top of Cool Whip.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Microwave chicken breasts 20 minutes, covered.
Debone chicken; add cream of chicken and reheat 5 minutes.
Prepare Stove Top stuffing as directed.
Cover chicken mixture with Stove Top stuffing.
Reheat if desired, 3 minutes in microwave.

title: spanish omelet
directions: Fry potatoes in oil; once fried, drain them.
Saute onion and add to potatoes.
Heat chorizo in a pan in the bacon grease, adding to them the potatoes, peas, peppers and eggs, beaten with salt.
Mix everything.
In a double frying pan, add 3 to 4 tablespoons olive oil; add mixture for a few minutes.
Put on lid; turn the omelet with large plate and add another 3 to 4 tablespoons oil and turn over omelet.
Cook another few minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets, reserving 3/4 cup beet juice.
Combine vinegar, reserved beet juice, cornstarch, sugar and salt in top of double boiler.
Cook over low heat until thickened, stirring frequently. Add beets; heat through.
Serves 8.

title: biscotti morina
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into a large mixing pan. Resift.
Cut shortening into flour and work into the mixture by hand until evenly mixed.
Beat eggs and milk for 2 minutes. Gradually add sugar and beat for 5 minutes.
Add liquid to dry ingredients.
Work in until dough is even and firm.
Do not knead. Cut dough into small pieces and form a ball about 1 1/2-inch in diameter.
Roll by hand until it reaches 6-inches long.
Shape into a backwards "S".
Keep moist towel on remaining dough.
Place cookies on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake on lower shelf of oven to brown bottom.
Shift pan to upper shelf to brown top. Approximately 10 minutes per shelf.
Cool on racks.
Oven 400°. Yields about 6 dozen.

title: fruit ala great
directions: Combine fruit.
Add lemon pudding; it should make a slight glaze type sauce.
Add orange liqueur.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cool and serve.
The longer it sets, the more blended the glaze becomes.

title: sparkling citrus cooler
directions: In a 2-quart nonmetallic pitcher, combine sparkling water, lemonade concentrate and lime juice.
Mix well.
Immediately serve over ice.
Garnish with lime slices.

title: hidden pear salad
directions: In saucepan, bring liquid to boil.
Stir in Jell-O until dissolved.
Remove from stove.
Cool until thickened but not set. Puree pears in blender.
Mix cream cheese and lemon juice until fluffy and smooth.
Add pears.
Mix well.
Prepare rich whip. Beat like whipping cream and fold into pear mixture.
Fold in cooled Jell-O and pour in mold.
Refrigerate.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix well. Roll thin and place in pie plate.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix together cake mix and butter, pack in a pan (13 x 9 x 2-inches).
Mix cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar.
Pour on top of other mixture.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°.
Let completely cool before cutting.

title: turkey spaghetti sauce
directions: Heat olive oil; add turkey, but do not brown.
Stir in the rest of the ingredients, except cheese.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve over pasta, rice or mashed potatoes.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: marinade cornish hens
directions: Pour dressing in a dish.
Place Cornish hens in dish.
Cover, refrigerate for 12 to 24 hours, turning once.
Remove from dressing.
Shake off excess.
Bake on a baking rack for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chilli
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.

title: twice baked potato casserole
directions: Cut baked potatoes into 1 inch cubes.
Place half in a greased 13 inch x 9 inch x 2 inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with half of the salt, pepper and bacon.
Top with half of the cheeses. Repeat layers.
Bake, uncovered, at 350 degrees for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serves 6 or 8.

title: golden onion rings(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Combine all ingredients except onions.
Mix until dry ingredients are well moistened.
Dip onion rings in batter.
Fry in hot oil until golden.
Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.

title: fish casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Place in baking dish and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serves 4-6.

title: camper's jerky
directions: Slice steak, against the grain, into pieces about 1 inch thick.
Cut pieces crosswise into 5-inch strips (about size of hot dogs).
Mix rest of ingredients.
Soak meat in this mix for at least 30 minutes.

title: coconut dessert(manjar de coco)
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for half of the shredded coconut and cook until thick (like a custard), stirring slowly. Pour into Bundt pan with sauce on the bottom.
Put it in the refrigerator after it is cooled.
Remove from pan and sprinkle remaining shredded coconut on top.
Refrigerate.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Use a 4-quart Dutch oven or saucepan.
Melt oleo and saute onion.
Add broccoli and stir.
Add soup; stir and simmer.
After several minutes, add the Cheez Whiz; stir.
When cheese is melted, add the rice.
If too thick, add a little water.
Put in casserole.
Freeze or cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: 2 minute microwave fudge
directions: Stir sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and vanilla together until partially blended.
Put butter over top in center of dish. Microwave at High for 2 minutes.
Stir vigorously until smooth. Blend in nuts.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy; add sugar gradually until stiff peaks form.
Fold in pecan halves.
Melt margarine in 15 x 10-inch pan.
Pour pecans in pan and bake 20 minutes at 300°.
Stir every 10 minutes.
Cool and store in container.

title: country ham steak with glazed apples
directions: In skillet, melt margarine until sizzling; stir in brown sugar and mustard.
Add apples; cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until apples are crisp-tender (5 to 7 minutes).
Place ham steak in same skillet, arranging apples on top.
Cover; continue cooking until ham steak is heated through (5 to 7 minutes).

title: turtle bread
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups flour, yeast, sugar and salt in large bowl. Heat water, milk and margarine to 125° to 130°.
Stir into yeast mixture.
Stir in egg.
Stir in enough of remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Sprinkle surface lightly with flour.
Turn dough onto surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Shape a 2-inch piece of dough into a ball for turtle's head.
Shape 4 walnut-sized pieces of dough into balls for feet. Shape 1 walnut-sized piece of dough into tail.
Shape remaining dough into a ball for body.
Place on cookie sheet and flatten slightly.
Attach head, feet and tail by placing one end of each under edge of body to secure.
Press raisins into head for eyes. Cover and let rise 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 400°.
Make crisscross cuts in body 1/4-inch deep to look like a turtle shell.
Bake until golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Put sugar over rhubarb and let stand overnight.
Boil 8 minutes.
Remove from stove.
Add dry Jell-O.
Stir well.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: bird seed pudding (not for human consumption)
directions: Melt beef suet and peanut butter in heavy saucepan.
Stir until blended. Remove from heat and cool to room temperature or until pudding starts to thicken.
Add sunflower seeds or bird seeds, mix thoroughly.
Spoon into tinfoil pans.
Refrigerate until solid, then nail or otherwise affix to outside table, balcony ledge, tree, etc.
in winter and watch birds feast.

title: frozen delight
directions: Mix all together and pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: fancy egg scramble
directions: In large skillet, cook bacon and onion in 3 tablespoons butter until onion is tender, but not brown.
Add eggs and scramble just until set.
Fold mushrooms and cooked eggs into the cheese sauce. Turn into 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining butter, crumbs and paprika.
Sprinkle on top of eggs.
Cover.
Chill until 30 minutes before serving.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: grape punch
directions: Combine grape juice and lemonade concentrates with club soda, stirring until concentrates are dissolved.
Chill slightly.
Yields 25 servings.

title: stromboli sandwiches
directions: Brown beef and sausage; drain grease.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until hot.
Spread mixture on bottom half of bun and sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over mixture.
Put top of bun in place; wrap in foil and bake 10 minutes at 400°.
These can be wrapped in paper towels and heated in a microwave until the cheese melts.

title: christmas bread or fruit bread
directions: Soften yeast and one tablespoon sugar in warm water.
Scald milk and pour over the butter, sugar and salt.
When lukewarm, add the yeast and three cups flour.
Beat thoroughly.
Add rest of ingredients and stir until well mixed.
Beat until smooth and elastic.
Brush with melted butter; cover and let rise until light, 1 1/4 hours.
Beat well and fill buttered bread pans 2/3 full. Brush with melted butter.
Cover and let rise until light, 3/4 hour.
Brush lightly with milk and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 3 or 4 loaves, depending upon size of bread pans.

title: fresh apple salad
directions: Combine apples, pineapple chunks, grapes and poppy seeds in large glass bowl.
Add chilled dressing; refrigerate until time to serve.
Stir in pecans right before serving for maximum crunchiness.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together, then add the others and mix together.

title: graham cracker toffee squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and sugar in small saucepan over low heat.
Add chopped nuts and salt.
Arrange graham crackers in single layer on greased cookie sheet and spread with nut mixture.
Bake for 10 minutes.
When cool, break into sections.
Yields 48 pieces.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In 1 1/2-quart kettle, cook sugar, Karo and cream of tartar to 257°.
Add peanuts.
Cook to hard crack 310°.
Add oleo and let it fully melt.
Add soda; mix well.

title: prune conserve
directions: Put chopped prunes, raisins, orange juice and lemon juice into large kettle.
Heat to boiling.
Add Sure-Jell.
Bring to rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Add sugar; boil 1 minute.
Add nuts just before removing from stove.
Put into sterilized jars and seal.
Turn upside down for 5 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Place rice, sugar, egg, milk and water in pot and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and slow cook for about 1/2 hour.
Add one teaspoon vanilla.
Pour mixture into a bowl and refrigerate until served.

title: hershey's cake
directions: In large mixer bowl, cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla, flour and syrup.
Blend well.
Bake in 2 (8-inch) greased and floured pans 25 minutes on 350°.

title: hot fudge topping
directions: Combine sugar, salt, cocoa and water in small saucepan.
Cook on medium heat stirring constantly until bubbly.
Simmer for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in oleo and vanilla.
Serve hot or cold over ice cream.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients and roll into balls.
In a heavy saucepan, melt chocolate chips and paraffin wax.
Dip balls into hot chocolate and put on wax paper.
Keep refrigerated or in the freezer.

title: quick dessert
directions: Pour pineapple (undrained) into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add pie filling.
Spread dry cake mix on top of filling.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Pour melted margarine over all. Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: orange french toast
directions: In a large bowl, combine orange juice, orange peel, orange juice concentrate, eggs and granulated sugar.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in yogurt.
Cut bread into 1 to 1/2-inch thick (about 16 slices).
Dip bread slices into egg mixture, turning to coat.
Place in single layer in a shallow pan.
Pour any remaining egg mixture over slices.
Cover; chill up to 2 hours.
Heat griddle or large skillet over medium-high heat.
Melt butter in pan.
Lightly brown French toast on both sides.
Keep French toast warm in oven until ready to serve.
Dust with confectioners sugar and garnish with orange slices before serving.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add oatmeal and chocolate chips; stir by hand.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 350°
about 8 minutes.
Do not brown.

title: dainty tea cookies(spritz)
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together until waxy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, and mix well after each addition.
Add flour, a tablespoon at a time, until all the flour is used up. Put into a cookie press; make into an S shape or round wreaths. Bake until light brown at 400° for about 10 minutes.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Blend marinade ingredients in blender until oil will not separate.
Pour over chicken and marinate overnight.
Grill on barbecue about 10 to 12 minutes per side, basting after each turn.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Let hash browns thaw for 1/2 hour.
Mix all ingredients and some salt and pepper.
Put in a 9 x 13 pan.
Top with crumbs. Bake at 355° for 1 hour.

title: the ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream butter-flavor shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Blend until creamy. Blend in egg.
Combine the flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture, gradually.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts; drop rounded measuring tablespoon of dough on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies (or 11 to 13 minutes for crispy cookies).
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: tomato crouton casserole
directions: In greased 2 quart casserole, mix tomatoes and 1 cup croutons. Stir in onion, sugar, oregano, salt and pepper.
Dot with butter: sprinkle with remaining croutons.
Bake uncovered, at 375 for 30-35 minutes.

title: chestnut-bacon appetizers
directions: In a bowl, combine the last 3 ingredients.
Cut bacon down the center and wrap strips around water chestnuts.
Insert toothpicks to hold.
Place on cookie sheet; bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
This cooks the grease out of the bacon.
Remove from cookie sheet and place in baking dish.
Pour sauce over chestnuts and bake at 350° for approximately 1/2 hour.

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, onion, egg, salt, pepper, and 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Form into loaf and place in a shallow 7 x 10 inch pan.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over loaf.
Bake for 1 hour 15 minutes at 350.
Baste often during baking.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rice krispies pudding
directions: Crush Rice Krispies.
Mix with peanut butter and honey.
Press into an 8 x 8-inch dish.
Top with prepared pudding (any flavor). May top with whipped topping.

title: fish chowder
directions: Fry bacon and crumble.
Put aside.
Place diced potatoes into bacon drippings and cover with water.
Cook until done.
Add fish chunks and cook additional 5 minutes (until fish flakes).
Add corn, butter and salt/pepper to taste.
Add bacon and enough milk to get to chowder consistency.
Cook until thoroughly heated. Serve hot.

title: apple fritters
directions: Sift the dry ingredients into a bowl.
Stir the milk into the egg; add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Mix in the apples. Drop batter by spoonfuls into deep fat heated to 375° and fry for about 3 minutes.
Turn fritters during frying.
Drain on paper towels.
Yields about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: karo nut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into pie dish.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: white fudge cake
directions: In a small pan, melt chocolate in hot water over low heat. Cool.
Combine flour, sugar, soda, baking powder, salt, margarine and buttermilk.
Blend at low speed until moistened.
Beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Add eggs, melted chocolate and vanilla.
Add nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chili con carne
directions: Heat, in a large heavy frying pan, vegetable oil or shortening.
Add minced beef, onions and green peppers.
When meat is lightly browned, add remaining ingredients.
Blend, cover and simmer gently for 20 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: texas cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients all together. Melt in saucepan the 2 sticks margarine, water and 4 tablespoons cocoa until bubbles and pour over above; mix. Bake in 9 x 13 pan at 350° for 23 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Trim pork of all fat.
Season chops.
Mix soup, sauce and seasonings.
Heat on low until dissolved.
Place 4 chops in casserole dish.
Pour half the sauce over chops.
Place remaining chops and pour rest of sauce on top.
Cover dish and bake at 350 degrees for 1-1/2 hours or until meat is tender.

title: split pea soup
directions: In large saucepan, soak peas overnight in water (or combine peas and water).
Bring to boil, about 2 minutes.
Add ham bone, onion, garlic salt, marjoram and dash of black pepper to pea mixture.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 2 hours, stirring constantly.
Remove ham bone.
Cut off meat.
Dice meat.
Add to soup, along with remaining ingredients.
Cook until vegetables are tender.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter a medium size casserole.
Put sliced apples in.
Mix cinnamon in 1/2 of water.
Pour over apples.
Then in another mixing bowl mix sugar, flour and room temperature butter together with fingers until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm, topped with Cool Whip (optional).

title: marie's potato candy
directions: With mixer, mix potato and vanilla.
Gradually add powdered sugar until stiff.
Then roll it out on wax paper.
Spread the peanut butter over it.
Roll it like a jelly roll and cut into pieces.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Crush crackers and mix with butter in pie pan for crust. Saute onion until clear.
Spoon into crust.
Beat eggs with salt, milk and pepper.
Pour over onions.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bubble loaf
directions: Top with remaining buttered balls.
Cover, let rise 45 minutes or until double.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Ice with confectioners sugar icing and sprinkle with chopped, candied cherries.

title: roast quail with mushrooms
directions: Wipe birds inside and out with clean cloth.
Wrap each bird in bacon slice; secure with toothpicks.
Place birds in a buttered pan and roast at 350°, basting often, about 30 minutes or until tender.
Remove birds and add butter, water and lemon juice to drippings in pan, stirring to make gravy.
Add mushrooms.
Serve birds on toast with gravy.
Serves 4.

title: apple-raisin sandwich filling
directions: Wash, quarter and core apples.
Sprinkle with lemon juice. Grind apples and raisins together.
Add sugar, if desired, and mix well.
May add nuts, finely chopped, for extra flavor.
Spread on bread for sandwiches.

title: baked haddock
directions: Mix salt, pepper and garlic together thoroughly and rub on both sides of fish fillets.
Place in a buttered shallow baking dish. Combine butter and lemon juice; add Worcestershire sauce.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Baste with butter mixture 2 to 3 times during baking.
Yield:
4 servings.
Carbohydrate 3 g, protein 37 g, fat 24 g, calories 381.

title: chili con queso
directions: Prepare ground beef according to directions on taco seasoning mix.
Melt Velveeta and add all ingredients, mixing well.
Serve with tortilla or potato chips.

title: oven-fried fish fillets
directions: Thinly coat fish fillets with mayonnaise; dredge in breadcrumbs.
Arrange in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Sprinkle with paprika, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork. Garnish with lemon wedges.
Yield: 3 to 4 servings.

title: sesame "fried" drumsticks
directions: Combine dry ingredients in shallow dish.
In a separate dish mix egg and water.
Dip chicken in egg mixture, then roll in crumb mixture.
Arrange chicken in baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 hour, turning once.
Cool slightly; remove from pan.
Cover and refrigerate 3 to 24 hours.
Yield:
5 to 6 servings.

title: sangria
directions: Cut all of the fruit into wedges.
Combine the apples, orange, lemons, pineapple tidbits (juice too), wine, juice of lemons and anise into a large bowl.
Dissolve the sugar into 1/2 cup of warm water.
Mix this mixture in with the other ingredients, except the orange soda pop.
Cover and let stand in the refrigerator for two days.
When getting ready to serve, add the orange soda pop.

title: world's best cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream together butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla, mixing well.
Add oil; mix well.
Add oats, corn flakes, coconut and nuts.
Add flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Shape into small balls the size of small walnuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in water.
Bake 12 minutes.
Allow to cool slightly on cookie sheet before removing.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: key west key lime pie
directions: In a bowl fold first 3 ingredients together and pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill in refrigerator for 4 hours to allow mixture to firm up.

title: cauliflower quiche
directions: Place cauliflower in covered saucepan in enough boiling water to cover.
Cook with lid on for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Place in greased 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with onion, green pepper and cheese.
Place remaining ingredients in blender container.
Cover and whirl 15 seconds or beat 1 minute with rotary beater.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake in preheated 375° oven 20 to 25 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean and top is golden. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pie filling in a greased and floured pan.
Spread evenly. Dump pineapple on top of pie filling.
Spread evenly.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Put foil over if coconut turns brown.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: In medium saucepan, place sugar, milk, margarine, salt, syrup and cocoa.
Bring to a boil and stir constantly.
Add peanut butter and stir until it melts.
Add oatmeal, vanilla and nuts (if desired).
Mix until begins to thicken.
Drop by spoonful on waxed paper.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix. Put in casserole dish.
Crumble Ritz crackers on top and dribble 1 stick or less melted oleo over all.
Cook at 350° until bubbly (about 25 minutes), then brown top under broiler.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together with mixer and spread in the bottom of a glass pie pan.
Break up sealegs into small pieces and lay on top, then pour and spread chili sauce on top.
Refrigerate.

title: grilled marinated tuna
directions: Trim away any dark red portions of the tuna.
Cut the tuna into 1 1/2-inch squares and place in
a nonmetallic bowl.
Add the garlic, onion, oregano and pepper and toss well, rubbing the seasonings into the fish.
Add the wine, oil, bay leaf and orange rind and turn the fish to coat with this mixture.
Marinate for 30 minutes at room temperature.
Prepare the grill.
Thread alternating pieces of the tuna and zucchini snugly on skewers. Grill about 5 minutes on each side, brushing occasionally with the reserved marinade, until lightly browned.
Serve immediately.

title: potatoes with cheese
directions: Boil potatoes. Grease pan.
Cube potatoes and a little onion. Pour oleo and Velveeta cheese over potatoes.
Sprinkle bread over top.
Pour the Pet milk over pepper.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: round steak supreme
directions: Rub meat with garlic.
Combine flour, paprika, salt and pepper.
Pound well into steak.
Brown in hot oil (you may spray with Pam and omit oil).
Top with onion and mushrooms.
Simmer, covered, until tender, 1 1/2 to 2 hours, adding more liquid if needed (using mushroom juice or more bouillon).
Remove steak. Add sour cream to skillet.
Serve mixture over steak.

title: open-faced chicken sandwich
directions: Put chicken into a small bowl and sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Mix prepared apple, celery and walnuts into a bowl.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and mustard and blend with the apple-celery mixture.
Place buttered bread on a board and cut into 3-inch rounds.
Top each round with a leaf of lettuce, then with 1/4 of the chicken and 1/4 of the apple mixture, piling it on top of the chicken in an attractive mound.
Garnish with a sprig of parsley.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: layered casserole(ultra low-fat)
directions: Brown meat and onion in large skillet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings.
Simmer 7 to 8 minutes.
In a large bowl, combine green pepper, cottage cheese, cream cheese and sour cream; mix thoroughly.
Spray large casserole dish (9 x 13-inch) with nonstick spray.
Cover bottom with pasta.
Add a layer of meat mixture.
Pour cottage cheese mixture for next layer and top with shredded fat free cheese. Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 8 servings. Contains 202 calories and 2 grams of fat per serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese; mix 1 cup of the pecans and all other ingredients with the softened cheese.
Mold into ball.
Roll in the other cup of pecans.
(This cheese ball will freeze well.)

title: banana crush
directions: Make a syrup of water and sugar by heating until sugar is dissolved.
Combine with remaining ingredients, except ginger ale. Pour into trays or containers and freeze.
(Best to divide into 3 containers.)
After frozen, take out of freezer one hour before serving.
Mix with ginger ale.

title: sad cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix the Bisquick, beaten eggs and brown sugar; mix well.
Add the coconut and pecans.
Grease and flour an oblong cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash cooked squash; add to other ingredients and mix well. Pour into greased 1 quart casserole dish and bake at 375° for about 40 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chicken pan pie
directions: Chop meat of chicken in bowl.
Add 3 cans cream of chicken soup.
Add milk to make thin.
Put in Pyrex and be sure it is real soupy.
Add biscuit dough, rolling very thin.
Does not have to be one solid sheet of dough.
Cook at 350° until dough is very brown on top.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix the shortening and sugar together. Add eggs, pumpkin and milk.
In separate bowl, blend dry ingredients.
Add to pumpkin mixture.
Stir in raisins and walnuts.
Bake muffins 15 to 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar in large mixer bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; gradually blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts and peanut butter chips, if desired.

title: for pasta lovers
directions: Cook fettucine to nearly done.
Add oil to large hot saute pan; add garlic and cook until just slightly tan.
Add mushrooms, olives, tomatoes, shrimp and crab meat.
Saute about 2 minutes or until shrimp are just pink.
Add fettucine and stir (or about 2 minutes).
Remove from stove; add shredded cheese and place under broiler until cheese just turns brown; serve.

title: quick and easy appetizer
directions: Place cream cheese on a decorative plate.
Put crab over it. Pour cocktail sauce over crab.
Serve with crackers.

title: easy cabbage beef soup
directions: Brown hamburger meat. Shred cabbage. Open all cans. Throw in a great big pan. Add 2 cups water. Drop in beef broth cubes. Cook to boil, then turn to medium. It's done when cabbage is tender (about 45 minutes). DELICIOUS! AND QUICK!

title: banana bread loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into greased bread pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 loaf.
Slice and spread Darigold butter on each piece.

title: hawaiian baked bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll bacon into curls and bake on a pie tin for 30 minutes or until brown.

Drain bacon and set aside. Mix the remaining ingredients and pour into a casserole dish. Bake for about 40 minutes or until hot and flavors have blended. Just before serving, lightly stir bacon curls into the casserole.

title: old timey scratch bisquits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt. Stir in 2 tablespoons oil.
Mix in buttermilk until dough is stiff and pliable.
Pinch off dough.
Roll and flatten by hand to desirable size.

title: shrimp in prosciutto
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Shell and devein shrimp, leaving tail on.
Put slice of roasted pepper inside shrimp and wrap with Prosciutto, leaving tail exposed.
Arrange shrimp on a baking pan propping the tails up alongside of the pan.
Pour the wine and melted butter over shrimp and bake about 20 to 25 minutes.
Take out of oven and place small slice of Mozzarella cheese over shrimp, to just cover.
Return to oven to melt.
Once cheese has melted, take out of oven and arrange on plates; pour a little of the pan juices over each shrimp and garnish with fresh chopped parsley.
Serve with rice pilaf and fresh vegetables.

title: french herb omelette
directions: Mix eggs, water, salt and pepper in small bowl with mixer or fork.
Heat butter in nonstick pan until it almost starts to brown.
Add egg mixture and shake and stir until set.
Just before folding, add fines herbs (parsley, chives, basil, chervil) to center.
Serves 1.
(Can be made with 2 large eggs.)

title: hot appetizer dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts together.
Spread mixture in an 8-inch pie plate and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: hurry-up yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Mix in Bisquick and beat vigorously. Turn dough onto surface which is well dusted with Bisquick.
Knead until smooth.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spray standard pizza pan with Pam and set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Blend
cream
cheese and margarine together; add sugar, beating slowly.
Add
eggs,
one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add
flour,
a small amount at a time.
Add vanilla and beat
well.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 300° for one hour and thirty minutes (1 1/2 hours).

title: spaghetti bake
directions: Cook beef with onions. While this is cooking, boil spaghetti. Drain beef; add sauce and simmer. Drain spaghetti; rinse and put in a casserole dish. Pour sauce over spaghetti and top with cheese. Bake at 350° until bubbly or cheese is melted.

title: spam treat
directions: Microwave vegetables in soup/sauce mix until done.
Top with grated cheese or
Durkee canned fried onions.
Goes great with leftovers, fishsticks etc.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown bacon; drain and crumble.
Brown beef and onions. Drain.
Combine with other ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a greased 3-quart casserole, uncovered for 40 minutes at 350°.
You can also bake in a crock-pot on low for 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt, then cut in Crisco until about like coarse meal.
Add water, vinegar and egg to flour mixture; mix until easy to handle.
Roll out needed amount.
Store unused dough in airtight container.
This will keep well in refrigerator for about a week.
It can also be frozen.
Let come to room temperature before using.

title: grandma's 7-up cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°, then 35 minutes at 350°.

title: deluxe chicken casserole
directions: Blend water with mayonnaise with wire whisk until smooth. Add rest of ingredients
except potato chips.
Pour into 11 x 7 inch baking dish.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly hot.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Melt butter in double boiler; add sifted sugar, flour, salt, milk and egg yolks.
Beat with hand mixer until smooth.
After it thickens, add vanilla and coconut.
Pour into baked pie shell. Top with meringue and coconut.

title: pancake mix
directions: Mix by hand or hand whip eggs first, then add all other ingredients.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Grate cheese and add soup, mayonnaise, onion and egg.
Mix well.
Drain broccoli and add to cheese mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Crush enough crackers to cover top of casserole (I use Ritz).
Pat with butter.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: liver pate
directions: When cream cheese is at room temperature, mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Chopped onions may also be added. Delicious!

title: chili salsa beef
directions: Trim fat from beef roast.
Cut roast into 1 1/4-inch pieces. In Dutch oven, heat oil over medium heat until hot.
Add beef and brown evenly, stirring occasionally.
Pour off drippings if necessary.
Stir salsa, sugar, soy sauce and garlic into beef. Bring to a boil; reduce heat to low.
Cover tightly and simmer 1 hour.
Remove cover; continue cooking, uncovered, an additional 30 minutes or until beef is tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chopped cilantro and lime juice.
Spoon beef mixture over rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: crab butter
directions: Cream ingredients well and serve with crackers.

title: no bake banana pudding
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Put half in the bottom of a large bowl.
Mix sweet milk to pudding mix.
Set aside for a few minutes.
Slice banana over the cracker crumbs.
Squeeze half a lemon over the banana (keeps it from turning dark and gives it a good taste).
Continue the next layer.
Top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate until ready to eat.
Serves a large family.

title: hershey brownies
directions: Mix all together and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Makes 1 large 15 x 16 pan with sides or 1- 9 x 13 and 1- 9 x 9.
