title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix together and set aside.

title: cream cheese and clam quiche
directions: *Bake pastry blind at 400° for about 5 minutes or just until set.
Cool.

title: healthy pizza
directions: Follow directions for pizza dough on package. Allow to rise in refrigerator. Form dough into pizza pan. Quick fry veggies to translucent. Spread sauce on dough. Top with veggies. Add desired sauce. Top with cheese. Cook at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: party egg casserole
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Bake, uncovered, until brown around the sides.
Can be frozen.
(Defrost 15 minutes.)

title: crock pot chicken
directions: Place above ingredients in crock pot.
Cover and cook on low 6 to 7 hours.
Yields 4 servings.

title: caramel sticks or bars
directions: Mix all in bowl (batter will be stiff).
Add a few more nuts or dates if you like them.
Spray an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin cupcakes
directions: Beat eggs at medium speed until well blended. Add sugar, flour, soda, baking powder, nutmeg, pumpkin, oil and milk. Stir until well mixed; add nuts and dates, if using. Place paper baking cups in muffin tins. Spray with cooking spray. Fill cups 3/4 full with pumpkin mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Remove cupcakes from pan and let cool before spreading on frosting or eat warm.

title: bombay turkey
directions: In skillet, melt butter or oleo.
Add curry powder and heat 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in onion; cook until tender.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper, stirring well.
Add chicken broth.
Cook and stir until mixture is bubbly; cook 2 minutes more.
Add turkey and lemon peel; heat mixture to boiling.

title: rice sour cream casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in casserole dish and bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake covered at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate crackle top cookies
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder and salt.

title: corn noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles until done; drain well.
Add oleo, cheese and sugar.
Heat until cheese melts.
Remove from stove.
Add cream-style corn.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet "n" sour meatballs
directions: Roll your hamburger into balls.
Chop onions and green peppers. Fry onions, peppers and meatballs together.
While this is frying, make a sauce out of ketchup, sugar and vinegar in a skillet.
Drain the grease off meatballs and add to sauce.
Let it simmer for an hour and then you have yourself Sweet "N" Sour meatballs.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In a bowl, mix asparagus, sour cream, cheese and mayonnaise together. Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish. Put cube bread on top. Pour melted butter over bread. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bread browns.

title: cornbread corn casserole
directions: Bake cornbread mix according to directions on package and crumble in baking dish.
Add corn, soup, onion and pimento.
Mix well.
Sprinkle one cup of cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: all-day macaroni and cheese
directions: Place the cooked macaroni in a 3 1/2-quart (or larger) slow cooker that has been coated with nonstick cooking spray. Reserve 1 cup of the cheese. Add the remaining cheese and the other ingredients to the macaroni. Mix well. Sprinkle with the remaining 1 cup cheese. Then cover and cook on a low setting for 5 to 6 hours or until the mixture is firm and golden around the edges. Do not remove the cover or stir until the mixture has finished cooking. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: studenetz(jellied pig feet)
directions: Wash feet and hocks well.
Scrape skin and rinse.
Soak beef shank in cold water to take out blood.
Place in large soup pot all the meat.
Add enough water to cover, about 2 inches above meat.
Cook on medium heat, skimming off scum, about 1 hour.

title: round steak dinner
directions: Shake 1 tablespoon flour into cooking bag; place in a 2-inch deep pan.
Pound rest of flour, salt and pepper into steak.
Cut into 5 pieces; place in cooking bag.
Arrange vegetables around steak.
Combine bouillon and tomato soup; pour over steak.
Secure bag; make 6 slits in top.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, or until meat is tender.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and salt in a large bowl.
Cook for 4 minutes in microwave on High.
Stir in peanuts.
Cook 4 more minutes on High.
Stir in vanilla and butter; cool 30 seconds.
Stir in baking soda until foamy.
Pour onto lightly greased cookie sheet.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Mix jello with 1 1/2 cups hot water.
Refrigerate and let set up partially. Then add lemon juice and sugar.
Mix well.
Put half the graham cracker crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
With an electric mixer, beat milk until it is the consistency of whipped cream. Fold in jello
mixture and mix well.
Pour over graham cracker crumbs and sprinkle the remaining graham cracker crumbs over the mixture.

title: pineapple meringue pie
directions: Heat pineapple in saucepan.
Mix sugar thoroughly with cornstarch and salt.
Add all at once to hot pineapple and cook, stirring briskly, until thick and clear.
Beat egg yolks in bowl. Stir in a little of the hot mixture, then return all to saucepan; cook, stirring for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in butter and lemon juice.
Pour into baked pie shell and spread roughly, covering in meringue.

title: pork and bean casserole
directions: Lightly brown the onion and pepper in butter.
Add ground beef and stir until meat changes color.
Drain.
Add to pork and bean mixture.
Pour into casserole dish.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marinated veggie salad
directions: Drain all vegetables well.
Mix together well.	Pour dressing mixture over vegetables.
Do not heat.

title: chocolate lovers delight
directions: *You may not need all of the cake when layering.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Make cake mix according to package directions.
Poke holes in cake while warm.
Warm sugar with pineapple, approximately 45 seconds.
Pour over cake while warm, spreading evenly.
Cool for half hour.
Spread pudding mix over cake.
Brown coconut flakes for 5 minutes.
When ready to serve, spread Cool Whip over cake and place coconut on top.

title: chicken parmesan(quick dinner)
directions: Cook chicken in sauce on the stove or oven (on stove is easier).
Be careful you don't burn them.
Once cooked, turn off stove.
Place Mozzarella cheese on top; cover.
Let stand until cheese melts.

title: caesar salad
directions: Squeeze garlic juice and rub in round wooden bowl.
Cut up shallot and anchovies.
Put 1 egg yolk per person.
Slowly pour olive oil.
Mix until it becomes pasty.
Add vinegar until smooth. Add lettuce, cheese and croutons.
Chill and serve.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: june's steak bites with gravy
directions: Roll steak in flour, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Brown quickly in small amount of cooking oil.
Remove from skillet and drain excess fat.
Saute onion and celery.
When browned, sprinkle lightly with flour.
Stir until browned and add 1 cup cold water slowly, stirring constantly.
Add steak pieces and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Serve over Alfredo noodles, prepared according to directions on package.
Yields 4 generous servings or have leftovers.

title: cheddar and turkey potato pie
directions: Cook and stir mushrooms and onion in butter over medium high heat for 3 minutes.
Stir in flour and pepper.
Gradually stir in broth and milk; cook, stirring frequently until mixture thickens. Reduce heat to low and stir in turkey, vegetables and 1 cup cheese.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Stir 3/4 cup cheese into potatoes. Spoon turkey mix into casserole.
Top with potato mix.
Place under broiler for 5 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and paprika.
Broil another 2 minutes.

title: pickled eggs(must be made 2 to 3 days before serving)
directions: Mix together sugar, salt, spices, vinegar, beets, beet juice and onion in skillet.
Cook over moderate heat until mixture boils, then reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 3 to 4 minutes. Remove from heat and let stand until warm.
Pack eggs into wide-mouthed jar.
Pour warm mixture over eggs, gently pushing eggs into liquid.
Store tightly covered in refrigerator 2 to 3 days before using.
Will keep 2 to 3 weeks in refrigerator.
Use in salads or whole.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on, not too much (10 to 12 minutes). Cool, peel and grate.
Mix together in bowl the sour cream, soups and cheese.
Saute onions in a little margarine until tender and add to the sour cream mixture.
Gently stir into potatoes and place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole (approximately).
Top with cheese and bake at 325° for 15 minutes or until heated through.

title: mock hollandaise sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Can be kept refrigerated for weeks.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In a large bowl combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; mix well.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: mock turtle soup
directions: In large pot, combine water, beef, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, onion, lemon, salt and pepper.
Separate the meat into bits in the water; cook until meat is well done, about 1/2 hour.
In the meantime, crush the gingersnaps by rolling between 2 pieces of wax paper.
Fill the empty catsup bottle with water and in a bowl add it to the gingersnap crumbs.
Stir until lumps are out and mixture well blended.
Add this to the meat mixture and simmer for 1/2 hour longer, until flavor is right, stirring occasionally, so crumbs do not stick.
A few minutes before mixture is ready, add vinegar and chopped eggs.
Leftovers can be frozen.

title: white sauce
directions: Heat butter in saucepan; blend in flour and cook until bubbly.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly; cook until thickened.
Cook 3 minutes longer.
Add seasonings, add whatever leftover meat you are using and continue cooking until heated through.
Serve over toast, rice, noodles or biscuits.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill several hours.

title: quick rigatoni
directions: Fry hamburger and onions with seasoned salt.
Drain off the fat.
Mix together hamburger with noodles and Ragu.
Put in a baking pan and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chip cheese ball
directions: Combine the cream cheese, butter and vanilla in a mixing bowl and beat until fluffy. Add the confectioners sugar and brown sugar gradually, beating until just blended. Stir in chocolate chips. Chill, covered, for 2 hours. Place on a large piece of plastic wrap and shape into a ball. Chill, wrapped in plastic wrap, for at least 1 hour. Just before serving, roll the ball in chopped nuts. Serve with graham crackers, graham cracker sticks or vanilla wafers.

title: pig out cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil and mandarin oranges with juice with mixer.
Bake in oblong pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
After cake cools, top with Cool Whip, crushed pineapple and instant pudding mixed with mixer.
Frost and refrigerate.
Best if eaten next day.

title: cherry puff
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Blend milk, eggs, biscuit mix, sugar, margarine and extract in blender 15 seconds or beat on high speed of mixer 1 minute.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Stir cheese and whipped cream in a heavy pan.
Warm until smooth and cheese melts; stir constantly.
Arrange potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
In layers, begin with potatoes, then pour sauce over.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Repeat until all are used. End with sauce.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Done when potatoes are golden brown and tender when pierced with a fork.

title: oven baked porcupines
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix meat, rice, water, onion, bell pepper and seasoning.
Easy and very good with mashed potatoes.

title: hershey pie
directions: Melt marshmallows, candy bars and milk in double boiler (or microwave).
Cool mixture and fold whipped cream into cooled mixture.
Add vanilla and pour into crust.
Chill.

title: chicken paprika with noodles
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven, heat 2 tablespoons of oil over medium heat. Add chicken. Cook, stirring, 3 to 5 minutes or until white. Remove. Heat remaining 1 tablespoon oil in Dutch oven. Add mushrooms and onion. Cook, stirring, 2 minutes or until tender. Add chicken and next 4 ingredients. Cover. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until chicken is tender. Re-stir cornstarch mixture. Add to chicken mixture. Stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute. Remove from heat. Stir in yogurt. Serve over noodles. Makes 4 servings.

title: century pudding
directions: Boil together water and 1 1/2 cups brown sugar for a few minutes. Pour into a 2-quart casserole or baking pan. In separate bowl, mix 1/2 cup brown sugar, butter, cloves, cinnamon, salt, flour, baking powder, milk, raisins and nuts. (For festive holidays, I use 1/2 to 2/3 cup candied fruit.) Drop batter evenly into hot syrup. Bake in slow oven (325°) for 1/2 hour. (Caramelized sauce on bottom.)

title: onion soup
directions: Coarsely slice onions and saute in butter until tender and brown.
Combine water, bouillon cubes and Worcestershire sauce with browned onions in saucepan and boil 30 minutes.
Fill crocks half, on top put onion rounds, Swiss cheese and Parmesan cheese. Bake in 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream together shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add one spoon at a time alternating with milk.
Add vanilla.
Stir in pineapple with juice and blend well.
Pour into well-greased tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until top springs back when lightly touched.
Let stand for a few minutes in pan.
Run knife around edges and remove carefully.
Combine powdered sugar, margarine and drained pineapple.
Pour over cake.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Chop
cabbage
fine; add all ingredients to the chopped cabbage;
everything
raw,	mix
well.
Put in casserole dish. Bake at 275° until done.

title: banana applesauce cookies
directions: Mix well.
Bake in a 375° oven until lightly browned.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a baking pan.
Stir well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam. Cook meats over medium heat. Drain. Add butter, onions, garlic and seasonings. Add 3/4 of tomatoes; simmer on low heat for 30 minutes.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook bouillon, onions and celery 20 minutes or until tender. Add cubed potatoes (raw) and frozen mixed vegetables to mixture. Cook about 20 minutes more.
Then add both cans of cream of chicken soup and Velveeta cheese, cut up.
Cook and stir until cheese is melted.
Serve with croutons and French bread.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: egg strata
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Place 6 thawed waffle quarters in single layer in dish.
Cover with ham and sprinkle with half (4 ounces) cheese.
Cover with a second layer of 6 waffle quarters and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Dot with butter.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, salt and spices.
Blend in eggs, milk and evaporated milk.
Pour into pastry shell (crimp edges high, filling is generous).
Bake in 400° oven for 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.

title: creamy liverwurst pate
directions: Blend liverwurst, cream cheese (softened) and sherry until very smooth.
Also, add onion and parsley.
Spoon mixture in small bowl. Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: taco salad
directions: Put refried beans in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Spread over beans the sour cream, then layer over the sour cream, lettuce, Ortega sauce, black olives, tomatoes and sprinkle the Cheddar cheese over top. Delicious.

title: pineapple squares
directions: Mix ingredients and knead well.
Roll out dough and place in oblong baking pan.
If unable to roll, may be spread into pan by working with fingers and pushing dough so as to cover entire pan.

title: snickerdoodles cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Mix thoroughly the shortening, sugar and eggs. Sift together and gradually add flour, cream of tartar and soda. Roll into small balls and roll in mixture of 3 tablespoons sugar and 1 1/2 tablespoons cinnamon. Bake 8 to 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package.
Melt butter in frying pan, saute onion until golden brown.
Add flour, salt and pepper to onion.
Mix well.
Gradually add cream and chicken broth. Stirring constantly, cook until thickened.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix ingredients; simmer tea until desired.

title: seafood spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil and butter until soft.
Add wine, clams and juice, shrimp and scallops, seasonings until tender. Cook spaghetti as directed on package.
Drain.
Mix noodles together with sauce.
Add 1 container fresh grated Parmesan cheese, adding slowly so it does not glob.

title: icebox slaw
directions: Chop cabbage, onions and peppers as for any slaw.
Mix with 3/4 cup sugar.
Toss or stir to mix well.
Heat celery seed, mustard, vinegar, 1 teaspoon sugar and salt to boiling point.
Add salad oil and bring to boiling point again.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Mix well.
Put in glass jar or plastic containers with lids.
Do not seal.
Store in refrigerator a few hours or overnight before eating.
Keep refrigerated.
This slaw will keep many weeks or until all gone.

title: easy apple goodie
directions: Pour pie filling into pie plate.
Mix oatmeal, flour and sugar and pour over apples.
Dot with margarine or butter.
Bake 1 hour at 325° or 350°.

title: taco dip
directions: Chop the tomato, green onions, and olives, and mix them together.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: snickers cake(no icing!)
directions: Prepare cake as box says.
Pour 3/4 batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels with oleo and milk.
Pour over baked cake.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Dot remaining cake batter over top.
Bake 20 minutes at 250°, then 10 more minutes at 350°.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic.
Add other ingredients and simmer until thick.
Makes enough sauce for 1 pound spaghetti.

title: basic cream soup
directions: Cook first 2 ingredients together in saucepan for 5 minutes. Blend next 3 ingredients into mixture.
Add vegetable liquid or meat broth to mixture, slowly.
Stir and boil slowly for 2 minutes.
Add last 2 ingredients to mixture, heat thoroughly and serve at once.

title: smoked stuffed chicken breast
directions: Roll chicken breast in Italian dressing.
Season both sides of chicken with Tony Chachere's, garlic salt & lemon pepper. Stuff chicken breast with cream cheese, chopped onion, and chopped peppers.
Fold chicken breast over.
Wrap chicken with bacon strips, leaving split on top.
Put 4 toothpicks through bacon & chicken to hold together.
Smoke on grill at about 250 degrees for 2 to 3 hours.
Thirty minutes before removing from grill, rub honey over each piece of chicken.
Do not turn over.

title: spice cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients (don't sift flour).
Add eggs, oil and baby food.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 hour. Remove from oven and, while still hot, pour glaze over.

title: tomato and zucchini salad
directions: In a medium mixing bowl combine tomato, zucchini, green onions, basil and light vinaigrette.
Toss lightly to mix.
Line 2 salad plates with lettuce.
Divide tomato mixture between plates. Sprinkle each serving with half of the cheese.
Makes 2 servings.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Take flour, pecans and margarine.
Blend until crumbly and press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes, then set aside to cool.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Saute the celery and onion.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour all together.
Put in an iron skillet or baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter fingers(yields 4 dozen)
directions: Cream butter, brown sugar and sugar together.
Blend in egg, soda, vanilla, peanut butter and salt.
Stir in flour and oats. Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with semi-sweet chocolate chips.
Let stand 5 minutes; spread evenly.

title: doris fatjo's pralines
directions: Mix 2 1/2 cups sugar with 1 cup cream in heavy saucepan and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Brown 1/2 cup sugar until caramelized.
Combine the 2 mixtures.
After blending the two, stop stirring and continue to boil until a small amount dropped in cold water forms a perfect ball.
Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon of vanilla and 2 cups pecans.
Beat until mixture loses its gloss, then drop by rounded teaspoons on waxed paper to make pralines.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs in a large bowl until foamy. Add flour and sugar.
Beat until well blended.

title: lemon raspberry bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray an 8 x 8-inch baking pan generously with butter-flavored nonstick spray.
Set aside.
Mix together flour, Splenda Granular and salt in a medium sized mixing bowl.
Cut in light butter until the mixture is crumbly, like a streusel topping.
Do not over mix.
Press dough into prepared baking pan.
Bake in preheated oven 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Place Splenda Granular and flour in a medium sized mixing blow.
Stir well.
Add egg substitute and half-and-half.
Stir until blended.
Slowly add lemon juice while stirring constantly.
Add lemon peel.
Stir raspberry preserves until they loosen up.
Spread evenly over warm crust.
Gently pour lemon mixture over preserves.
Bake in preheated oven 20 to 25 minutes or until set.
Remove from oven and allow to cool before placing in refrigerator.
Chill in refrigerator 2 hours before serving.
Makes 16 bars.

title: refrigerator muffins
directions: Put shortening in small saucepan.
Melt over low heat.
Set melted shortening aside.
In large mixing bowl, put cereal, flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Stir lightly.
Break eggs into another large bowl.
Add buttermilk and melted shortening.
Beat well.
Pour egg mixture over bran mixture and stir until ingredients are well mixed.
Spoon batter into large container. Cover and refrigerate.
(Batter can be kept in refrigerator several weeks.)

title: katie's pecan chicken cutlets
directions: Pat chicken dry.
Combine butter, 2 tablespoons mustard, salt and pepper.
Brush on chicken.
Encrust each cutlet with pecans. Heat oil on high.
Saut for 6 minutes each side until brown. Remove chicken and wipe out skillet.

title: spiced rhubarb
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

title: peanut patties
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, salt, water and peanuts in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
When mixture has reached a hard boil, time it to boil 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in margarine, vanilla and food coloring.
Beat until very stiff.
Drop on buttered foil in size of patties desired.
When cool, wrap each in plastic wrap.

title: buttermilk dressing
directions: In a bowl, whisk together all the ingredients.
Refrigerate two hours before serving and continue to keep any leftovers in the refrigerator. Yield: 1 1/2 cups.

title: pie crust
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Add shortening and mix until crumbly. Mix egg with water and blend well; add to flour and shortening mixture and stir until moist.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Stir the Dream Whip and ice cream together; add Hershey's syrup, chocolate chips and nuts, as desired.
Spoon into crust; sprinkle more chips or nuts on the top and freeze until firm.

title: whipped strawberry salad
directions: Prepare jello according to package.
Chill until partially firm.
Add remaining ingredients, whipping cream before stirring into jello.
Chill until firm.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Slice apples into large mixing bowl and put sugar on them. Stir egg into apples and sugar.
Combine dry ingredients and stir into apple mixture.
With wooden spoon, push mixture into a nongreased 9-inch pie plate or 8-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Put the cooked potatoes into a large bowl and add eggs, bacon, pickles and onion.
Stir in Miracle Whip, mustard, bacon grease, pickle juice and salt. Mix well and refrigerate.

title: sesame vegetables
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet.
Add vegetables and saute over medium heat about 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add water and cover.
Simmer until tender, 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir in sesame seed and serve.
Carrots and onion complement the sweetness of each other.

title: magic crust chicken
directions: Place chicken on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour broth over chicken; place drained peas and carrots over chicken.
Mix soup together and pour over peas and carrots.

title: temptation waldorf salad
directions: Wash apples, celery, raisins and lettuce.
Dice and mix apples, celery, nuts and raisins.
Add salt and mayonnaise and mix well. Serve on a bed of lettuce leaves.
Preparation time:
5 to 10 minutes; serves 6 to 8.

title: javaneh's pecan puffs
directions: Process flour and pecans in a food processor or blender until nuts are very finely chopped.
Beat butter, sugar and vanilla in large bowl with electric mixer until pale and fluffy.
By hand, gradually add flour mixture just until blended.
Roll level tablespoons dough into balls and place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until golden. While warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Cool on wire rack.

title: oklahoma posse stew
directions: Cook ground beef with chopped onion. Add the other ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: cooked pimento cheese
directions: Cut cheese into pan with pimento and melt over low heat.
Add the milk, mustard, sugar and salt and stir until well blended. Add the eggs and continue to stir until the eggs are cooked.
Add the flour and stir until thickened.
Serve on bread as a hot sandwich.

title: busy day pie
directions: Spread pie filling in buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Cover with cake mix (enough cake mix to make light covering over pie filling).
Add chopped nuts over cake mix and dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until butter melts and a light brown crust covers pie.
Cool and serve with ice cream.

title: florentine  vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into a 2 quart greased casserole dish. Bake at 325 degrees for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cinnamon with sliced peaches.
Pour into crust and cover with crust.
Mix small amount of milk and sugar. Brush over crust as it will brown good.
Bake in glass plate at 425° or metal pan at 450° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: egg nog punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, mix first three ingredients.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Bake at 450° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: bacon-cheese loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Arrange one package biscuits in one layer of prepared loaf pan. Spread mustard over biscuits.
Sprinkle cheese and bacon bits over mustard.
Arrange second package of biscuits in one layer over cheese.
Bake 10 minutes, uncovered.
Cover loosely with foil and bake 15 minutes longer.
Serves 10.

title: swiss cheese and tuna casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: mom's zucchini cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients and set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Add vanilla and zucchini; add flour, alternating with milk.
Add nuts and beat well.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in 10-inch tube or Bundt pan, greased and floured.
Let cool, then sprinkle powdered sugar over top.

title: crunchy banana delight
directions: Mix egg, sugar and nuts. Spread on cookie sheet and bake until brown at 350°, about 20 minutes. Cool; crumble. Sprinkle 1/2 crumbs on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cover with sliced bananas.

title: papa barringer's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in large pot; boil for about 5 minutes. Cool and store in glass jar. Not necessary to refrigerate if used soon.

title: quiche
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower in enough water to cover until crisp-tender; drain.
Add all other ingredients; blend well.
Bake in greased casserole dish at 400° for 30 minutes, or until a knife inserted comes out clean.

title: sandwich cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients in bowl, except icing.
By small teaspoonfuls, roll in balls and drop onto greased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes.
Let cool.
Ice cookies with canned icing; match up with cookie of same size to make sandwich.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cook white cake as directed on package in a 13 x 9-inch pan. When done, poke holes in cake with large wooden spoon.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Pour cream of coconut over cake.
Let cool completely, then top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle coconut on top. Then refrigerate.

title: cornmeal seafood batter
directions: Combine egg and flour.	Beat in milk, salt and pepper. Whip to a smooth batter.
Put cornmeal in a shallow pan.
Set aside. Dip the fish into the batter, coating both sides.
Place into the cornmeal and coat thoroughly.
Shake off excess and fry to a golden brown.

title: homemade waffles
directions: Mix all together with beater.
Pour into hot waffle iron.

title: freezer pickles(heritage recipe)
directions: Pour liquid mixture over cucumbers, and then put in refrigerator overnight.
Take out, put in containers or jars and freeze.

title: curried ground beef
directions: Cook ground beef, onion, salt and pepper, then add water and curry powder.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve over rice with sliced oranges, bananas, apples, raisins, nuts and coconut.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger. Drain grease.
Add the taco mix.
Add your own seasonings. Cool in refrigerator.
Cut up all vegetables to bite size (dice them).
Open bags of Doritos and smash them to small bite size.
Mix all other ingredients, including chilled hamburger.
Mix in Doritos immediately before serving for crispiness.
Makes a very large party size bowl.
Might want to cut amounts in half for smaller portions.

title: cranberry apple tarts
directions: Fit pastry into eight 4-inch tart pans.
Reserve remaining pastry for garnish.
Combine cranberries, apples, sugar and 1/2 cup water in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and 2 tablespoons water, stir into cranberry mixture and cook over low heat 2 minutes.
Let cool. Stir in pecans and orange rind.
Spoon filling into prepared pastry shells.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool completely.
Using a fluted pastry wheel, cut thirty-two 3 x 1/2-inch strips from remaining pastry; pinch ends of 16 strips together to look like loops of a bow.
Place loops and remaining strips on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Brush with melted butter and allow to cool completely.
Place 2 loops and 2 strips on each tart to form bow; pipe whipped cream on bow.
Yields 8 servings.
Tarts can be frozen after assembly; thaw and serve.

title: vivian's cheesecake
directions: Mix together and pour over graham cracker crusts.

title: toasted snack mix
directions: In wok, melt butter or margarine over medium heat; stir in Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder, celery salt and hot pepper sauce.
Add nuts; cook over medium heat about 4 minutes or until lightly browned, stirring constantly.
Add pretzel sticks and cereal.
Toss to coat well; continue to cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, about 1 minute or until slightly toasted. Cool before serving.
Makes 6 cups.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil the potatoes first.
Add ingredients, mixing along the way.
When all ingredients are mixed in, strain mixture to make smooth.
Pour in pie crust.
Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour. Makes 4.

title: brisket
directions: In large pan put bay leaves under brisket.
Add water, Worcestershire sauce and Wish-Bone dressing and marinate overnight. Bake at 250° for 6 hours.

title: joe's tomato wine
directions: Work 15 days
and
off	and strain.
Add 3 pounds sugar and 2 packets yeast.
Let work until done, strain and bottle.

title: pepper relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in kettle; bring to a boil.
Cook uncovered for 2 minutes.
Put into jars and set on rack in kettle or canner.
Add water to kettle and boil, covered, for 30 minutes.

title: waffles au dave
directions: Add dry ingredients in appropriate size bowl.
Add enough milk to form loose paste.
Add the eggs, shortening and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Batter should be just pourable.
Add milk to adjust. Bake.

title: cranberry delight spread
directions: Blend all together with a mixer. Refrigerate. Garnish with a small mint leaf, slice of cranberry or zest of orange. Serve with crackers.

title: old-fashioned devil's food cake
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients in a 10-inch skillet; set aside. Mix together next 3 ingredients and set aside.

title: chicken pupu chunks
directions: Skin (and debone if necessary) chicken breasts and cut into 1 inch square pieces.
Mix egg and water, add flour, sesame seed, and salt; stir to smooth batter.
Fill heavy saucepan or deep fryer 1/3 full with cooking oil.
Dip chunks in batter and fry four or five at a time until golden and fork tender (about five minutes).
Serve with a mixture of shoyu and Chinese mustard; add a small amount of pineapple juice for a different, tangy taste.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Pour pumpkin pie mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sift 3/4 of the box of yellow cake mix over pie mix.
Sprinkle pecans on top of cake mix.
Melt butter and drizzle over top of pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream.

title: pumpkin pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and pour into unbaked pie crust. Preheat oven to 350° and bake about 40 minutes.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Cover bottom of pan with dried beef.
Wrap chicken in bacon.
Lay on top of beef.
Sprinkle with black pepper.
Mix soup and sour cream together.
Pour over chicken.
Seal with lid or aluminum foil.
Bake 3 hours at 275° to 300°.
Oven may vary.
Serves 6.

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on box.
On low speed, mix in sour cream and then half of Cool Whip.
Make a layer of cookies and bananas and pour pudding mixture over them.
Put remaining Cool Whip on top.

title: glazed corned beef
directions: Cook corned beef on low flame until fork pierces meat easily (a few hours).
Boil ingredients for a few minutes.
After corned beef cools, dot top half with cloves (about 12).
Pour glazing over corned beef and bake for 30 minutes (cover with foil).
Slice when cooled.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Bake 1/2 of batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: sweet-potato puff
directions: Peel and rinse potatoes.
Cover with water.
Bring to a boil and boil until tender; drain potatoes and mash.
Beat eggs, cream, salt, sugar and spices together, then beat into mashed potatoes. Whip until fluffy.
Start oven at 350°.
Butter a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Pile whipped potatoes in baking dish.
Press marshmallows lightly into potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, for about 30 minutes, or until marshmallows are puffy, melting and brown. Makes 5 or 6 servings.

title: chili
directions: In large pot, brown ground chuck with onion and garlic; drain fat.
Return meat to pots and add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil, stirring occasionally.
Turn heat to low and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: crocked beef
directions: Mix in crock-pot, cover and cook on low for 8 hours or on high for 4 to 5 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: grape pie
directions: Squeeze grape pulp out of skins.
Keep skins separate.
Cook pulp until seeds start to come to top (about 10 minutes).
Strain in colander.
Discard seeds.
Cook pulp and skins together to add color.
Add sugar to taste.
Thicken mixture and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle a little flour and sugar over grapes.
Put on top crust and bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: italian chicken(microwave)
directions: Arrange chicken in 12 x 8-inch microwave baking dish.
Top with mushrooms and onions.
Pour sauce over.
Cover with wax paper and microwave on High for 22 minutes or until chicken is nearly done.
(Rotate chicken 1/2 way through.) Let stand 5 minutes (covered).
Check for doneness, if not done, microwave an additional 5 minutes.

title: lemon pecan cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add sifted dry ingredients, fruit and nuts. Grease and flour a tube pan.
Bake 2 hours in a 300° oven, or until done.
Some ovens may take 3 hours.

title: really fast fish fillets
directions: Line your broiler pan bottom with aluminum foil (you can use any baking dish you want).
Dot with dabs of margarine.
Salt and pepper fish.
Place in pan.
Dot fish with dabs of margarine. Pour the wine and splash the lemon juice over the fish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes (or until fish flakes).

title: cherubs
directions: Mix flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt, oleo, 1/2 cup brown sugar and nutmeats and put in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan in a 375° oven.
Set in oven until other is ready.
Mix the coconut, eggs, vanilla, salt, white and brown sugar together and pour over the mixture in the pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: sweet potato surprise
directions: Place potatoes in greased casserole dish.
In a saucepan, combine brown sugar, cornstarch, salt, cinnamon, orange and 1 cup apricot juice drained from apricots.
Then cook mixture over medium heat until boiling for 2 minutes.
Add apricots, butter and pecans.
Pour total mixture over sweet potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Sift flour and salt into medium sized mixing bowl and form a well.
Place eggs and milk inside of well and beat lightly. Gradually mix flour and egg batter by hand.
When dough mixture becomes moderately stiff and can be rolled out, turn it out onto a lightly floured board and knead.
Roll very thin on floured board; let dry 20 minutes.
Roll up and cut into 1/4-inch strips.
Unroll. Spread out and let dry 2 hours or until breakable.
Freeze or store in container until needed.

title: herbed-yogurt baked tomatoes
directions: You will also need vegetable cooking spray.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage and cheese, then add Bisquick mix.
Form into small balls and bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until light brown.

title: rita's coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box; let cool.
When cake is cool, poke holes in top with fork.
Mix cream of coconut and Eagle Brand milk, then pour over top of cake.
Mix Cool Whip and coconut.
Spread over top of cake.
Sprinkle rest of coconut on top.
Bake in oblong pan.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Melt butter.
Add garlic.
Saute 2 minutes.
Stir in broth and tortellini.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and add spinach and cheese.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Open can of shrimp first; put them in a bowl.
Add water and ice.
Mix other ingredients.
After all mixed, drain the shrimp and add to the rest of the ingredients.
Cover and set in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: russian bonbons
directions: In large bowl, beat butter and granulated sugar until creamy. Beat in flour and cream of wheat cereal until well blended.
Stir in walnuts and vanilla.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes at 350° or until lightly golden.
Cool slightly.
While still warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Cool completely on wire rack.

title: quick chicken and rice
directions: Wipe chicken pieces with paper towels.
Mix salt, pepper, Accent and paprika together.
Sprinkle over chicken and set aside.

title: delicious potluck potato casserole
directions: Mix partially thawed potatoes, undiluted soup, 1/2 cup butter, salt, pepper, onion, sour cream and cheese.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix corn flakes with remaining 1/4 cup butter. Sprinkle on top of potato mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Serves 12 to 15.

title: vegetable lasagna(yield:  1 pan)
directions: Prep Instructions:
Mix the salt and pepper with the Ricotta cheese; set aside.
Bake the zucchini and yellow squash for 5 minutes at 375°.
Saute the mushrooms, onions, garlic, red pepper and green pepper in the vegetable oil until all liquid is absorbed, approximately 8 minutes.

title: freezer cucumbers
directions: Sprinkle the salt on the cucumbers and onions. Place in the fridge. Heat the sugar and vinegar until dissolved. Let cool. Squeeze cucumbers and onions and pack in freezer boxes. Pour vinegar and sugar mixture on pickles and freeze. Can eat after 4 days.

title: cheese filled meat loaf
directions: Roll on waxed paper 10 to 12 inches; then put Mozzarella cheese on top.
Roll up and seal ends.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered with foil.
Drain juice.
Pour on the saved tomato sauce. Bake 15 minutes more.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix well; form balls.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: cheddary pasta and vegetables
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, prepare macaroni according to package directions.
Add carrots, broccoli and pepper for the last 5 minutes of cooking time.
Drain.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt margarine in heavy pan.
Add syrup, salt and sugar. Bring to a boil and boil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and baking soda; stir.
It will foam up.
Pour over corn in large, shallow pan.
Put in 250° oven for 45 minutes. Stir every 15 minutes.
When cool, place in a covered container. I use a large aluminum pan; turkey size.

title: fudge
directions: Mix cream, margarine and sugar on low heat and bring to a boil.
Stir all the time.
Boil for seven minutes.
Add chocolate chips and vanilla.
Stir until chips are melted.
Pour onto a wax paper-lined pan and cool.
Cut to desired size.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix well. Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix corn flakes and butter.
Spread on top of potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until bubbly all over and brown on top.

title: wilds casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; then layer in casserole dish in the order they are given.
Bake until Tater Tots are done.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, cheddar and the mix together.
Cover with chopped pecans.
Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: easy, but elegant gazpacho
directions: Place all ingredients except the olive oil in a blender, and blend for 10 seconds.
Strain and chill thoroughly.
Stir in olive oil and mix well.
Add more V-8 juice to achieve the ideal consistency.
Serve chilled with cucumber cubes, chopped onion, chopped green pepper and herbed croutons in separate bowls.

title: easy brunswick stew
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion.
Drain.
Put in crock-pot with remaining ingredients and cook for 6 hours on slow temperature.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Add remaining 6 ingredients to cooked broccoli and onion. Bake at 275° to 300° for 1 hour.
Bake slow, so it's not watery. Crumble one tube Ritz/Town House with 1/2 stick margarine.
Top casserole with topping with 10 minutes to go in cooking time.

title: streusel coffee cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together, then add melted butter; mix with a fork.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening and blend in well beaten egg mixed with milk.
Spread half of batter in greased oblong pan 6 x 10-inch, sprinkle with half the streusel mixture, add other half of batter and sprinkle with remaining mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until tender enough to stick with a fork but still firm.
Cool, peel and cut into pieces and place in dish. (I use 4 or 5 large potatoes.)
Stir together Karo, margarine, water and sugar.
(Double these ingredients if you have a large dish of potatoes.)
Pour over potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients mixed together.
Cook at 400° until thick.
If necessary, place foil over top of potatoes after they have cooked for a while so that they won't scorch on top.

title: bran muffins
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, salt and baking powder; set aside. In a large bowl, combine bran and milk; let stand 3 minutes.
Add egg and oil to flour mixture.
Combine all and bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil spaghetti.
Boil chicken and onion.
Combine soup, mushrooms and broth from chicken.
Layer dish with spaghetti, cheese and mushroom soup mix.
Heat in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: mushroom pilaf
directions: Saute mushrooms and onions in butter, until onions are transparent.
Add rice and stir until rice is completely coated. Heat broth.
Add slowly to rice.
Add in remaining ingredients. Place in 9 x 13-inch oblong baking pan and cover tightly with aluminum foil, because you want it to steam.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.
Watch carefully last few minutes, because rice will dry out quickly.

title: merry sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In bowl, combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Beat in flour mixture.
Stir in 1 cup morsels.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets; shape into balls.
Gently press 3 or 4 remaining morsels on top of cookies.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes. Let stand on cookie sheets for 2 minutes.
Remove; cool.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: creamy chicken and mushrooms
directions: In a large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon oleo.
Add chicken; cook until done.
Remove from skillet.
Reduce heat.
Add 1 tablespoon oleo to skillet.
Cook mushrooms, onion and garlic until onion is tender.
Stir often.
Stir in soup, milk and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet with other ingredients and cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Stir often.
Serve over hot noodles.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Remove tops and seeds from peppers.
In a skillet brown beef and onions.
In a large kettle bring water to a boil.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Remove and drain.
Cook rice according to package.
Drain drippings off of hamburger and add tomato sauce, herbs, salt and pepper.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in rice.

title: reindeer crunch
directions: Dump all ingredients into a roaster pan and toss to mix. Sprinkle with salt and garlic salt.
Pour this mixture over all: melted butter, Worcestershire sauce and soy sauce.
Toss again. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: pickled okra
directions: Rinse okra, drain well and pat dry.
Pack okra tightly into hot jars, filling to 1/2 in from top.
Place 1 hot pepper and 1 clove garlic in each jar.

title: beef au jus(my favorite party dish)
directions: One or even 2 days ahead, cover roast with water and bring to a boil.
Add all remaining ingredients, except green peppers; simmer for 3 hours.
Cool overnight for best results to slice; layer meat in shallow pan. Pour juice over meat.
Add more garlic salt and soy sauce.

title: rainbow ice-cream cone cakes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package. Pour 1/4 cup batter into ice cream cones, filling each about 1/2 full.
Place cones in rectangular or square pan.
Bake as directed on cake mix package for cupcakes.
Cool; frost with frosting.

title: chocolate-dipped nuts
directions: In the top of a double boiler, melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Add about 1 cup nuts to chocolate, stirring to coat well. Remove nuts individually with a fork.
Place on wax paper to set.
Repeat with remaining nuts.
Yields 4 cups dipped nuts.

title: banana pudding filling mix
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients thoroughly.
Add milk and mix with flour and sugar.
Pour mixture of sugar, flour and milk into pan and bring to boil.
Stir in 4 beaten egg yolks for 5 to 9 minutes. Remove from stove.
Add vanilla and butter.
Line pan with vanilla wafers, then pour in pudding and bananas.
Alternate in building the pie.

title: beef teriyaki kabobs
directions: Put beef in freezer for 2 hours so it will slice evenly.
Slice beef into very thin strips about 2-inches wide and 4 inches long. Mix other ingredients together and pour over steak, making sure each piece gets covered.
Let stand about 1 hour to marinate at room temperature.
Place on skewers and broil 1 to 2 minutes on each side.
Serve with rice, if desired.

title: polynesian casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Add celery, onion and green pepper.
Cook with sausage.
Bring water to boil and add soup mix and rice.
Cook for 7 minutes.
Add to meat and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add pimento and water chestnuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spicy corn bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine cheese, butter, milk and salt in a saucepan. Heat on low until melted and smooth. Add corn and tomatoes. Pour into an ungreased casserole dish and top with chips or crackers. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until hot and browned on top.

title: mother's pimento rice
directions: Cook onions and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add rice, seasonings and water; heat to boiling.
Stir once, cover and reduce heat.
Cook 15 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Add pimentos; fluff lightly with fork.
Makes 6 servings.
Serve with your favorite meat dish.

title: cinnamon hearts(not for eating, but decorating only.)
directions: Mix applesauce and cinnamon together to form a ball.
Sprinkle cutting board with cinnamon and roll out dough to 1/4-inch thick. Cut with small heart cookie cutter or any small cookie cutter.
If to be hung by ribbon, use a pencil to make a hole in top of heart. Dry on cake racks of cookie sheets in a 150° oven for 6 hours, leaving door ajar.
Happy Hearts for you!

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Allow to set on counter until room temperature.
Mix cheeses thoroughly and refrigerate until firm enough to form a ball.
Roll into a ball and roll in chopped pecans or chopped parsley. Refrigerate.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil and oranges.
Beat 3 minutes.
Bake in 13 x 9 inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: praline chiffon cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a medium mixing bowl. Make a well in center. Add oil, egg yolks, water and flavoring. Stir just until moistened. Beat egg whites (room temperature) in a large mixing bowl until foamy. Add cream of tartar, beating until stiff peaks form. Gently fold yolk mixture into egg whites. Pour batter into an ungreased 10-inch tube pan. Cool 40 minutes and remove cake from pan. Yield: One 10-inch cake.

title: one skillet breakfast
directions: Put butter into skillet add onions, peppers and sausage, cook 10 minutes. Add eggs and herbs. When eggs are almost done sprinkle cheese over the top of mixture and prepare to serve.

title: zesty broiled shrimp
directions: Saute garlic in butter.
Remove cloves when brown and discard. Set aside.
In small bowl combine remaining ingredients except shrimp.
Add butter mixture and pour 1/2 over shrimp.
Broil in single layer 4 inches from broiler for 6 minutes.
Remove from broiler, turn shrimp over and baste with remaining sauce.
Broil 3 to 4 minutes longer.
Serve with rice.

title: low-fat macaroni bake
directions: Bring water to a boil; add macaroni.
Stir constantly for 2 minutes.
Cover pan; remove from heat.
Let stand 12 minutes. Drain and rinse immediately.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
Wash rice and spread in bottom of casserole dish. Combine cream soups, melted butter, French dressing and water.
Pour about half of the mixture over the rice. Place the chicken breasts on top of the rice and pour remaining soup mixture over the chicken.
Cover with the cheese, if desired. Bake in slow oven at 275°, uncovered, for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: chicken diablo
directions: In kettle, cook noodles according to package directions. Drain.
In saucepan, mix together soup and milk.
Heat and stir until smooth. Add chicken, noodles, olives, mushrooms and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 25 minutes. Remove from oven. Top with remaining French fried onions and bake for another 5 minutes.
May substitute turkey for chicken.

title: spicy potato soup
directions: Take a large kettle, fry beef; add all remaining ingredients. Cook until potatoes are tender.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
Dice stems; set aside. Simmer mushroom caps in 1 1/2 cups water for 10 minutes.
Remove and set aside.
Mix crabmeat, margarine, bread crumbs, lemon juice and mushroom stems.
More lemon juice may be added if needed. (Stuffing needs to be wet.)
Stuff mushroom caps and place in baking dish.
Pour juice from cooked mushrooms over caps.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: vegetable lasagne
directions: Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add eggplant, onions and garlic; cook, stirring 5 minutes. Stir in tomatoes, 1 teaspoon salt, the sugar and basil. Bring to boil; reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer until eggplant is tender, 20 minutes. Makes 4 3/4 cups.

title: dianne's dressing
directions: Mix corn meal, flour, melted 1/2 stick butter, 2 eggs and milk together; bake in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 400° until cornbread is done.
Cool and crumble in a very large mixing bowl. Add finely crumbled saltine crackers.
If crackers are not crisp, place them in microwave for a few seconds to dry them out.
Add crumbled stale bread, onions, celery, celery salt, pepper, eggs and broth (or margarine and water).
Mix together well.
Batter will be very loose.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: smoked sausage and bean soup
directions: Cook onion and garlic until tender.
Add water, potatoes, sausage, beans and bouillon.
Heat to boiling, then simmer, covered, 15 minutes.
Add cabbage, tomato paste and vinegar. Simmer 30 minutes or more.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all together but save 1/2 of grated cheese to put on top. Bake in 350° oven until brown (about 1/2 hour). Use a 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.
Makes 6 to 7 servings.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Mix remaining ingredients together; add to shortening mixture.
Form into 1-inch balls; roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: beef pasties
directions: In a bowl, combine first 9 ingredients; set aside.
On a lightly floured surface, roll out 1/4 pastry into a 8 inch circle. Mound 1 c. filling on 1/2 of circle.
Moisten edges with water; fold dough over filling and press the edges with a fork to seal. Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Repeat with remaining.
Cut slits in top of each and brush with cream.
Bake at 450° for 20-25 minutes or until golden brown.
If using pre-rolled pastry, cut each circle in half.
Mound filling 1/2; fold pastry over, forming a wedge.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, oil, sour cream, water and vanilla.
Beat in eggs slowly and mix well.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured 10 inch tube or Bundt pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until cake tests done.

title: old-timey egg custard
directions: Put milk and butter in a heavy saucepan.
Heat to scalding and remove from heat.
Beat whole eggs (slightly).
Add sifted sugar, a little at a time, stirring all the while.
Add vanilla; then stir in the milk.
Put in unbaked crust and bake at 400° until firm in the middle.
Makes 2 small pies or 1 large pie.

title: dilly bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Heat cottage cheese until lukewarm. Remove from heat
and
add
sugar, onion salt, butter, dill seed, salt, soda, egg and
yeast
mixture.
Add flour gradually, beating well after each addition.
Let
rise
until double
(1 hour approximately).
Stir down and put into
bread pans.
Let rise again until light, 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake at 350°
for
30 minutes.
Brush with butter after it's out of the pans.

title: chinese barbecued pork
directions: Remove and discard fat from meat.
Combine soy sauce, wine, sugar, honey, food coloring, cinnamon and garlic in a large bowl. Add pork, turning tenderloins to coat completely.
Cover and let stand at room temperature for 1 hour or refrigerate overnight, turning occasionally.

title: festive chicken salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Combine reserved syrup and cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add pineapple and combine remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Chill and serve with cherry tomatoes and any type of crackers.

title: pie crust
directions: Whip shortening and hot water.
Add dry ingredients.
Makes 3 pie crusts.

title: frozen angel food cake dessert
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar and beat in egg yolks.
Add almond extract flavoring and cool.
Whip the whipped topping as directed. Fold into first mixture.
Slice the cake into thin slices and arrange in single layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour half of filling over slices.
Continue to arrange remaining slices on top. Top with rest of filling.
Sprinkle the chocolate bars over the top.
Freeze.

title: barbecued hamburger
directions: Brown meat in fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend thoroughly.
Cook over low heat 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve on hamburger buns.

title: fruit and cheese pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cover a 14-inch pizza pan with aluminum foil.
Cut cookie dough into 1/8 to 1/4-inch slices.
Arrange in slightly overlapping pattern in pan and press dough together to seal.
Bake until puffed and golden, about 10 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: sugar glazed walnuts
directions: Boil sugar, cinnamon and water to 238° or until strings from spoon.
Remove from heat.
Stir in nuts and cool on waxed paper. (Cools fast so have nuts ready to add.)

title: cowboy beans
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and bell pepper in skillet.
In crock-pot, mix together all other ingredients.
Add ground beef mixture and cook for 4 hours on high.
Then serve.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Spread peaches in syrup in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Layer cake mix evenly on top of peaches.
Cut butter into thin slices; cover top of cake mix. Bake until completely brown.

title: pat's pasta salad
directions: In a saucepan, blanch snow peas for 1 minute.
Remove from heat, drain and run under cold water.
Blanch broccoli for 1 minute.
Remove from heat, drain and run under cold water.
Place snow peas and broccoli in a large bowl with tomatoes, mushrooms and olives.
Cook the 2 pastas according to package directions. Drain and cool slightly.
Combine vegetables, pasta and 1 tablespoon Parmesan cheese.
Add dressing and mix well.
Chill several hours before serving.
Garnish generously with additional Parmesan cheese and serve.

title: chicken marsala
directions: In a large frying pan, melt 2 tablespoons of the butter over medium heat.
Add chicken and saute, turning once, until lightly browned, about 2 minutes on each side.
Remove and set aside. Melt remaining butter in pan.
Add shallots and mushrooms.
Cook until mushrooms are lightly browned, 3 to 5 minutes.
Add marsala and bring to a boil, scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pan.
Add cream and lemon juice and return to boil.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Return chicken to pan and cook, turning in sauce, for about 3 minutes to reheat and finish cooking.

title: sausage and cheese puffs
directions: Remove sausage from casing and brown.
Drain and break up into small pieces.
Cool completely.
Add cheese, Bisquick and water; mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes on greased cookie sheet at 400°.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Combine and set aside sugar and flour.
Bring to a boil in saucepan the oleo, cocoa and oil.
Cool.
Add all ingredients and pour into large cookie sheet and bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: easy pineapple angel food cake
directions: Mix dry cake mix and can of pineapple together in ungreased 13 x 9-inch cake pan until well blended. Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: quick barbecue sauce
directions: Slowly cook onion in butter in a saucepan until onion is tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Simmer about 15 minutes.

title: bean bake
directions: Brown meats together and drain off grease well.
Crumble bacon. Mix all together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or can put in crock-pot for several hours.

title: onion pie
directions: Mix the crushed crackers and 1/4 cup margarine together to make pie shell in 9-inch pie pan.
Saute onions in 2 tablespoons margarine on low heat until wilted and then pour in pie crust. Mix milk and eggs together with fork and pour over onions.
Put grated cheese on top of pie.
Bake on 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Shred bread.
In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, place one layer of bread and follow with a layer of pineapple, cherries, pecans and Cool Whip.
Start over with a layer of bread, etc.
Refrigerate overnight for best results.
Great for diabetics!

title: apple-pecan cobbler
directions: Combine pie filling and pecans in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes, until mixture is hot and bubbly.
Combine biscuit mix and brown sugar in a bowl.
Stir in buttermilk, mixing well.
Drop biscuit dough in 6 spoonfuls onto hot pie filling.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg; sprinkle over dough.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 3 to 4 1/2 minutes, giving dish 1/2 turn after 1 1/2 minutes.

title: texas ranch cake
directions: In large pan, mix the first 3 ingredients.
Bring to boil; remove from heat.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Pour all into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan (jelly roll pan).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese toast
directions: In a shallow dish, whisk together the eggs and the mayonnaise. On a plate combine well the Parmesan, the Romano, the paprika and the cayenne.
With cookie cutters, cut out 1-inch shapes such as rounds and triangles from the bread.
Dip the bread in the egg mixture and coat it all over with the cheese mixture, transfering it to a well-buttered baking sheet as it is coated.
Bake the toasts in a preheated 400° oven for 12 minutes, or until the tops are golden, turn them and bake them for 3 minutes more.
Makes 24 cheese toasts.
Serving 6 to 8.

title: edna's fruitcake
directions: Chop fruit into small pieces.
Add 1 cup sugar.
Add WHOLE pecans.
Stir very good and set aside.
In another bowl, mix 1 cup sugar, flour, eggs, salt and vanilla.
Mix together good and add to first mixture.
Mix very good.
Grease and flour (I use Baker's Joy) a Bundt or tube pan.
Pour in mixture.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: easy pea salad
directions: Chop eggs and onion.
Mix in drained peas, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix with mayonnaise.
If more is needed, double recipe.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and spoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sausage and cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese with a little milk.
Mix browned and drained meats with tomatoes and chilies.
Stir in cheese.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: yum-a-settie
directions: Brown hamburger with onion, salt, pepper and sugar.
Add tomato soup.
Cook noodles until tender; drain.
Add cream of chicken soup to noodles.
Layer in a casserole dish with cheese between layers.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: roast venison
directions: In a shallow dish, combine first 4 ingredients.
Place venison in marinade.
Cover and chill at least 8 hours, turning occasionally.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place meat on a rack in a roasting pan, fat side up.
In a small saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in 1 cup marinade.
Insert meat thermometer in thickest part of meat, not touching bone or fat.
Place meat in oven and roast about 3 hours, allowing 25 minutes per pound for medium rare.
Baste occasionally with marinade mixture.
Serve with sour cream gravy.

title: red beet juice for eggs and beets
directions: Mix the above ingredients and then add eggs or beets.
Allow to stand for several hours.

title: apple crunch
directions: Cook chopped apple in microwave for 2 minutes on High.
Mix apple and all other ingredients together.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake in conventional oven 10 minutes at 350°.

title: garden salad
directions: Take the ingredients and place in a large bowl in layers.
Use as much or less dressing as you please.
You need enough to coat lettuce and eggs good.
Slice red onion and put on the top. Refrigerate.
Serve cold or at room temperature.
You can make it ahead of time.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Don't add dressing until ready to serve.

title: monkey bread
directions: Add shortening, salt and sugar to 1 cup boiling water.
Add beaten eggs to yeast mixture.
Gradually add flour.
Mix thoroughly.
Cover and let double in size.
Knead down and form into balls.
Dip each ball in melted margarine.
Place in a Bundt pan or in two loaf pans.
Let rise.
Bake at 350°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend all ingredients with mixer.
Divide between the 2 pie shells.
Freeze at least 12 hours.
Thaw 8 hours before serving. Put Cool Whip on top of pies.

title: pepper cole slaw
directions: Prepare cabbage and peppers.
Toss in a bowl to mix.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Pour over cabbage.
Mix well.
Cover and chill.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the sugars and Crisco.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Mix well and add the peanut butter.
Sift flour, soda and salt and add gradually.
Form balls (walnut size) and bake at 375°.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fruit pizza
directions: If you use the roll sugar cookie mix, you will need to slice roll as if you were making cookies.
Then placing the cookie by starting in the center of the pan (spray with Pam) working your way out.
If you use the box cookie mix, follow the directions on the box, then just place dough on pan and use your hands to spread the dough around on the pan so it is all covered.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until it is a golden color.

title: chicken tetrazzini(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Blend 3 tablespoons oil with flour until smooth.
Add salt and broth, stirring until smooth and thickened.
Add mushroom soup; stir until smooth.
Remove from heat.

title: grandma temple's cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, blending well.
Combine flour, soda and salt and add to mixture. Mix well.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and oatmeal.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: strawberry cheese dip
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients together in a food processor or blender for 1 to 2 minutes. Add enough mayonnaise to hold mixture together. Shape on platter or put into a mold.
Cover with Saran Wrap and chill overnight.
Before serving, top with strawberry jam. Serve with Ritz or Wheatsworth crackers.

title: fat free oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray cookie sheet with light spray. Add ingredients in order and mix well (batter will be stiff). Drop by teaspoon.
Bake 10 minutes or until firm.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix carrots, pepper and onion.
Set aside.
Bring to a boil rest of ingredients.
Cool and add to carrot mixture.
Refrigerate overnight before serving so flavors can meld.
Keeps in refrigerator indefinitely.

title: cheese dip
directions: Cook ground beef on medium but do not brown; drain.
Cut cheese in chunks and place in large bowl.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and melt in microwave or slow cooker.
Drain cooked meat and mix well. Serve with your favorite chip or Tostitos.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, margarine, evaporated milk and cocoa 1 1/2 minutes to a full boil.
Remove from heat and add oats, vanilla and peanut butter.
Remember to mix all ingredients well and drop (cookies) on a wax paper.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground chuck in skillet.
Crumble into small pieces. Set aside.
Put can of soup through blender about 1 minute.
Add to beef and mash with a fork until it looks like rice.
Cover pan and simmer on low for 20 minutes.
Add all other ingredients into a large saucepan.
Add beef mixture when done.
Cook thoroughly or until flavors blend (about 20 minutes).

title: judy's quick cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill for 2 hours.

title: jalapeno pepper corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 9x13 pan.
Bake approximately 40 minutes until brown at 400°.
Freezes well! Serves 18.

title: hot artichoke spread
directions: Make sure artichokes are well drained and cut up fine.
Mix with rest of ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownie mix according to package directions.
Let cool and crumble.
Break up the candy bars in small pieces.
In 9 x 9-inch pan, layer the ingredients, starting with the crumbled brownies, then the pudding, then whipped cream and the Heath candy bar bits.
Repeat until all ingredients are used up.
Good!

title: luscious potato casserole
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Fold in potatoes; pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: pavlova
directions: Whip egg whites until they form peaks.
Gradually add sugar, vanilla and vinegar.
Continue beating until very stiff.
Spread waxed paper or brown paper (cut into a circle, slightly larger than desired size of dessert) on a cookie sheet.
Put mixture onto paper and shape with slight hollow in center.
Bake mixture one hour at 250°.
Turn off oven and leave for several hours to dry. Top with fresh fruit and whipped cream.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook onions in margarine in Dutch oven over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until onions are tender and just begin to brown.
Sprinkle with flour.
Gradually stir in 1 can of broth. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Stir in remaining broth, the water and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat. Simmer uncovered 5 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Wash, pare and core apples.
Cut in 1/4-inch slices.
Butter baking dish and put in sliced apples.
Pour the water over them. Work the sugars, flour and butter together until crumbly.
Spread over apple mixture and bake, uncovered, 45 minutes at 350°.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together after the cheese has softened. Shape into a ball and pat on nuts.
Add more pineapple juice if stiff.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Flatten biscuits and put in muffin pans to that the biscuits make a cup.
Brown ground beef with onion.
When beef is browned, add barbecue sauce to make a thick sauce.
Pour beef mixture in biscuit cups and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pecan rolls
directions: Prepare muffin pans by spreading thickly with creamy mixture made by creaming together 3 tablespoons butter and 6 tablespoons brown sugar.
Put 2 or 3 pecan halves into each muffin cup.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; cut in shortening.
Add milk, stirring only until dough holds together.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crumbs with 1/2 cup margarine (melted).
Put in 14 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cream 1 cup margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Spread over crust.
Cover with bananas.
Sprinkle with pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
Garnish with cherries and nuts.
Chill thoroughly. Better if made the day before.
Serves 20.

title: betty's lo-cal chicken casserole
directions: Brown chicken, saute onion and place in baking dish.
Cover with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, covered, and 1/2 hour, uncovered (total 1 hour).

title: hamburger dip
directions: Brown together the hamburger, onion and garlic.
Add tomato sauce, oregano and cream cheese.
Top off with Parmesan cheese.

title: zucchini bread squares
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed. Mixture will lightly coat zucchini. Spread in 9 x 9 pan and bake at 325 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients and allow to set overnight.
Recipe may be halved or doubled and canned according to canning directions.

title: methodist hospital pea and cheese salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together gently, adding more cheese or mayonnaise, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: gingerbread men
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix molasses with brown sugar, egg and shortening.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring to make a soft dough.
Chill for 1 hour.
Roll out dough to 1/4-inch thickness and cut with cookie cutter.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Makes 18 (4-inch) men.

title: cheese and bacon frittata
directions: Mince
onion,
grate
cheese and melt butter.
Cook and crumble
bacon.
Mix all ingredients; pour into a buttered 9 x 9-inch
pan.
Bake
at 400° for 20 minutes.
We usually cut it into pieces and put it in warm rolls with a slice of meat, and it's really good.
It also makes a nice supper.

title: curried chicken & broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Cook broccoli in microwave as directed on pkg, or until tender.
Drain and arrange in a shallow greased pyrex baking dish.
Place chopped chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayo, lemon juice, and curry powder.
Pour and spread on top of chicken.
Sprinkle croutons on top and bake, 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Sprinkle cheddar cheese on top of croutons and continue baking for 10 minutes, or until cheese is melted.

title: lasagna
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, brown the ground beef, green pepper, onions, celery and garlic; drain excess fat.
Add basil, salt, oregano, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, tomatoes, tomato sauce and mushrooms.
Simmer, covered, for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: nice rice
directions: Heat oil in a heavy pot with lid and add rice.
Keep stirring as rice changes color.
Add almonds and stir.
When rice and nuts are golden brown, add onion, salt, pepper and Tabasco to sauce. When ingredients are brown and smoking, pour in chicken stock and cover pot.
Quickly reduce heat and simmer for about 30 minutes until all liquid is absorbed.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: date balls
directions: Cook dates, butter and sugar until it comes to a boil, stirring constantly.
Beat egg, milk and vanilla.
Add to cooked date mixture and boil 2 minutes more.
Cool and add Rice Krispies. Form into balls with buttered hands.
Roll in coconut.

title: chocolate coconut bars
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 15 minutes before cutting.

title: highland pot roast
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Brown beef in shortening in Dutch oven on medium heat.
Arrange vegetables around meat.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top meat with apricots and mushrooms.
Pour catsup over all; cover.
Bake 2 hours or until meat and vegetables are tender.
Add a little water if a thinner gravy is desired. Makes 8 servings.

title: butter riches
directions: Cream together butter, brown sugar and sugar.
Add flour. Chill.
Then shape into balls.
Place on greased baking sheet. Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 9 minutes.

title: old-fashioned pole beans
directions: Clean and remove strings from beans; cut beans into 2-inch pieces.
Place ham hock in water in Dutch oven; bring to boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add beans, salt and pepper; continue cooking for 45 minutes or until tender.
Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: linguine salad
directions: Cook pasta.
Add salt to water and a little oil to keep pasta from sticking.
Drain and rinse.
Mix in large bowl with all other ingredients.
Chill.
Toss and serve.
Serves 20 or more people.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Mix sugar, Carnation milk, and marshmallows in a large saucepan.
When it starts to boil, let it boil for 6 minutes. Remove from heat and add chocolate chips, butter, and vanilla. Stir until mixed well, add pecans, and pour into buttered dish.

title: company fish
directions: Mix dressing and lemon juice.
Marinate fish in dressing at least 3 hours.
Place marinated fillets in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake, covered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Combine shortening, salt and sugar.
Add egg.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add small amounts of flour to creamed mixture alternately with pineapple juice.
Sprinkle brown sugar on bottom of deep 8 x 8-inch pan, well-greased.
Arrange pineapple slices on sugar and pour batter over all.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: modeling clay (to eat)
directions: Have children wash hands.
Mix honey and peanut butter.
Add enough powdered sugar to make it workable, then let children sit at table and mold and eat.
When they are full and tired of the game, remainder can be stored in a covered container for another time.

title: beef meatball stroganoff
directions: Combine ground beef, bread crumbs, milk, egg, Worcestershire sauce and seasonings.
Mix. Shape into small meatballs.
Brown meatballs in oil until done.
Remove meatballs; drain, saving about 1 tablespoon.
Add onion, cook until tender.
Add cream cheese, water and mushrooms.
Stir over low heat until cream cheese is melted.
Fold in meatballs; serve over hot noodles.

title: pizza style cube steak
directions: Place cube steak in baking pan.
Spread tomatoes over meat. Sprinkle all other ingredients over cube steak (except cheese). Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese; bake until cheese is golden.

title: strawberry jello
directions: Dissolve
jello
in boiling water.
Let cool
a
while, then add
crushed
pineapple and strawberries.
Put
half
of mixture in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Let set.
Spread sour	cream over it (you may not need the whole carton).
Add mashed bananas to the other
half and spoon over the sour cream.
Put in refrigerator and chill until top layer is set.

title: skillet pork chops and beans
directions: Spray skillet with cooking spray and heat over medium heat for 1 minute. Brown pork chops. Set aside. Remove skillet from heat. Spray with cooking spray. Add onion and celery and cook until tender. Add beans and brown sugar. Heat to a boil. Return pork chops to pan. Cover and cook over low heat for 5 minutes.

title: red hot pickles(like candy apples)
directions: Cover cucumbers with lime and 8 1/2 quarts water.
Set 24 hours.
Drain and wash.
Soak in cold water 3 1/2 to 4 hours. Drain.
Simmer cucumbers in next 3 ingredients with enough water to cover cucumbers for 2 hour.
Drain and throw away liquid.
Bring next 5 ingredients to boil.
Add cucumbers.
Set overnight.
Drain and reheat syrup 3 times (morning, evening and next morning).
On third day, pack and seal.
Process 5 to 10 minutes.
