title: dreamy chocolate pie
directions: In heavy saucepan over medium heat, melt chocolate with sweetened condensed milk and salt.
Cook and stir until very thick and fudgy, 5 to 8 minutes.
Add water; cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Cool to room temperature.

title: hungry man surprise
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Season with garlic salt; drain. Add cream of mushroom soup and a can of mushrooms, if desired. Stir together; season to taste.
Serve over mashed potatoes and corn.
Serves 4.

title: chicken szechuan style
directions: Heat oil in well seasoned cast-iron skillet or nonstick skillet.
Add chicken and saute until it begins to brown, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, in medium-size bowl, combine stock, soy sauce, honey, ginger, garlic, hot pepper sauce and tomato paste. Pour over chicken.
Reduce heat; cover loosely and simmer until cooked through, 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with scallions.
Serve with rice or thin noodles.

title: baked beans with hamburger
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together.
Add in beans and rest of ingredients and heat.

title: chess and fruit pie
directions: Cook peaches until tender.
When water has cooked out, add 1 cup sugar and mash with potato masher.
Put in refrigerator and cool.
Spread 1/2 of fruit in bottom of pie shell (enough for 2 pies).
Mix with spoon the eggs, sugar, butter and vanilla.
Pour on top of fruit.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: brown rice
directions: Place rice in casserole dish.
Pour soups on top of rice. Place margarine on top of rice and soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old-fashioned taffy
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a small Dutch oven; cook, without stirring, over medium heat just until mixture reaches crack stage (270°).
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour candy onto a well buttered 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan or slab of marble.
Let cool to touch; pull candy until light in color and difficult to pull.
(Butter hands if candy is sticky.)
Divide candy in half and pull into a rope, 1-inch in diameter.
Cut taffy into 1-inch pieces; wrap each piece individually in waxed paper. Yield:
about 40 (1-inch) pieces.

title: stroganoff(microwave)
directions: Cook rice or noodles conventionally while microwaving sauce. In 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine beef mix and mushrooms.
Stir flour into water until smooth. Blend flour mixture, bouillon and Worcestershire sauce into meat mixture.
Microwave on High 3 to 6 minutes or until hot and thickened.
Stir in cream cheese until melted.
If necessary, microwave on High 1/2 to 1 1/2 minutes or until heated. Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: never fail chess pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, cornmeal, salt, butter, cream and vanilla.
Blend well before pouring into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: mom's millionaire candy
directions: Melt together caramels, milk and margarine.
Add the pecans. Stir; drop on wax paper.
Let cool in refrigerator.
Melt in double boiler Hershey's Kisses and wax.
Dip candy and place on wax paper.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all
ingredients
in mixer or blender and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake
in a 350° oven until firm.
(This is real good and light.
Top with Cool Whip.)

title: the easiest loaf of bread you'll ever bake
directions: To Knead It:
Lightly flour board to prevent sticking. Fold far end of dough back over on itself towards you. Press dough away with heels of hands.
After each push, rotate dough 90°.
Repeat process for about 3 minutes.
Let dough rest while you scrape out and grease mixing bowl.
Knead dough again about 3 more minutes, until bouncy and smooth.

title: alaskan moose roast
directions: Braise moose roast in shortening/bacon grease on both sides until golden brown.
Put braised roast in roasting pan.
Surround with vegetables and cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Reserve drippings; add desired amount of water to make gravy.
Bring to boil and thicken with cornstarch paste.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

title: ham fun buns
directions: Mix margarine with mustard, onion, poppy seed and Worcestershire sauce.
Spread on top and bottom of buns.
Put ham and 1 cheese slice on each bun.
Wrap in foil.
Heat 20 to 30 minutes, if chilled in refrigerator.
If prepared and frozen, bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: nonstick clay
directions: Cook 3 to 5 minutes or until it is rolled into a ball.
This is good for schools!

title: carnation five minute fudge
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan over medium heat. Heat to a boil, cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
(Begin timing when mixture bubbles around edges of pan.) Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir 1 to 2 minutes (or until marshmallows melt).
Pour into buttered 8 or 9-inch square pan. Cool.
Cut in squares.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: broccoli 'n cheese
directions: Cook onion in 4 tablespoons butter until tender.
Stir in flour.
Add milk gradually and cook slowly until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add salt, pepper, egg yolk and cheese.
Pour 1/2 of sauce into a greased baking dish.
Arrange broccoli on top of sauce, cover with remaining sauce, sprinkle with bread crumbs and dot with remaining butter.
Bake in a hot 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream
butter
and
sugar
until fluffy.
Sift together flour, baking
powder
and salt.
To butter and sugar mixture, add eggs, one
at
a	time, beating after each addition.
Add flour mixture, milk and flavorings.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.

title: hot tuna sandwiches
directions: Combine ingredients and mix lightly.
Fill buns and wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Add the blueberries and stir.
Place in the pie shell; sprinkle with the lemon juice.
Dot with butter.
Adjust top crust and bake in hot oven at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: haggis
directions: Wash stomach with cold water.
Bring to a boil in a pan of water, scrape and clean; leave overnight.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: In small bowl stir together soup and sour cream until smooth. In small saucepan over medium heat, cook margarine, onion and chili powder until onions are tender. Stir in chicken and 2 Tbsp. of soup mixture. Remove from heat. In center of tortillas spread 1/4 c. of chicken mixture, fold sides over filling and place seam-side down in greased 12 X 8 baking dish. Spread remaining soup mixture over enchiladas. Cover with foil. Bake 15 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese, bake uncovered for 5 extra minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: *Or 2 1/2 cups self-rising flour.

title: lemon torte
directions: Mix butter,
flour and walnuts together like pie crust. Pat into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: irish stew
directions: Brown hamburger with onion; drain.
Add tomatoes, corn and diced potatoes.
Add a little hot sauce, if desired.
Cook until desired consistency, about 1 hour.
Serve with corn bread.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Cook the first 6 ingredients until forms a soft ball.
Take off heat.
Add the soda; stir good.
Pour over the popcorn.
Cover popcorn thoroughly.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Spray an 8 x 8-inch baking dish with non-stick cooking spray. Melt margarine (or butter) in a large mixing bowl. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into baking dish. Bake about 30 minutes until set and light brown.

title: tavern lemon sherbet punch
directions: Blend lemon juice and club soda thoroughly.
Serve at once over ice in stemmed glasses.
Strawberries on top.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a 13 x 9 inch buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Top with crushed corn flakes and dot with margarine.
Bake 30 more minutes.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large mixer bowl, beat eggs until foamy, about 3 minutes.
Beat in flour, sugar and brown sugar until well blended.
Stir in walnuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until top is golden brown and knife inserted halfway between edge and center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Serve with whipped cream as a garnish.

title: party dip
directions: Place in layers in order of ingredients (heavier stuff first) in a small casserole dish or cake pan.
Put in oven or microwave until warm.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach as package directs.
Mix all ingredients and roll into balls; bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: poppy's good old chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain well.
In 5 to 6-quart pan, bring water to broil.
Add seasonings and meat.
Stir constantly to keep from sticking.
Add tomato juice and bring to a boil, stirring. Add more salt if needed to taste.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Beat the eggs, then mix in flour.
Add butter, cheese, cottage cheese and thawed broccoli.
Fold together until mixed well.
Bake in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: bean casserole
directions: Combine the beans in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Cube bacon and brown it; drain off most of grease.
Add onion and brown.
Add sugar, vinegar, catsup and mustard; simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour over beans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.
Can be made ahead.

title: mother's orange balls
directions: Mix all together.
Form into balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: steak soup
directions: Put meat on to brown; drain. Parboil onions, carrots and celery. Melt butter in a 2-quart pan; add flour mix. Add water and stir while heating until thickened; continue stirring. Add Accent, pepper, beef base and tomatoes; cook a minute. Add Kitchen Bouquet and rest of vegetables and cooked meat. Cook on medium heat for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. This soup may be frozen for later use. Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: greens and sardine salad
directions: Cut sardines into 1-inch pieces.
Place all the ingredients, except the greens, in a salad bowl and stir gently to combine.
At serving time, add the greens to the bowl and toss to coat them with the dressing.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings. Preparation Time:

title: swedish pineapple cake
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add all other ingredients and stir until blended.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Spread icing on warm cake.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Pour melted margarine in casserole dish.
Mix the milk, flour, egg and dry pudding mix with the peach juice.
Pour into casserole dish on top of melted margarine.
Place sliced peaches on top of mixture.
Cream sugar and cream cheese with mixer until creamy. Drop by spoonfuls on top of peaches.
Bake at 350° until brown around the edges.

title: creamed rice
directions: Place all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish and bake at 400° for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir after 30 minutes and again after 1 hour.
Yields 1 1/2 quarts.

title: cranberried chicken
directions: Cut breasts in half.
Thickly slice mushrooms.
Mince the garlic and saute in skillet with warm olive oil until soft.
Add the chicken and cook quickly on both sides; don't brown it.
Cut scallions in 1/2-inch pieces and add to pan, stirring until soft.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla.
In separate bowl, mix cloves, salt, flour, soda, baking powder, allspice and cinnamon. Add to batter.
Mix well.
Add walnuts, if desired.
Pour in greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: blt pasta salad
directions: In large bowl, combine mayonnaise, chili sauce, lemon juice, bouillon and sugar.
Stir in the macaroni (cooked and drained), tomatoes and onions.
Cover and chill.
Just before serving, stir in lettuce and bacon.

title: seven-layer overnight salad
directions: Rinse lettuce under cold running water; drain and pat dry. Tear into bite size pieces.
Layer lettuce, celery and green pepper in large salad bowl. Drain peas on paper towels.
Sprinkle over layers.
Add sliced red onion next.
spread mayonnaise over top, sealing to side of bowl.
Sprinkle sugar, cheese and bacon bits over top.
Chill, tightly covered, with plastic wrap.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Grease two 8-inch pans.
Sift flour, then sift all dry ingredients into mixing bowl.
Add water, vanilla and mayonnaise.
Blend all ingredients together and beat 75 to 100 strokes until smooth.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with favorite chocolate icing.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Pour 1/4 of that mixture in greased bundt pan.
Add chocolate chips and syrup.
Pour into cake pan, bake at 350 for 1 hour.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cut eggplant into one inch cubes, boil 3 minutes.
Pepper and onion may be sauteed in the butter.
Add eggplant, tomatoes, saltines, egg and milk.
Heat to boiling in same fry pan.
Pour into greased casserole and brown in a 350° oven.

title: chicken yumm yumm
directions: Place chicken in a greased casserole.
Mix chicken broth and can of soup and pour over chicken.
Add chopped, boiled eggs.
Mix flour, milk and melted margarine.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.
tags: cream of chicken soup or celery

title: healthy snack apple oat muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix dry ingredients in large bowl and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients in small bowl and add to flour mixture until dry ingredients are just moistened.
(Batter will be lumpy.)
Spoon batter into 12 muffin pan cups almost to the top of each.
Bake 25 minutes or until firm.

title: creole fish fillets
directions: Melt butter and saute celery, onions and peppers.
Mix soup with water.
Add to vegetables.
Stir and heat.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch greased baking pan.
Arrange fillets in sauce.
Sprinkle combined crumbs and cheese over.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: my mother's depression cake(no eggs)
directions: Boil together raisins, sugar, shortening and water for 5 minutes.
Cool and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° until done (pulled away from pan, etc.) about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 55 minutes or until brown on top.

title: chocolate "no bake" candy cookies
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients in large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until it reaches full boil.
Continue boiling for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour over cereal mixture.
Mix with fork until cereal mixture is well coated. Drop by teaspoonful to waxed paper.
Work rapidly.
Let stand until firm.

title: pressed salad
directions: Flatten rolls on pan; don't pull apart.
Bake according to directions on can until golden brown.
Let cool.

title: raisin cake
directions: Cook sugar, raisins, spices and water 3 minutes.
Everything but flour and soda.
Add flour and soda.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in an iron skillet or until a toothpick is clean.
Note:
May cancel salt, I do.
May ice cake if you wish.

title: quick and easy brownies
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low flame.
Stir in cocoa and sugar; turn off flame.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well. Blend in vanilla and flour, stirring until blended.
Pour into an 8-inch greased square pan.
Top with pecans.
Put into a 350° oven.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
This recipe may be doubled.

title: "special baked beans"
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Add drippings and all to the rest of the ingredients.
Bake in the roaster with lid on for 2 hours at 350°.

title: cinnamon french toast
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend at medium speed until smooth.
Coat bread on both sides.
Fry on hot griddle lightly greased with oil.

title: cheesy broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Melt cheese and butter over double boiler.
In buttered dish, layer broccoli and cheese mixture, then cracker crumbs.
Bake for 25 minutes for 350°.
Spoon off excess butter before serving.

title: date carrot cake
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Beat margarine and sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Beat in pineapple, carrots, dates and vanilla.
Combine flour, soda, cinnamon and ginger.
Gradually add flour mixture and beat until well blended.
Pour batter into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes until cake tested in middle comes out clean.
Cool completely.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serves 20.

title: cheesy broccoli soup
directions: In large stock pot put water, potatoes, celery, onion, carrots, broccoli, chicken broth, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil and simmer until vegetables are tender, 15 to 20 minutes. Blend flour with milk.
Slowly add to vegetables stirring constantly until it thickens.
Add cheese cubes and stir until melted and smooth.
Serves 4.

title: japanese salad
directions: Wash 10 ounces bean sprouts under cold running water and drain.
Cut 1 carrot and 3 green peppers into thin strips.
Cook carrot in boiling water for 1 minute.
Add sprouts and pepper. Turn off heat.
Rinse veggies under cold water.
Drain well.
Mix together in a glass bowl: soy sauce, rice or cider vinegar, vegetable oil and sesame oil.
Just before serving, toss in vegetables.
Mix well with a pinch of toasted sesame seed.
Serves 4.

title: cornmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add egg. Add dry ingredients and vanilla. Drop dough from a teaspoon onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° approximately 15 minutes until lightly browned. Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: apple cinnamon raisin rolls
directions: Mix the Bisquick and milk. Turn out dough on surface. Dust with Bisquick. Knead 10 times and roll to 1/4-inch thick. Melt the margarine; spread over dough. Sprinkle with plenty of cinnamon sugar. Put on stewed apples and raisins. Roll up and slice into 3/4-inch (approximately) rolls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown.

title: hamburg pie
directions: Cook vegetables and drain.
Fry hamburg.
Mix together in a casserole dish with tomato soup.
Make biscuits and place on top. Bake in a 425° oven until biscuits are done.

title: spaghetti ala diable
directions: Drain spaghetti and place in greased casserole dish.
Saute onions and garlic in Crisco until tender, not brown.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper, sugar, mushrooms and pour over spaghetti. Toss with fork.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: hot mustard sauce
directions: Combine mustard and vinegar in top of double boiler.
Stir well.
Cover and let stand 8 hours or overnight.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour over boiling water and cook 3 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly until thick.
Store in refrigerator. Yields 2 cups.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All and peas.
Add onions, soup and mayonnaise.
Mix well and put into a buttered casserole dish.
Pour melted butter over crushed crackers and place on top of vegetables.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: judith's italian ground beef for meatballs or hamburgers
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix well with ground beef the egg, parsley, garlic and dash of salt and pepper.
Add bread crumbs to the mixture until the beef is no longer sticking to hands.

title: coffee squares
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and egg.
Beat until creamy.
Add dry ingredients alternately to creamed mixture with coffee.
Spread in bottom pan. Sprinkle 1/2 bag bits.

title: baby applesauce
directions: Wash apples.
Quarter and core.
Cover and cook over medium heat until apples come to a full bowl.
Let cool.
Run through colander; sweeten to taste.

title: easy tuna pie(low fat)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix vegetables, tuna and soup in an ungreased pie plate.
In a bowl, stir remaining ingredients with a fork until blended and pour over tuna mixture. Bake
for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: candy pie
directions: Beat milk, pudding mixes, and 1/2 of the Cool Whip in medium bowl with wire whisk (will be thick).
Reserve 1/4 c. of the candy bars.
Fold remaining candy into pudding mixture.
Spoon mixture in crust, spreading evenly. Spread remaining whipped topping over pudding layer in crust. Sprinkle top with remaining candy.
Enjoy immediately or refrigerate until ready to serve.
(Recommend refrigerating it to let it set). If you choose you can drizzle a little melted chocolate over the top for added effect.

title: cozy's snake cheese-cheese spread
directions: Let cheese get to room temperature, if you can stand the wait. Mix all ingredients together with your hands (hard job). Separate into 3, 4, 5 or 6 parts and roll each part into a long roll.
(Like a snake about 14 to 18 inches long; whatever the diameter of a half dollar gets you.) Roll these rolls in chili powder sprinkled on a sheet of wax paper.
(This spread is not hot!)

title: corn muffins
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together.
Blend beaten egg, corn and melted butter or margarine.
Add egg mixture to dry ingredients and stir only enough to moisten the flour.
Do not beat.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake in a preheated hot oven at 425° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: donna's fudge
directions: Mix peanut butter, marshmallow and vanilla.
Set aside.
Hint: Mix the peanut butter in marshmallow jar and it will come right out.
Mix remaining ingredients well and boil for 3 minutes (no longer).
Remove from heat and mix well and fast with peanut butter mix.

title: holly's favorite cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix softened butter and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs and cream together.
Sift flour, pudding and soda into butter mixture.
Add vanilla extract and chocolate pieces.
Drop by rounded teaspoon on nonstick cookie sheet.
Bake until almost done.
Remove and cool slightly.
Freezes well while still warm.

title: laura's favorite chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375.
Combine water and soup in mixing bowl and stir.
Spread one cup of rice in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Pour soup mixture over rice and spread.
Place chicken breast on top of rice and soup and season to taste.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour.
Remove foil and bake for additional 10 minutes.
Let cool and serve with lima beans!

title: basic crepes
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender or mixer and beat well. Let batter stand at room temperature for 1 hour before using.

title: peach and sherry punch
directions: Pour sugar and sherry over peaches and set for 2 to 3 hours in refrigerator.
Then add ginger ale, lemon juice and ice.

title: grandma nina's eggless, milkless, butterless cake
directions: Boil first 6 ingredients together for 3 minutes.
When cool, add remaining ingredients.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: lime-cilantro dressing
directions: Combine olive oil, lime juice, garlic, cilantro and pepper. Process in blender until smooth.
Add sugar and salt to taste. Makes 1/2 cup, about 8 servings.

title: texas strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie shells.
Cool.
Cube 1 banana into each pie shell; set aside.
In 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, flour and pineapple; stir until thick.
Add jello and stir until dissolved. Add frozen strawberries; stir until well mixed.
Cube remaining 2 bananas into mixture and add pecans.
Mix well and pour in shells. Refrigerate for about 2 hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Add liquid from asparagus to soup.
Mix cheese with cracker crumbs.
Put layer of crumbs in bottom of casserole dish.
Add layer of asparagus.
Cover with soup.
Repeat, ending with crackers and cheese on top.
Pour melted butter over casserole. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: 7 minute dinner western skillet noodles
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add noodles, corn, 1 1/2 cans of water and chili powder.
Let simmer for 5 to 6 minutes.
Add cheese and simmer 2 minutes.
Ready to serve.

title: thelma's chocolate pudding
directions: Boil the sugar, water and cocoa; set aside to cool.
Cream together the powdered sugar and butter.
Add 3 beaten egg yolks to cream mixture, then add cocoa mixture.
Add the marshmallows, broken nut meats and vanilla.
Fold in beaten egg whites (3) and 12 graham crackers (rolled).
Sprinkle half of it in pan.
Pour in all mixture; sprinkle with crackers on top.

title: cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage and carrots.
Add onions.
Add salt and pepper to taste and about 1/4 cup sugar.
Add about 1 cup mayonnaise.
If this is not enough mayonnaise, add enough until slaw is creamy.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Pick meat from bone; reserve broth. Place small pieces of chicken in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In saucepan, mix and bring to boil soup and chicken broth.
In another bowl, mix margarine, pepper, salt, flour and buttermilk.
Pour broth mix over chicken and spoon batter over top.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spanish rice and beans
directions: In a large pot heat oil, recieto, sauce, spices and rice until hot.
In a separate pot mix 1 can chicken broth and water with washed kidney beans.
Heat until warm.
Mix two together and heat on high until all water evaporates (5 minutes).
Lower heat to low heat and cover pot.
Cook until rice is tender (about 20 minutes).

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together well the cream cheese and beaten eggs.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Spread mixture into pie crusts and bake for 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Meanwhile, mix instant pudding with milk, fold in sweet potatoes, cinnamon and Cool Whip.
Blend well. Turn potato mixture into cool pie shells.
Add Cool Whip to top and refrigerate.

title: creamed tuna on toast
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Saute onion and celery.
Add tuna, Cheddar cheese, milk, salt, pepper and garlic.
Simmer until well mixed, about 15 minutes.
Serve over toast.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fudgsicles
directions: Warm milk.
Dissolve pudding mix and sugar; blend until completely dissolved.
Pour into ice trays or popsicle molds.

title: johnny marzetti(serves 12)
directions: In large skillet saute	onions,
beef,	both
salts and pepper in 1/4 cup	of
margarine.	Stir
often;
cook macaroni until just
tender.
Drain
and
toss with 1/4 cup margarine. Place macaroni in 10 x 13-inch pan.
Add 2/3 of cheese to meat mixture; stir until cheese melts.
Add 1 can tomato sauce and mushrooms. Pour
over	macaroni.
Top	with
can of tomato sauce. Sprinkle
with
remaining
cheese.	Bake 1 hour and 40 minutes or until hot and bubbly at 350°.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Fry ground beef, onions
and butter together and put in last. Cook vegetables
until
partly soft.
Mix together; add salt to taste.
Cold pack for 2 hours.

title: pan pizza
directions: Cook meat and onion.
Drain. Add spaghetti sauce and garlic salt to taste.
Pour meat sauce into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top of meat sauce.
Mix in a bowl the eggs, milk, oil, flour and salt.
Stir until smooth.
Pour mixture over meat sauce mixture. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top of crust mixture. Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: lemon buttermilk cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and butter well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift flour and soda together.
Beginning with the flour, mix the flour and buttermilk, alternately, small amounts at a time into the shortening mixture, beating well after each addition. Add the lemon extract and the hot water.
Beat well.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Decrease heat to 250° and bake 45 minutes or until done.
Turn cake on cooling rack and spread with lemon sauce (juice of 1 lemon, 1 cup confectioners sugar and parched pecans).

title: pork chops dorothea
directions: Place pork chops in a roasting pan.
Mix tomato sauce, vinegar, brown sugar and allspice.
Simmer for 10 minutes in the pan that pork chops were browned in.
Pour over chops in baking pan.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325°, depending on thickness of chops.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Puree cream cheese, mayonnaise and garlic in food processor or blender until smooth.
Put in saucepan or microwave-safe bowl. Stir in crab meat, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and pepper sauce (mild or hot).
Warm over low heat, stirring often or heat in microwave until steaming.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Lay in bottom of 2-quart casserole. Next, layer boned chicken.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken; cover with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Top with bread crumbs.

title: pumpkin crunch
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, cinnamon, pumpkin, salt, milk and cloves. Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan lined with waxed paper.
Sprinkle 1 box yellow cake mix over mixture.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over cake mix.
Spoon melted butter evenly over nuts.
Bake at 350° until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from oven; immediately invert onto a serving tray and remove wax paper.
Cool completely.
Frost with large container of Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: welsh cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients except egg into dough.
Add beaten egg slowly.
Flour a board and roll dough to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Grease skillet and cook on low; turn when brown. Cool on a cooling rack and sprinkle with sugar when cool.

title: kentucky lake pecan bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Stir in milk, mixing well.
Dust the pecans with 1/2 cup of the flour.
Sift remaining flour and other dry ingredients together and add to the creamed mixture. Add nuts and mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake 1 hour at 350° or until the bread begins to leave the side of the pan.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Place hash browns in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soup, sour cream, cheese and 1 stick margarine.
Spread over hash browns.
Spread corn flakes over mixture.
Then pour 1 stick margarine over corn flakes.
Bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: fried tacos
directions: Brown meat and onions, then add chili seasoning.
Next, add instant potatoes that have been prepared according to package directions.
Blend 2 mixtures together.
Spoon about 1 tablespoon in flour tortillas.
Roll up and fry in skillet.

title: macintosh muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake in a 350° oven for about 25 minutes or until golden. Makes 1 dozen.

title: apple bran coffeecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease a 9x13x2 baking pan. In the bowl of the food processor fitted with the steel blade, combine the all-bran and butterscotch morsels.
Process until the mixture is fine but not powdery. Remove the blade and stir in the pecans.
Reserve 3/4 cup of this mixture.
In a large mixing bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda, sugar, eggs, butter and sour cream.
Mix well.
Stir in the apples and the bran mixture (except the reserved 3/4 cup). Pour the batter into the prepared pan. Sprinkle with reserved bran mixture.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool for about 10 minutes on a cake rack.
Drizzle with glaze. Serves 12.

title: award winning german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water, cool.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks 1 at a time, beat well after each.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift together flour and soda.
Add alternately with buttermilk to chocolate mixture and beat well.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in egg whites. Pour into 3 layer pans, lined on bottom with wax paper.
Bake in moderate oven, 350°, 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes and remove from pans.

title: aunt flossie's pickled peaches
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar and spices (tie whole spices in a cheesecloth bag) to a boil and cook gently 20 minutes.
Scald peaches.
Peel, then drop a few at a time into boiling syrup.
Cook gently just until tender but not broken.
Remove with slotted spoon and pack into hot sterilized jars.
Boil down the syrup until thickened.
Pour over fruit, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Seal process 15 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: mom's zucchini bread
directions: Beat zucchini, sugar, eggs and oil together.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Raisins may be added, if desired.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.
Leave in pan until cool.

title: lump crabmeat over pasta
directions: Saute seasoning in butter.
Add flour; stir until well blended. Add Pet milk; stir well.
Add crabmeat and bring to slight boil. Lower fire and add green onions.
Serve immediately over angel hair pasta.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in vanilla.
Combine flour and crushed chips.
Add gradually to creamed mixture, stirring
until all trace of flour is mixed into batter.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 11 to 15 minutes.

title: alicia's artichoke appetizer
directions: In a food processor, chop artichokes.
Add Parmesan cheese, mayonnaise and cream cheese and blend.
Pour mixture into a 2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: white rice
directions: Place all these ingredients together in the pot and mix well. Place the pot on the flame and bring to boil.
Reduce the flame and let it simmer and cook until the water is absorbed and the rice looks cooked to your taste.

title: baked beans - texas style
directions: Brown the meat, onion, peppers and celery. Add salt to taste. Add remainder of ingredients, mixing well.
Place in a large baking dish or pan.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 30 minutes. Serves about 20.

title: blueberry dumplings
directions: Bring first four ingredients to boil.
Cover.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add lemon juice.
Stir together dry ingredients.
Cut in butter until like coarse meal.
Add milk all at once.
Stir only until flour is dampened.

title: make ahead casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish lightly.
Put raw elbow macaroni in dish.
Add all remaining ingredients and stir well. Put foil on baking dish and put in refrigerator overnight.
Bring to room temperature.
Then bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: dutch cabbage rolls
directions: Combine and mix well the meat, salt, pepper, rice and egg. Wash cabbage leaves and boil until tender.
Put equal amounts of meat mixture into cabbage leaves, roll tightly and secure with toothpicks.
Place rolls in saucepan.

title: western meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients, mixing well.
Pack lightly in loaf pan and bake 90 minutes.
Top with seasoned tomato sauce and green pepper rings.
Makes 8 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Fry garlic in oil.
Heat sauce and puree.
Add 1 can water. After frying garlic, brown sausage and add to sauce, then brown hamburger, onions and green pepper and add to sauce after draining.
Add seasoning and simmer for 4 hours.

title: barbecued cocktail franks
directions: In a large saucepan, combine all ingredients except frankfurters.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently; reduce heat. Add franks; simmer 10 minutes.
Serve with toothpicks.
Makes 32 appetizers.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Mix onion soup mix, margarine, and vegetable oil together. Place potatoes in baking dish.
Pour soup mix over potatoes.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes, turning potatoes about halfway through baking time.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Clean the chicken from the bones
and put in bottom of pan. Put noodles over chicken.
Mix the soups, broth and sour cream. Pour over noodles.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes. While baking, make the stuffing and pour over the top of the casserole and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: bubble bread
directions: At night put frozen rolls in a greased Bundt pan.
Melt margarine.
Add
sugar
and
cinnamon.
Stir
until dissolved. Add nuts;
pour
over frozen rolls.
Cover pan with towel.
In the morning bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cupa, cupa, cup
directions: Mix and bake at 350° until gold and bubbly.

title: stewed okra and tomatoes
directions: Cook all ingredients until okra is just done.
You may want to cook in casserole in microwave.
You can put buttered bread crumbs on top and brown in conventional oven.

title: hot chicken sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Remove crusts from sandwich bread. Make sandwiches, wrap in foil and freeze.
Before heating, dip into 3 beaten eggs, then into crushed potato chips.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool slightly and cut into 1 1/2 inch squares.
Serve warm, also good cold.

title: california citrus cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add cake mix, pudding, water and oil.
Beat 5 to 7 minutes.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan for 50 minutes at 350° or until done.
Cool in pan a few minutes, then turn over on wire rack to finish.
Glaze warm cake that has been pricked all over with a fork.

title: doughnuts
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add sugar, liquids, dry ingredients and flavoring.
Chill.
On a floured bread board, pat out dough.
Cut with doughnut cutter.
Drop into hot shortening to cook.
Deep fat fryer best to use.

title: frosty cereal cups(great for kids)
directions: Empty the yogurt into a medium bowl.
Freeze, uncovered, for about 2 hours, stirring every 30 minutes until thick, but not firm.
Line 12 medium muffin cups, about 2 inches apart.
Spoon about 1 tablespoon of Trix, Lucky Charms or Cocoa Puffs cereal into each cup, forming single layer.
Top with frozen yogurt. Sprinkle with additional 1 to 2 tablespoons cereal.
Press lightly into yogurt.
Freeze for 1 hour, or until firm.
Best when served the same day.

title: normandy farm famous popovers
directions: Mix eggs, milk, salt and sugar.
Add flour and mix for 1 minute.
Do not overmix.
Preheat popover pan with 1 teaspoon of cooking oil in each cup for 10 minutes.
When hot, fill each cup 3/4 full.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 350° for an additional 30 minutes.
Be sure popovers are cooked inside to prevent from collapsing.

title: taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown meat; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and seasoning mix; simmer 5 minutes.

title: cornie bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and add corn muffin mix. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: thumbprints
directions: Cream butter, salt and vanilla until light and fluffy, gradually adding brown sugar.
Blend in flour, milk and chocolate. Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. With thumb, make depression in each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
While cookies are warm, roll in confectioners sugar. Cool and fill.

title: praline grahams
directions: Grease cookie sheet; line with whole graham crackers until full.
Preheat oven to 350°, then in saucepan, melt margarine and butter.
Add sugar and let dissolve, then cook 10 minutes, stirring all the time (it will burn if you don't).
Pour over grahams and add chopped nuts.
Bake for 10 minutes, then cool. Break into pieces.
Store.
Keeps well.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt together.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla and add sifted dry ingredients a little at a time.
The mixture will be thick.
Add zucchini; the mixture will be gummy.
Pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Check at 50 minutes; if toothpick comes out clean, bread is done.
Great hot or cold, stays moist.
May be frozen.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chili-corn pancakes(cowboy supper!)
directions: In medium bowl, pour boiling water over cornmeal and whisk quickly to mix.
Set aside to cool slightly.

title: korean barbecue meat sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients together and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Makes 1 cup of sauce.
Serve as a barbecue meat sauce dip.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and bananas.
Add salt, eggs, soda, flour and nuts.
Cook one hour at 325°.
Turn temperature down and let stay 10 minutes.

title: strawberry delight cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch greased and floured cake pan.
Bake according to directions on box.
When cake is done, remove from oven. Poke holes over entire cake. Then carefully pour pop over the entire cake.
Let cool.
When completely cooled layer strawberries over entire cake.
Then add frosting.

title: russian tea cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla together thoroughly.
Mix dry ingredients together and then add to butter mixture.
Chill dough. Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Cookies do not spread.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until set, but not brown.
While warm, roll in additional confectioners sugar.
Cool and roll again in sugar.

title: turtle cake
directions: Combine cake, butter, water, oil and 1/2 can condensed milk. Mix well.
Pour 1/2 batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Melt caramels and remainder of condensed milk over low heat until smooth.
Spread over cake layer.
Sprinkle generously with pecans.
Cover with remaining cake batter.
Return to oven and bake 25 to 35 minutes. Cool and spread with frosting.

title: hash brown potato dish
directions: Mix all ingredients but potatoes and cornflakes, then add thawed potatoes.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish (well-greased).
Mix cornflakes and 1/2 cup melted margarine and sprinkle over top of the casserole.
Bake at 400°, uncovered, for 40 minutes.
This can be frozen.

title: stuffed breast of lamb
directions: In a medium size skillet, saute onion and celery in butter. Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and remaining ingredients.
Spoon stuffing over first lamb breast which has been placed in a shallow baking dish and sprinkled with salt and pepper.
Cover with the second breast and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Secure with skewers, if desired.
Bake at 325° for about 2 hours or until tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth.
Then add peanut butter and milk, beat until smooth again.
Then fold in Cool Whip and mix; pour into crust and put in freezer.
Take out 2 hours before serving and put in fridge.
You can sprinkle with peanuts and drizzle chocolate syrup on the top.

title: crab salad
directions: Combine the crabmeat, celery and green pepper in a bowl. Combine the paprika, salt, catsup, salad dressing, lemon juice, mustard and sugar in separate bowl and mix well.
Then add to crabmeat mixture.
Toss lightly until crabmeat is well coated. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve on lettuce leaf.
Garnish with sliced hard-boiled eggs, if desired.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Measure flour into a bowl.
Cut in butter with a pastry blender until coarse crumbs form.
Add ice water, mixing with a fork, until dough forms a ball.
Wrap.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix ingredients well and beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Pour into four greased and floured layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Or bake 2 cakes and split the layers. Cool.

title: banana cake
directions: Cut Crisco into dry ingredients.
Add 1/3 cup buttermilk and bananas.
Blend with mixer for 2 minutes.
Add eggs, 1/3 cup buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Fold in nuts and pour into well-greased and floured pan.
Bake one hour in a 350° oven.
Place cake on rack 5 minutes before turning out on waxed paper to cool.
If desired, frost with Butter Cream Frosting.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix
cornmeal,	salt and sugar.
Add margarine to water and bring
to
a boil.	Add to cornmeal, mix well.
Beat eggs and milk
together
and
put
the
two mixtures together, add baking powder.
Pour into greased pan, bake in preheated oven at
350° about 30 to 40 minutes until firm and slightly brown. Serve immediately for best results.
Serves 4.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle chops with garlic salt and pepper.
Brown in nonstick skillet.
Place chops in oven casserole.
Add apple.
Combine puree and ginger ale; pour on. Bake, covered, 45 to 60 minutes.

title: potato stroganoff
directions: In a skillet, brown the beef, onion and celery.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: grannie earvil's refrigerator fruitcake
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk.
Add all other ingredients and pack in buttered pans.
Garnish with whole pecans and cherries. Refrigerate overnight.

title: no can pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in glass jar and refrigerate. Liquid will not cover pickles.
Check in the morning.
Sauce will cover pickles.
Will keep up to 1 year.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pineapple and juice in a 10 x 13-inch pan. Add pie filling.
Pour
cake
mix
dry
over that.	Melt margarine and pour over
cake
mix.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts over mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Serve warm with vanilla ice cream or cold, by itself.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup and sour cream.
Grease baking dish (bottom only). Pour small amount of soup mixture into dish just to cover bottom. Spread chicken over this and then pour remaining soup mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over mixture and pour melted margarine over crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add onions and bell pepper; saute. Add sauce and sugar; heat.
Spread thin layer of sauce on bottom of casserole, then layer noodles, meat sauce and grated Mozzarella. Keep layering ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted (about 30 minutes).
You may add mushrooms to sauce if desired.
Freezes well.

title: garlic and cheese biscuits
directions: Mix together and spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 450°.
Brush tops with melted butter and garlic powder.

title: italian pasta sauce
directions: In 20-quart stainless pot, brown ground chuck and pork.
Drain off grease.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring well. Add water to bring level to 3/4-inch of top of pot.
Simmer 24 hours using an anti-scorching device, adding water as necessary to keep level within 3/4-inch of top.
Freeze in containers until needed.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix cheese and sausage thoroughly.
Add Bisquick one cup at a time.
Roll into small balls and bake at 325° for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: In medium sized pot, bring potatoes, onion, salt and pepper to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook until potatoes are done.
Save this broth.

title: sugared carrots
directions: Cut carrots crosswise in half; cut each half lengthwise into thin slices; then cut again into stick thin strips.
Bring 1 inch of water to boil, heat carrots to boiling and reduce to low. Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until tender, drain well.
To carrots add margarine, brown sugar, salt and pepper over medium heat until margarine melts, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 accompaniment servings.

title: punkin center potatoes
directions: Scrub the potatoes (new potatoes are especially good for this recipe).
Cut them into 8 pieces each and place in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cut the bacon into pieces and place on top of the potatoes. Sprinkle the dry onion soup mix over the top.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked corn
directions: Melt butter; add flour and mix well.
Add milk gradually and bring to the boiling point, stirring constantly.
Add corn, sugar, salt and pepper and beat thoroughly.
Remove from heat and add well-beaten eggs.
Pour into a greased baking dish.

title: eric's real man broccoli and ham quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium skillet, saute mushrooms in butter until tender; drain well on paper towels.
Steam broccoli until barely fork-tender; drain well and set aside.
Blend next 8 ingredients in blender and pour into bowl and stir in mushrooms, Jack cheese and ham.
Pour half of egg and cheese mixture in ungreased 10-inch pie or quiche dish.
Place steamed broccoli on top and cover with remaining mixture.
Bake 45 minutes or until knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: american chop suey
directions: Fry onions, pepper and celery in butter.
When soft, add meat and brown.
Add tomatoes.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mexican black-eyed peas
directions: Soak black-eyed peas overnight in water.
Brown sausage.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Drain.
Add 1/2 cup water to drained peas.
Also add chili powder, sugar, black pepper, garlic salt and celery.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add water, if needed.

title: mocha mix
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Store in airtight jar.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Cook hen until tender.
Remove from broth; cool and then remove meat from bone.
Melt chicken fat and blend with flour. Season with 1 teaspoon salt and pepper to taste.
Slowly add broth and milk; stirring constantly.
Cook over medium heat until sauce thickens.
Combine cornbread crumbs with celery, onions, 1 teaspoon salt, pepper to taste, melted butter and sage.
Arrange the chicken which has been cut into bite-size pieces, and the dressing mixture in alternate layers in a very large casserole.
Cover with the sauce and bake one hour at 350°.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add sugar; beat until well blended.
Mix fruit and nuts and fold into cheese mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour mixture into oblong pan or 2 loaf pans.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer 30 minutes before serving. Cut and allow to set 5 minutes longer.
Return to freezer if you can't serve at once.

title: grandma huett's doughnuts
directions: Mix by dissolving yeast in milk containing vanilla, eggs, butter, lard, sugar and salt.
Cream until light.
Sift cake flour in mixture.
Add plain flour.
Heat 5 minutes.
Dough should be like biscuit dough.
Let rise double in size.
Turn dough on floured board.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut out with doughnut cutter.
Let rise until double in size in warm place.
Fry in deep fat.

title: cocoa
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and water in saucepan.
Simmer gently over low heat 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Pour milk into cocoa.
Heat until hot.
Do not boil.
Add vanilla and beat well.

title: vanilla cream filling for cupcakes
directions: Combine flour and milk in saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly with wire whisk, until mixture thickens and boils.
(It may form a ball, that's okay.)
Cool completely.
Cream butter or margarine and shortening.
Add vanilla and salt, gradually add powdered sugar.
Blend in cooled flour mixture until real smooth and creamy.
Fill pastry tube with filling; insert narrow tip into center of cooled cupcake.
Squeeze gently until cupcake begins to swell or to peak.
Cover hole with frosting.

title: hearty hobo stew
directions: Cook ground beef in large saucepan, stirring to crumble; pour off excess fat.
Stir in contents of envelope of seasoning mix, tomatoes, macaroni, pork and beans and water.
Cover; simmer 15 minutes or until macaroni is tender.

title: low-fat pea salad
directions: Cook macaroni until done.
Drain.
Cook egg whites and chop. In a bowl add macaroni, eggs, peas, onion, cheese and Miracle Whip.
Stir well and chill.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Blend sugar and fat with mixer.
Add other things as listed and blend well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on lightly sprayed cookie sheet.
Press slightly with floured fingertips.
Bake about 8 minutes at 375°.
Bake a bit longer for crisp cookies, less for soft cookies (dough keeps well frozen).

title: fudgie scotch squares
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl; mix well by hand.
Press mixture into a well-greased, 9-inch square cake pan (this is a very important step).

title: punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid according to package.
Add sugar and pineapple juice.
Mix in 1 gallon jar; add water to fill jar.
Pour into small containers to freeze.
You only have to take out what you need.
When you get ready to use, take out and let thaw up some. Take sharp knife and break up.
Pour ginger ale over and serve.

title: darlin' stew
directions: Put browned beef in large stew pot.
Add all ingredients at once and cook on low simmer for 2 1/2 to 3 hours, until potatoes are tender.
Can add other vegetables, corn, cauliflower, green beans, okra and broccoli.
Serve with corn bread.

title: babi ketsap(pork in soy sauce)
directions: Brown the meat in about 1/3 cup hot oil. Add the garlic, onions and nutmeg.
Mix well and add 1/2 cup water.
Add soy sauce, sugar and lemon juice. Simmer on low until done.
Finish with pepper.
(As soy sauce is usually salty, salt probably is not necessary.) Serve with rice.

title: blue cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, except parsley; blend well.
Form mixture into a ball.
Roll in chopped parsley.
Chill thoroughly.

title: microwave sliced baked potato
directions: If skin of potatoes is rough, peel.
If not, wash and scrub well. Cut potatoes in thin slices but not all the way through. Place potatoes in a microwave dish, sprinkle with melted butter or margarine, parsley, chives or sage.
Microwave for 10 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar liberally. Microwave on High until potatoes are soft and cheese is bubbly, about 6 minutes.

title: easy chicken
directions: Note:
To make ahead, cook as directed.
Cool and refrigerate or freeze to serve, thaw and reheat.

title: french green beans
directions: Drain beans; place in clear water with bacon drippings.
Boil about 5 minutes and drain again. Beat soup; add layer of beans, soup and cheese. Add onion rings last. Place in 350° oven for about 30 minutes. Top with crumbled bacon and some cheese.

title: great grandmother's crab cakes
directions: Combine ingredients; fry in butter until brown.
Serve with tartar sauce.

title: broccoli cheese noodle soup
directions: Saute the onions in melted butter.
Cook the broccoli as directed.
Boil the noodles in the water, with bouillon cubes added.
When noodles are cooked, add broccoli, milk and cubed cheese.
Stir in the flour to thicken soup.

title: crawfish soup
directions: Wash crawfish; pat dry and sprinkle with Tony's seasoning. Saute vegetables in 1 stick of oleo. Add crawfish and cook. Add soup and corn; cook about 10 minutes. Add milk, salt and pepper to taste; simmer 10 minutes. Serve over rice with crackers.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening. Add eggs and vanilla, then all your dry ingredients.
Last add chips and nuts. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes on greased cookie sheets.

title: blondies
directions: In large saucepan, melt margarine.
Add sugar and stir well. Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir after each.
Add flour and stir well.
Make sure mixture is cooled before adding chocolate morsels and nuts.
Pour mixture into two 7 x 11 x 1 1/2-inch pans or one 11 x 16 x 2-inch pan that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let cool before dumping out to cut into squares.
Yield:
3 dozen (2-inch) squares.

title: mango bread
directions: Mix flour, cinnamon, soda and salt and form a well in the center.
Add remaining ingredients; mix.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 large or 2 small loaves.
If using small pans, check in 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; press into bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: easy cherry dessert
directions: Mix pineapple and cherry pie filling and spread on bottom of large oblong pan.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Cut margarine in small pieces and place on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: crawfish supreme
directions: Before cooking crawfish tails, blot with paper towels to remove fat.
Saute tails in 1/2 stick margarine for 10 minutes.
In another skillet, saute onions and parsley in 1 stick margarine. Blend in flour.
Gradually add half and half, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add sherry, then tails, being careful not to include fat in bottom of skillet.
Season to taste.
Serve in patty shells, over toast or as a filling for crepes.
Will freeze well.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Put unbeaten egg whites, sugar, syrup and water in a double boiler; whip with rotary beater until mixture is stiff.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Put in favorite cake.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Bring water to boil; add broken spaghetti.
Cook until done; let cool.
Add chopped onion and pepper to spaghetti; add salad dressings and mix well.
Stir and mix several times before serving.
(This is better made 12 hours ahead.)

title: "de-skunking" shampoo
directions: Mix solution together and pour over dog, working it into the coat.
Make sure you have completely covered the animal.
Rinse thoroughly with tap water.

title: peach ginger crunch
directions: Preheat
oven to 250°.
Grease a deep
dish
pie
plate with the 2 tablespoons of butter.
Peel and slice peaches; mix with ginger and place in deep dish.
Sprinkle with sugar, then put on the dry cake mix.
Put pecans over
the
cake
mix
and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Melt the one stick of
butter
and drizzle
it over
the top.
Bake for 2
hours.
Garnish
with whipped cream or ice cream.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: venison taco salad
directions: Toss all ingredients just before serving.
Add chips last. Lo-cal Russian dressing can be used if you like.

title: peachy punch
directions: Stir peach nectar into honey gradually; stir in juice.
Chill until ready to serve.
Add carbonated beverage just before serving.

title: amazing cake
directions: Mix and pour batter into well-greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes for chocolate cake or 60 minutes for butterscotch cake.
Cool.
May sprinkle with powdered sugar and glaze.

title: five minute peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk together. Let come to a boil and boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and add peanut butter and marshmallow cream. Beat with spoon until thick, but not until it loses its gloss. Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cut into squares when cool.

title: oreo pudding dessert
directions: Crumble Oreo cookies; reserve 1/4.
Combine butter and Oreo crumbles and press into 13 x 9-inch dish.
Then combine vanilla pudding, milk and cream cheese and spread over crust.
Spread onto filling the whole container of whipped topping.
Sprinkle reserved cookie crumbs on top.
Chill.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise and dressing mix together.
Mix vegetables and cheese together.
Pat rolls together to form a crust on a jelly roll pan or cookie sheet and bake (at temperature on package of rolls) for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: ham-cheese-potato casserole
directions: In a saucepan, heat cheese and cream, stirring constantly until cheese is melted and sauce is creamy.
Put rest of ingredients into a 1 1/2-quart ungreased casserole.
Pour cheese mixture into casserole and stir until well coated.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: *Can use 18 ounces frozen hash brown potatoes.

title: cheese tarts
directions: Cream the oleo, sugar and egg yolks.
Add raisins, nuts, vanilla and salt.
Fold in well beaten egg whites.
Bake in tart shells or pie crust at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 16 tarts.

title: orange spice crust
directions: Crush cookies and grahams.
Mix with other ingredients.
Add more cloves and nutmeg to taste.
Pat into pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: nancy's cornbread casserole
directions: Mix and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: turtle cake
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt caramels with 1/4 cup evaporated milk.
Set mixture aside.
Beat together cake mix, 3/4 cup evaporated milk and margarine.
The batter will be thick.
Pour 1/2 of batter in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal cream cheese muffins
directions: Place oats and milk in bowl and let stand for 30 minutes.
Stir in brown sugar, oil and egg into soaked oats.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into oat mixture just until blended. Do not overmix.
Spoon half the batter into greased muffin tins. Place about a teaspoon of cream cheese into center of batter.
Top with remaining batter.
Combine oats and brown sugar for topping. Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: 5 cup salad - ambrosia
directions: Drain all of the ingredients and mix together.
Chill for several hours before serving.
Serves 6.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix all together.
Serve in a large open flat-style dish (like a large pasta bowl).

title: roasted tomato and mozzarella pasta salad
directions: Cook the pasta according to package directions. Drain and place in a large bowl.
Cut the roasted tomatoes into large chunks and add to the pasta along with the bell pepper, Mozzarella cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
Pour the salad dressing on top and toss to coat. Garnish with fresh basil leaves.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Add remaining ingredients; blend well.
Spread batter in greased, fluted, 2-quart mold or mini-Bundt pan or 9-inch square pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes; cool 10 minutes in pan.
Invert on wire rack; cool completely.
Glaze and decorate as desired.
Makes one cake.

title: chocolate torte
directions: Prepare mousse as package directs.
Line the bottom and sides of pan with ladyfingers.
Make sure ladyfingers are standing up on sides.
Pile mousse into pan.
Chill until firm.
Remove torte from pan.

title: hamburger chop suey
directions: Brown meat, onion and celery, then drain.
Combine meat mixture with rest of ingredients in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart dish. Sprinkle crushed potato chips on top of mixture.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes until bubbly in a 325° oven.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly in medium mixing bowl.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Mix well and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: brunch rice
directions: Cook rice as follows:
boil 2 cups water; add a pinch of salt. Pour in 1/2 cup long grain brown rice and return to boil.
Add 1/2 cup long grain white rice and return to boil, then reduce heat to simmer.
Cook for about 30 minutes without stirring.
Set aside.

title: sausage squares
directions: Mix Bisquick with milk and 2 tablespoons mayonnaise.
Put in well-greased casserole dish (patting down dough), 7 x 11-inch or 9 x 13-inch.
Saute sausage and onions, drain well on paper towels. Spread on top of Bisquick mix.
Beat 1 egg and 2 tablespoons mayonnaise, Cheddar cheese and chilies.
Pour over top and bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Cut in squares and serve for breakfast or brunch.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice onions; combine with cucumbers and salt.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain good.
Combine vinegar, sugar, mustard seed, celery seed and cayenne.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add onions and cucumber.
Heat to simmering point.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: hanky panky's
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage.
Add oregano, Accent, garlic and onion salt to meat and mix in.
Put meat on bread.
Top with Velveeta.
Broil for 3 to 5 minutes.
These are great and easy for a party!

title: baked potato soup
directions: Cut potatoes in half lengthwise, scoop out pulp.
Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat; add all-purpose flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk, cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened and bubbly.

title: fresh apple cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and spices together.
Cream the butter; add sugar gradually.
Mix well. Add egg and beat until fluffy. Alternately add sifted dry ingredients and milk.
Mix in fruits and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Frost with Vanilla Icing while hot. Makes about 10 dozen.

title: spring 7-up cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pie filling, oil, 7-Up and eggs.
Bake on 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes three 9-inch layers.
Spread filling between layers.

title: church window candy
directions: Lightly butter 2 pieces of foil.
Melt stick of butter; remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
If chips are hard to melt, put back on heat for a minute.
Add marshmallows, stir quickly and gently.
Spoon onto foil in close thick clumps. Roll-up foil.
The next day, slice into pretty rounds.

title: exotic chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, water chestnuts, celery, grapes and almonds. Mix mayonnaise, curry powder, soy sauce and lemon juice.
Add mayonnaise mixture to chicken mixture and chill for several hours. Serve on leaf lettuce and top with pineapple chunks.
Garnish with orchids, tropical fruit slices, etc. if desired.

title: pig slop(hamburger casserole)
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Combine hamburger, vegetable soup, tomato soup and half of the noodles.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and cover with remaining noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until noodles are slightly brown.

title: peach salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sugar, cream cheese and nuts.
Cool until partially jelled.
Add Cool Whip and pineapple. Refrigerate until molded.

title: quick and easy dessert
directions: Mix and refrigerate or freeze.

title: ginger snaps
directions: Cream crisco and sugar; add egg and molasses. Sift remaining ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Roll into 1 inch balls; roll in sugar. Flatten with fork on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 - 10 minutes.

title: graham-chocolate brownies
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, chocolate chips, pecans and condensed milk in bowl; mix well.
Spread in well-greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares while hot.
Cool completely before removing from pan.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: something-good-to-eat
directions: Brown ground beef; place in casserole and cover with peas, green peppers and onions.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with remaining ingredients.
Bake 1 hour, covered, at 350°.

title: hershey bar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add unbeaten eggs one at a time.
Mix well.
Add soda to hot water and pour over dates; add to creamed mixture.
Add chocolate bars, broken into small pieces.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Add flour which was sifted.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven about 15 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat.
Drain.
Combine vegetables, meat and seasonings. Boil slowly until tender.

title: party mix
directions: Melt oleo, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce, garlic powder, onion powder and salt all together.
Place the Chex, Cheerios, pretzels and nuts together in a very large pan.
Pour oleo over dry mixture.
Stir well.
Place in a 250° oven and bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Be sure not to let it burn. Place on paper towels and cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: pepper steak
directions: Fry meat; season with salt and brown on both sides. Add onion; cook till tender. Stir in soy sauce, garlic and broth. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes. Add bell peppers; simmer for 5 minutes. Blend cornstarch and water. Blend in cornstarch mixture into sauce and cook. Stir constantly till thickens and boils. Stir and boil for 1 minute. Add tomatoes, cook 1 minute. Serve over rice.

title: cheesy vegetable ritz medley
directions: Cook and drain the California blend.
Melt Velveeta and margarine together.
Pour over vegetables in baking dish.
Mix melted margarine and Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle over cheese mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: minted sundae soda
directions: Combine jelly and water in saucepan.
Place over low heat and stir until jelly is dissolved.
Cool.
Into each chilled 14 ounce glass, pour 3 tablespoons mint syrup.
Add 1 spoonful of sherbet; stir until melted.
Add scoop of sherbet, then vanilla ice cream. Fill with 7-Up or Sprite, pouring down side of glass to save sparkle.
Make sure soda is well chilled.
Serve with a straw and a spoon.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, bread crumbs, onion, Parmesan, eggs and seasonings.
Mix lightly.
Press into 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Pour off drippings.
Combine tomato sauce and oregano.
Pour over meat.
Top with Mozzarella. Continue baking for another 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix the ingredients and put in uncooked pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes at 450°, then reduce heat to 350° and cook for 30 minutes longer.

title: chicken manicotti
directions: Cook
manicotti according to package directions.
Saute onion and
garlic
in
olive
oil.
In
a large bowl, combine chicken, onion,
garlic,
Ricotta
cheese,
parsley and 1 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Mix thoroughly (you may even want to blend in
a
food processor).
Stuff chicken mixture into manicotti pasta using a small spoon.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish and pour spaghetti sauce over the manicotti.
Top with remaining Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for
minutes.
Remove foil and bake 10 minutes to slightly brown top.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Place chocolate chips and milk in microwave bowl.
Put in microwave for 2 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Stir and put in an 8 x 8-inch buttered pan; refrigerate for 1 hour or until set.
Keep unused fudge in refrigerator.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Clean shrimp and wash them.
Cut bell peppers in half.
Wash them.
Place them in pot with two cups of water.
Steam them.
In a large skillet, simmer onion, garlic, celery and parsley in 1/4 tablespoon of margarine for 10 minutes.
Then add shrimp and bread crumbs.
Simmer on low heat until shrimp turn pink and bread crumbs brown.
Stuff the shrimp dressing into peppers and bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Grease baking dish.
Layer vegetables and put ground beef on the top.
Mix soups and pour over the top.
Cover the dish with foil; bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over the top.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Put potatoes in shallow broiler-proof baking dish. Melt 3 tablespoons butter. Blend in flour. Add milk gradually and stir until thick. Add cheese and stir until melted. Season. Pour over potatoes and mix lightly. Put under broiler at medium heat and broil until browned.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Peel potatoes and slice into flat pieces.
Place a layer of potatoes in casserole dish.
Place a layer of pork chops on top of potatoes.
Continue in this order until all of the potatoes and pork chops are used.
On top of this, add mushroom soup and milk. Do not stir.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: garlic salad
directions: Take the clove of garlic and cut in half.
In a glass bowl rub the inside of the bowl with the garlic until thoroughly coated. Take the garlic pieces used to rub the bowl and dice up fine.
Mix all together into bowl.
Let stand until it makes a quite a bit of juice.
Add lettuce, as much as you want and carrots, celery or whatever you like in your salad.

title: cape cod fish chowder
directions: Saute onion in oleo until soft.
Add potatoes, salt, basil, pepper and water.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat and cook 15 minutes. Add fish on top of potatoes.
Cook 15 minutes more, until fish flakes and potatoes are tender.
Add corn and it's liquid and milk.
Heat, do not boil.
Serves 6.

title: sweet potato casserole delight
directions: Mash sweet potatoes.
Mix sugar, oleo, eggs, vanilla and milk to sweet potatoes.
Put into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: bird suet
directions: Melt lard for 1 1/2 minutes in microwave.
Add peanut butter. Microwave until completely melted.
Mix together dry ingredients. Add wet to dry ingredients and mix well.
Form into small balls or place on cookie sheet to be cut into cubes.
Let set to harden. Store unused portions in freezer.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Trim fat from beef.
Cut crosswise into 1/2-inch thick slices. Coat beef with flour.
Melt margarine in a large skillet.
Add beef, garlic and onions; cook until beef is browned on all sides. Add mushrooms, bouillon cubes, dill weed, parsley, catsup, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add sour cream and sherry; mix well.
If desired, serve with cooked noodles.
Serves 8.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick margarine with crackers and pat into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Next beat with electric mixer for 15 minutes the eggs, 2 sticks margarine and powdered sugar.
Spread this over graham cracker crust and cover with sliced bananas.
Spread pineapple over bananas and top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and place cherries on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Store in refrigerator.

title: dirty rice
directions: Place margarine and oil in frying pan.
Cut up onion and cook slightly.
Add rice and brown.
Pour consomme over the rice.
Pour all into casserole and bake at 300° for 1 to 2 hours (until all liquid is absorbed).

title: hot taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Add taco seasoning and follow package directions.
Add tomato paste.
Heat refried beans with sausage.
Spread chips in ovenproof dish.
Top with ground beef; layer refried beans and sausage, then taco cheese.

title: crock-pot roast beef
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Cook in crock-pot for 6 hours on low.
Retain stock after removing meat.
Add pineapple, green pepper and cornstarch.
Cook until gravylike.
Slice beef and pour stock over meat.
Garnish with parsley and serve.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash and peel carrots.
Boil in salted water until tender.
Saute onions in butter until golden.
Place carrots in greased 1-quart baking dish and mash.
Add onions and soup.
Blend well, adding salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake until bubbly, 25 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: ham cups
directions: Grease muffin cups.
Place 1 biscuit in each greased muffin cup.
Firmly press in bottom and up sides, forming 1/4-inch rim.

title: lime gelatin salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in hot water.
Do not add any more water as you are adding a different type of liquid later.
Then add lime gelatin.
Cool.
Then add drained crushed pineapple, cottage cheese and walnuts.
Finally, fold in whipped cream.
Chill.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Mix well together.
Shape into ball.
Chill.
Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Grind cheese and pimentos.

title: hot bacon cheese dip
directions: In a 1 1/2 Qt slow cooker, combine the first six ingredients. Cover and cook for 2 hours or until cheeses are melted, stirring occasionally. Just before serving, stir in bacon.

title: crab quiche
directions: In a prepared pie shell, sprinkle the grated cheese.
Beat eggs; mix with milk and seasonings.
Pour over cheese.
Sprinkle crabmeat over pie.
Bake 35 minutes or until knife comes out clean at 375°.

title: hershey's cocoa fudge frosting
directions: Melt butter (margarine) in saucepan.
Add cocoa; heat 1 minute or until smooth, stirring constantly.
Pour into small mixer bowl. Alternately add confectioners sugar and milk; beat to spreading consistency.
Blend in vanilla.
Add 1 tablespoon crushed peppermint candy if desired.
Fills and frosts 2 (8 or 9-inch) layers.

title: midge's quickie asparagus casserole
directions: Mix peas and asparagus in casserole dish.
Pour mushroom soup over mixture; cover with cracker crumbs.
Pour melted margarine over crumbs and bake in a 350° oven until brown and bubbly.

title: fresh corn salad
directions: Mix oil, vinegar, lemon juice, parsley, sugar, salt, basil and pepper.
Add corn, tomatoes, onion and peppers.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Toss the cabbage and peppers and place into a strainer resting over a bowl to drain for 2 hours. Then place into a mason jar.

title: key lime cheese cake
directions: Mix well and pour into pie crust.
Let set overnight.

title: holiday hideaways
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream Crisco, sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in a large bowl at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda. Beat into creamed mixture at low speed.
Press dough in a very thin
layer around cherries.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Cool on baking sheet 1 minute.
Remove to cooling rack.
Cool completely.
Dip in chocolate.

title: favorite biscuits
directions: Mix flour and buttermilk, a little at a time, until your dough is real stiff.
Then add oil; mix well.
Pour out on wax paper covered with flour.

title: peanut butter gems
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients and roll into small balls (48). Grease miniature muffin tins and bake the balls for 7 to 9 minutes at 375°.
When cooked, immediately push (unwrapped) mini Reese's peanut butter cups into the cookies firmly while still in pan. Let set for 2 minutes and then remove cookies from pan.
Makes 4 dozen gems.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients, except butter.
Knead on floured board and cut with biscuit cutter.
Brush with melted butter.
Bake in oven preheated to 450° until brown.
Delicious!

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Whip together until very light, eggs and sugar.
Measure into cup the flour.
Add vanilla to egg mixture. Heat milk with butter until butter melts.
Dump hot milk and flour into egg.
Fold thoroughly, using wire whip.
Pour into greased and floured 2 layer cake pan or 9 x 13-inch sheet cake pan.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: zesty oyster crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers together in a large bowl. Add crackers and toss with large spoon until well coated. Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 200° for 20 minutes. Cool. Keep in air tight container.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Drain and add 1 teaspoon salt. Mix with other ingredients.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into 3-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: snowball kiss cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and sherry.
Fold in flour and nuts. Refrigerate.
Roll into 1-inch balls with kiss inside.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in 325° oven.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: almost snickers
directions: Combine in a mixer and pour into an 8-inch square pan. Freeze. Serves 8.

title: bernie's baked beans
directions: In 13 x 9-inch baking dish, mix together all ingredients except for bacon.
Cover beans with bacon strips.
Cover dish with aluminum foil and bake in preheated oven at 400° for 1 1/2 hours. Remove foil and bake for an additional 15 minutes.
Enjoy!!

title: instant hot spiced tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in airtight container. To serve:
2 heaping teaspoons of mix into 1 cup boiling water. You can use more or less mix to taste.

title: fiesta cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Pour shortening into 10-inch iron skillet and place in oven to heat.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour all but 2 tablespoons of heated shortening into cornmeal mixture; mix well.
Pour batter into hot skillet and bake for 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: monkey bread
