directions: Dissolve yeast cakes in warm water.
Mix shortening, sugar and salt.
Add flour and yeast mixture to the shortening mixture, alternately, until all is mixed.
Beat and mix well.
Let rise until double the size.

title: daddy's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, beat butter, sugar and vanilla extract until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually beat in flour mixture. Stir in Nestle morsels.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Divide olive oil in two skillets and heat both to medium heat.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and Italian seasonings in mixing bowl and set aside.
Beat eggs in another mixing bowl, then dip each breast first in egg, then in the flour mixture, then place in the skillets.
Turn once or twice as necessary until the breasts are a light golden brown.

Use a large, flat, deep Pyrex baking dish and cover the bottom with a layer of spaghetti sauce, a layer of the browned breaded chicken breasts, a thin slice of Mozzarella, a thin slice of Provolone and a sprinkle of grated Parmesan/Romano; then another layer of sauce, chicken, etc. until you run out of sauce and chicken.
Bake for about 1/2 hour until chicken is done but not dried out.
Put a lid or cover on the baking dish since the tomato sauce tends to bubble and splatter.
This is a great dish for people who think they don't like chicken!

title: 20-minute chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken in egg, then in crumbs.
In skillet over medium heat in hot margarine, brown chicken on both sides.
Add Prego sauce.
Reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: bean soup
directions: Soak beans in water overnight. Cover everything with water in large pot. Cook on top of stove for 6 hours on slow heat.

title: creamy cheese cake
directions: Combine melted butter with graham cracker crumbs, powdered sugar and pecans. Line bottom and sides of spring-form pan with mixture and press firmly.
Set aside.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Coarse grind onion, peppers and zucchini and sprinkle with salt.
Stand overnight.
Drain and rinse.
Drain again.
Heat to full boil, stirring constantly.
Seal hot in sterile jars.

title: sauce pique
directions: Fry sausage after cutting into thin slices.
Drain, saving grease.
Boil chicken breasts until done. Bone and cut into bite size pieces. Chop onion, bell pepper and celery.
Fry in sausage grease over low heat for 3 minutes.
Mix all ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 6.

title: golden wedding punch
directions: Combine thawed concentrates in large container.
Add juices and water; mix well.
Stir in sugar.
Chill in refrigerator. (It's best if half or more is frozen when you start to serve.
It will be icy.)
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: chicken enchilada pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a Pam sprayed 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake until thoroughly heated.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Melt on stove tomato soup and cream cheese; set aside. Prepare vegetables; mix with soup mixture.
Melt gelatin in water. Pour into mixture.
Crumble shrimp.
Add mayo; mix well.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients well.
Blend in eggs, peanut butter, soda and vanilla.
Stir in flour and rolled oats.
Spread in greased pan, 10 x 13.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: meatball skillet luau
directions: Mix beef with egg, bread crumbs and seasoning.
Form into 16 balls.
Dredge balls in flour.
Brown in salad oil in a large frying pan.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl 2 minutes or until dissolved completely.
Stir in cold water.
Stir in ice cream until smooth.
Pour into serving bowls or cups.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until set.
Garnish with Cool Whip, fruits and nuts. Makes 8 servings.

title: no-bake peanut butter oat cookies
directions: In medium saucepan, mix in sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and butter or margarine.
Put over medium heat and bring to a boil; boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and oats.
Drop by teaspoon onto foil-wrapped sheet pan.
Let stand until firm and cold.
Store airtight.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix all ingredients well using wooden spoon.
Pinch off small pieces of dough and roll into thickness of pencil.
Form into crescents.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes or until delicately brown.
Roll immediately in confectioners sugar.
Yield:
40 cookies.

title: mulled wine
directions: In a large pot, combine all ingredients except brown sugar and honey.
Stirring frequently, cook over medium heat until near boiling.
Add brown sugar and honey to taste.
Serve in mugs.

title: lemon cream chicken
directions: Cut chicken in serving size pieces.
Cook until brown all over in 4 tablespoons butter.
Cover pan; saute 30 to 40 minutes. Remove chicken; stir in sherry and bring to boil.
Add 2 teaspoons lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Slowly add 1 cup heavy cream; thicken with 1 tablespoon flour, dissolved in 1/2 cup water.
Put chicken in mixture and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.

title: congo bars
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs, salt and baking powder.
Add flour and mix well.
Add nuts, then add chocolate chips.
Pour into a greased or sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: creole sauce
directions: Cook onions and peppers in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer for 10 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil fryer until done; reserve broth and debone chicken and cut up in small bite-size pieces.
Melt oleo in large skillet; chop up bell peppers, onion and celery and cook in oleo until crisp-tender.
Add tomatoes and mushrooms; break up tomatoes into small pieces while cooking.
Add vegetable mixture to chicken in large covered casserole dish; break spaghetti in thirds and cook in reserved broth until done.
Drain and combine with chicken and vegetables.
Stir in mushroom soup; arrange cheese on top of mixture and sprinkle with pepper and garlic salt.
Heat at 300° until cheese is melted and casserole is heated through; stir melted cheese throughout mixture.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: the burger loaf routine
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl, then place in loaf pan to bake.
Bake in a 350° oven for 60 minutes.
Serve with favorite gravy.

title: moon cake
directions: Bring water and margarine to a boil, then add flour and cool a little.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Spread mixture onto an ungreased jelly roll pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown, like cream puffs.
Mix cream cheese, milk and pudding mix. Spread over cream puff base.
Top with whipped topping, drizzle with chocolate syrup and sprinkle with chopped nuts, if desired.

title: refrigerator pickles(for diabetics)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and let stand overnight. In the morning, drain and rinse.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Grease and flour pan; cook at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chinese cabbage salad
directions: Shred cabbage; crumble up Ramen without seasoning, sunflower seeds, sliced almonds and sesame seed; saute in butter.
Set aside until room temperature.

title: sausage and biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare biscuit dough. Place flour in bowl.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender to consistency of coarse crumbs.
Add milk.
Stir with fork just until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Roll out dough on lightly floured board to 1/4-inch thick rectangle.
Spread sausage over dough almost to edge.
Roll up, jelly roll fashion.
Cut into 1/2-inch thick rounds.
Place rounds on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve immediately.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: bacon-egg casserole
directions: Combine ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into a greased Pyrex pan (9 to 10-inch square) and refrigerate 12 hours or overnight.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Do not preheat oven.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken; cut into bite size pieces.
Saute pepper, celery and onion in small amount of butter.
Add mushrooms and pimentos. Cook spaghetti in the chicken broth until tender; drain.
Add soup and evaporated milk.
Add chicken and sauteed ingredients to the spaghetti mixture; mix well.
Sprinkle cheese on top; heat for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in loaf pans or any small container and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix sour cream and taco sauce 1 hour before; refrigerate and set aside.
Brown hamburg and drain fat.
Add taco mix according to directions.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, layer hamburger, lettuce, tomatoes and sour cream mixture.
Top with Cheddar cheese and serve with tortilla chips.

title: quiche
directions: Put onion, almonds, Swiss cheese, butter, flour and bacon in pie shell.
Mix eggs and cream together and pour in pie shell. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes and then at 325° for 25 minutes more.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter and cream.
Boil until softball stage.
Add marshmallow cream, chocolate chips, peanut butter, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: lemon nut fruitcake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, extract, 3 cups flour and baking powder.
Mix one cup flour with cut up fruit and raisins.
Add fruit with creamed mixture.
Add nuts last.
Pour into lined 10-inch Bundt pans.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Cook bacon. Beat eggs. Stir in milk and bacon drippings. Add bacon and remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour batter into hot (cast-iron) skillet. (Makes 2 pans.) Bake for 35 minutes or until golden brown at 400°. Great with chili.

title: bearnaise sauce
directions: Heat vinegar and pour on well beaten egg yolks; set bowl with mixture over hot water.
Stir constantly until thick.
Remove from heat; add butter a half teaspoon at a time and blend into sauce.
Season with salt and paprika.
Good served over steak.

title: hamburger chow mein
directions: *Can use water chestnuts and chow mein vegetables, then only use 1 can bean sprouts.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Put apples in a saucepan with a small amount of water (serves 7).
Cook over medium heat about 20 minutes.
Drain well.
Mash slightly and measure 2 1/2 cups apples.
Combine apples, sugar and allspice.
Stir well; set aside.

title: balsamic chicken
directions: Tenderize chicken with mallet. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.

Cook chicken 4 minutes per side and transfer to serving plate. Cover and keep warm. Add shallots to skillet and cook, stirring 2 minutes. Add broth, vinegar and brown sugar. Bring to a boil and cook until reduced by 1/3 (about 4 minutes). Whisk butter into skillet until melted.
Pour over chicken. Toss parsley with orzo (pour any leftover balsamic sauce onto orzo) and serve with chicken.

title: brownie cupcakes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line 24 muffin cups.
Blend brownie mix, chocolate
syrup,
water and eggs with spoon.
Fill cups 2/3 full. Drop 1 tablespoon Cream Cheese Filling on batter in each cup. Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
tags: Betty Crocker fudge brownie mix supreme

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs; mix.
Add flour with soda and salt.
Last, add vanilla, nuts and raisins.
Makes 4 rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Leave in refrigerator several hours. Slice and bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° about 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: southern yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Combine dry ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Roll on floured surface to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut with biscuit cutter.
Roll in butter.
Place in pan.
Let rise 1 hour. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: taco salad
directions: Add cheese, dressing and chips last, just before serving.

title: frog stew
directions: In a very large pot of water (at least 6 quarts), add Seafood Boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Add sausage; boil for 5 more minutes.
Add corn, boil for 5 more minutes.
Add shrimp; stir until shrimp are pink.
Remove from heat and drain into colander. Serve immediately in a large bowl with hot bread and cold beer or white wine.
Use fingers and enjoy!

title: deluxe chocolate bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix 1/3 cup margarine and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Stir in 1 cup flour.
Press in an ungreased baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: jelly dot cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt and soda. Set aside. Combine margarine, sugar, egg and vanilla. Beat for 1 minute or until smooth and slightly thickened.
Add dry ingredients and blend well.
Chill until dough is firm to handle.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Render salt pork.
Remove crisp pieces.
Add onions and celery.
Cook until translucent.
Add potatoes, juice from the clams and enough water to barely cover the vegetables.
Cover and simmer until tender.

title: spanish steak
directions: Cut steak into strips or cubes; brown.
Add onions; brown. Add all ingredients.
Cook 1 1/2 hours.
Make brown gravy. Take broth from steak and put in gravy.
Pour back into steak. Cook for 1 hour on medium heat.
Serve over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate.

title: tuna cakes
directions: Mix tuna, mayonnaise, vegetables, pimento, seasonings and 1/2 cup bread crumbs.
Shape mixture into fifteen (2-inch) balls. Roll in remaining 3/4 cup bread crumbs, coating well.
Flatten balls into small patties.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Brown meat and onions and add spaghetti sauce.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch lightly greased baking pan with thin layer of meat mixture.
Cover with lasagna noodles (overlap).
Mix cottage cheese with eggs, parsley, salt and pepper and put a layer of that mixture over the noodles and cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with more meat mixture.
Repeat layers until pan is full.
End with meat sauce and shredded cheese.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Top with more cheese and bake 5 to 10 minutes more.
Let set 15 minutes before serving.

title: pie crust
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in apple juice until mixture holds together.
Press half of mixture in bottom and up sides of nonstick 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 5 minutes.
Save remaining crust for topping (to use with some sort of apple filling).

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add warm milk and vanilla.
Beat until thick to spread.

title: honey dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender.
Mix for 30 seconds or until creamy.
Store in refrigerator.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Mix tomato sauce, sugar, vinegar and mustard in a small bowl until blended. Place remaining ingredients and 1 cup of sauce mixture in a large bowl; blend thoroughly. Place meat mixture in a 2-quart loaf dish, pressing to form a loaf. Pour 1/4 cup of sauce over the top. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour, basting with 1/4 cup sauce after 30 minutes. Remove from oven and cool for 10 minutes.
Drain excess fat. Pour over remaining sauce which has been heated.

title: meal-in-a-salad
directions: Arrange in layers and top with Marizetti Poppy Seed Dressing. Good served with warm muffins.

title: church of god fried pie crust recipe
directions: Combine all ingredients except flour.
Mix well.
Add enough flour to make a thick dough.
Let chill in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Roll out and cut in circles.
Makes 10 pies.

title: red apple salad
directions: Heat applesauce and dissolve the gelatin in it.
Chill until slightly thickened and add the lemon-lime soda.
Mix thoroughly and pour into a chilled 1 1/2-quart mold or 10 to 12 individual molds.
Unmold on lettuce leaves.

title: chicken in crock-pot
directions: Place chicken in crock-pot.
Add vegetables.
Add salt, pepper, garlic and chicken broth; slow cook until tender.
Add rice and cook until rice is done.
This dish can be removed from crock-pot when done, placed in Pyrex dish and browned.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Sift flour and sugars in a large bowl.
Heat margarine, cocoa and Coke. Bring to boiling point.
Pour over flour mixture. Add buttermilk, soda, eggs, vanilla, salt and marshmallows.
Batter will be thin and marshmallows will float on top.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Ice cake while hot.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spray baking dish with nonstick spray.
Pour beans into baking dish; cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
If beans are too dry, add back some bean juice.

title: english trifle
directions: Prepare jello and pudding according to package directions. When jello is almost set, add fruit.
Place jellyroll or ladyfingers in bottom of trifle bowl (or deep glass bowl).
Add jello on top of cake; add pudding on top of jello.
Cover with Cool Whip.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients and saute ground beef with cheese and peppers.
Pour part of bacon drippings in a skillet.
Sprinkle with corn meal.
Pour 1/2 of bacon drippings in the cheese and meat mixture.
Pour 1/2 of the batter in the skillet.
Add meat mixture and add the rest of batter.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: creamy white frosting
directions: Combine milk and flour.
Cook until thick and let cool.
Beat the sugar, oleo and shortening until fluffy.
Add to first mixture and beat until ready to spread.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Brown ground beef, onions and peppers. Add taco seasoning.
Spread meat mixture in pan.
Sprinkle in olives and cheese.
Beat milk, eggs and Bisquick with electric mixer until smooth (1 minute).
Pour over meat mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until brown and knife comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: no bake fruit balls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in small bowl and let stand 1 hour. In medium bowl, beat butter and corn syrup until well blended. Gradually beat in crumbs; add fruit mixture and mix well.
Shape in 3/4 inch balls, wetting hands if mixture becomes dry.
Roll balls in sugar.
Store in airtight container up to 1 month.
Allow at least a week for flavors to mellow.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: In a large frypan, saute onion and pepper in oil over medium heat until tender. Remove from heat. Add paprika, salt and pepper. Return pan to heat and add chicken. Cook 10 to 15 minutes. Add tomato sauce and water; simmer 25 to 30 minutes longer. Stir occasionally. Remove chicken from pan and arrange on serving platter over noodles. Skim excess fat from sauce.
Mix 1/2 cup sour cream with sauce.
Gradually ladle over chicken and noodles. Dollop with remaining sour cream.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients as for pie dough.
Pat into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Next, beat eggs; add remaining ingredients in order listed.
Pour over baked crust and return to oven.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with a thin glazed icing and cut into squares.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Mix yeast into warm water.
Melt and cool margarine.
Add sugar and beaten egg.
Stir in slowly flour.
Put in covered bowl and refrigerate.
Spoon in muffin pan and let rise 1 to 2 hours. Bake at 375° until brown.

title: turkey club casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter 2 quart baking dish.
Mix turkey, soup and seasonings.
Set aside.

title: ground beef grand style
directions: Brown hamburger and onions; add the rest of ingredients.
Put in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, then lay biscuits on top and bake until biscuits are brown.

title: chicken 'n rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together in a large baking dish.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Prepare graham cracker crust in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan as directed on box.
Beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth. Make Dream Whip as directed.
Then blend it with sugar and cream cheese mixture.
Pour filling over crust.
Then spread cherry filling over top of cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and pat dry the mushrooms; remove the stems, chop and set aside.
In a large skillet, cook the bacon until crisp, when cools off crumble and set aside.
Pour off bacon grease; and in the same skillet, melt the oleo.
(Use 4 tablespoons of this to brush the mushroom caps and to remaining 2 tablespoons, saute onion and mushroom stems.) Remove from heat.

title: cheesy-herb low-fat dip
directions: Blend all ingredients and chill well. Serve as a dip for carrot sticks, celery sticks, cauliflower, etc.

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Cut squash in half. Remove seeds. Bake, cut side down, in shallow pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Turn, cut side up. Salt and fill with sausage. Brush with butter and 1 tablespoon honey. Bake 25 minutes.

title: special chocolate pie
directions: Combine flour, margarine and nuts.
Press mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 12 to 15 minutes; let cool.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat this mixture very hard.
Alternate flour and milk.
Stir in buttermilk and then add bananas, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in greased loaf pans in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Cut tips from chicken wings and discard. Separate wing and drummie. Dip each piece in egg and then into cornstarch to which garlic salt has been added. Brown in fry pan. Make sauce of remaining ingredients. Place chicken wings in 10 X 10 pan. Cover with sauce and bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; press tightly in pan.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Cover bottom of casserole with crackers (crumbs).
Then use a layer of sliced eggs, then one of asparagus and one of mushroom soup.
Cover top with cracker crumbs and grated American cheese. Bake 10 to 15 minutes in 450° oven.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into 6 to 8 pieces.
Mix flour, salt and pepper. Pound into meat with meat hammer or knife.
Brown meat in hot oil, turning once.
Reduce heat.
Add tomatoes, sugar, celery and onions.
Bring to simmer.
Cover and cook until tender, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Arrange meat and sauce in shallow, covered casserole. Heat about 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: tiger butter candy
directions: Melt white chocolate and peanut butter in a double boiler or a microwave for 5 minutes on 50% power.
Stir occasionally.
Melt chocolate chips the same way, 2 1/2 minutes on 50% power.

title: crumb crust
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Press into a pie pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°.
Fill with your favorite pie filling.

title: scallop, corn and tomato pasta
directions: Cook fettucine until al dente.
Meanwhile, heat cream and garlic to boiling in medium saucepan.
Add scallops and cook just until centers are opaque, 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Using slotted spoon, transfer scallops to bowl.
Continue to boil cream until thick enough to coat back of spoon, about 6 minutes.
Stir in chopped tomatoes and corn and cook until heated through.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Drain fettucine well and transfer to large bowl.
Add cream sauce, scallops and basil; toss well.
Serve at once.

title: cherry crunch dessert(dump cake)
directions: Put pie filling in 13 x 9-inch pan and sprinkle cake mix evenly over the pie filling.
Drizzle melted margarine over the cake mix.
Bake for approximately 1 hour at 325° or until bubbly and golden brown.

title: chicken and cheese chimichangas
directions: Combine chicken, salsa, onion and spices in saucepan.
Heat until most liquid has evaporated.
Brush 1 side of tortilla with butter.
Spoon about 1/3 cup meat onto center of the unbuttered side; top with a handful of cheese.
Fold 2 sides over filling; fold ends down.
Place seam side down in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 475° for 13 minutes until crisp and golden.
Top with guacamole, sour cream or salsa to serve.

title: scallop casserole
directions: Fry onions, celery and peppers until tender.

title: pineapple salad supreme
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water; heat over hot water to liquid consistency.
Add gelatin to all other ingredients combined. Congeal.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine tomatoes, cornstarch.
Cook until thickened.
Pour over chicken. Top with cheese.
Bake 10 minutes uncovered.
Makes 4 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together; put in greased pan.
Put Ritz crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Saute onion,
pepper
and
celery in 1 stick of butter. Mix mushroom soup
and	1
cup	pea
juice.
Add
pimento
and mushrooms.	Combine
all ingredients in a long casserole dish. Top with bread	crumbs	and dot with butter.
Bake in moderate oven for 30 minutes.

title: roast beef
directions: Place oil in large skillet.
While oil is heating, flour roast on both sides.
When oil is hot, put roast in skillet and brown on both sides.
Remove roast from skillet and place in roasting pan. Brown remaining flour in skillet and make brown gravy.
Pour this over roast.
Add Worcestershire sauce, mushrooms, mushroom soup, soup mix, chopped onion, salt and pepper.
Cook in 375° oven for approximately 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: ruth ann's sweet dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers, slice lengthwise to fill about 8 pints.
To each jar, add 2 slices onion, 1 piece celery and 1 head dill.

title: chocolate truffle cake
directions: Pour Kahlua on chocolate cake after cake cools.
Prepare mousse.
Crumble 1/2 cake in base of large bowl.
Layer 1/2 of mousse, Cool Whip and Heath bars.
Repeat with second half of ingredients.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Place oats in water and let stand for 10 minutes.
Cream oleo and sugar.
Mix with oats and add eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Bake cake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: frozen delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in cupcake liners or in a glass dish.
Freeze, then serve.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and pour into baking dish.

title: hot water pastry
directions: Sift flour and measure 2 cups.
Add 1 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon baking powder; sift.
Add shortening to 1/3 cup boiling water and stir until smooth.
Then add to flour and stir until blended; roll in waxed paper and chill slightly before rolling into pie crust.
(Makes two 8-inch crusts.)

title: cordon bleu
directions: Flatten chicken; sprinkle with salt and pepper on each chicken.
Place slice of cheese and ham on chicken.
Roll up and secure with toothpicks.
Beat egg yolks and water.
Dip chicken and roll in bread crumbs.
Fry in butter and oil.
Brown each side.
Place on a baking sheet and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sausage and cheese dip
directions: Scramble meat and cook until done.
Drain well.
Mix cheese and tomatoes.
Cook on low until mixed good and heated.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: paintbrush party cookies
directions: Stir butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and Mix. Add flour and vanilla and mix.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls of dough onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°.

title: mozzarella meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except Mozzarella.
Put half mixture in loaf pan.
Spread Mozzarella cheese and then put the rest of the mixture on top, sealing the edges.
Spread catsup on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple chutney
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil in a medium saucepan, over medium heat.
Reduce the heat to low and simmer, uncovered, until the fruit is tender and sauce has thickened, about 45 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Good with duck, pork, chicken, grilled meats. Put on meats just before serving.
Makes enough for 14 ounces of meat.

title: irene's scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Arrange potatoes in layers in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle each layer with onion, salt and pepper; dot with butter.
Add hot milk.
Bake, uncovered, about 1 1/4 hours.

title: simple skillet dinner mexicana
directions: In a medium skillet, brown beef and drain.
Stir in water, salsa and taco seasoning. Mix and bring to a boil.
Stir in rice. Cover and simmer over low heat for 15 to 20 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid absorbed. Serves 4.

title: taco salad
directions: Prepare lettuce, tomato, onion and avocado as you would for a salad.
Rinse and drain pinto beans.
Add beans, olives, cheese and hamburger.

title: crab dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in a disposable pizza pan.
Top with chili sauce.
Top with crab dip.
May also substitute shrimp for crabmeat.
Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: krispy kraut salad
directions: Mix kraut, celery, onion and green pepper.
Heat vinegar and sugar.
Add to kraut mixture and refrigerate overnight.
(Keeps a long time.)

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients until brown and add tomatoes, bay leaves, pepper, tomato paste, salt and water.
Cook slowly, then remove bay leaves.
Cook noodles.

title: crock-pot potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan over low heat and add sour cream and soup and onion flakes.
When margarine mixture is melted and smooth, combine with the 6 to 8 medium-sized potatoes (boiled) and place in crock-pot on low heat.
Cook in crock-pot for at least 1 hour.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Mix well; pour into 2 baked pie crusts.
Top with blueberry pie filling.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine sugar, vanilla, eggs and Crisco.
Then add flour and milk.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water; heat.
Add Jell-O and cook to boil.
Cool and pour over berries.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix according to directions and pour into 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle rhubarb and sugar over cake batter.
Pour whipping cream over rhubarb.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.	Remove from oven and invert onto a cookie sheet covered with aluminum foil.

title: granny's sugar cookies
directions: For a glaze, mix sugar and water (with or without food coloring).
Brush or dribble onto baked cookies.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Have butter at room temperature.
Cream sugar and butter well (I use electric mixer).
Add flour.
Flour palms of hands.
Dip up cookie dough by teaspoon and in palms of hand carefully roll into ball.
Place on cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
When you have cookie sheet filled with small balls of dough, flour finger and depress each one in center.
Place about 1/2 teaspoon jelly (I use Smucker's crabapple) in depression in each cookie; put pecan half on top of jelly.
Bake in slow oven.
Watch carefully; do not brown cookie.
They should be barely golden in color.

title: honey-glazed chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Score chicken in several places to let the spices soak into meat.
Sprinkle spices over chicken.
Pour 1 cup of honey over chicken.
Add chicken, potatoes and carrots to roasting pan or roasting bag.
Reduce heat in oven to 325° and bake from 1 1/2 hours to 2 hours, depending on size of chicken.

title: pumpkin pie filling
directions: Cook and pour into 2 baked pie crusts.
Top with whipped cream.

title: zucchini stuffing casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in a little salt water until tender.
In saucepan, cook carrot, onion and 4 tablespoons margarine until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups stuffing cubes, soup and sour cream.
Gently stir in zucchini.
Put into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt remaining margarine and rest of cubes. Top casserole with remaining cubes.
Cook at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Then add the last four ingredients, mixing well and slowly.
Use a 13 x 9-inch pan lightly sprayed with Pam.
Cook 30 to 35 minutes.
If using Bundt pan sprayed with Pam, cook 45 minutes or until done. No need to ice the cake.
Lots of milk to drink.

title: baked oatmeal
directions: Cream first 2 ingredients together, then add the rest.
This is a "stick-to-the-ribs" breakfast!
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan
at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese chilies cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease heavy 10-inch skillet and heat in oven.
Whisk eggs, yogurt and butter together in medium bowl. Add dry ingredients and mix until just well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into heated skillet and bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.
(Can substitute Cheddar cheese.)

title: broccoli-stuffed shells
directions: Steam or boil broccoli florets until crunchy tender.
Allow to cool.
Mince florets, either with a sharp knife or in food processor, fitted with a sharp blade.
Combine broccoli with Ricotta, eggs, Parmesan, pepper, nutmeg and oregano and stir until well combined.
Stuff each cooked shell with 1 tablespoon of mixture.
Pour sauce over shells and bake at 375° until hot.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together sugar, butter, eggs, flour, salt, almond extract, vanilla and syrup; beat well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes, or until filling is set.

title: potato wraps
directions: Wash potatoes and cut into quarters.
Sprinkle each with mixture of seasoned salt, seasoned pepper and bay leaves.
Wrap 1 bacon piece around each potato piece.
Sprinkle with any remaining seasonings.
Microwave at High for 7 to 8 minutes or until bacon is crispy and potatoes are cooked.
Serve with sour cream and chives, if desired.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, using enough Miracle Whip to mix well.

title: old-fashioned coleslaw
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, mayonnaise, milk and salt.
Pour over cabbage.
Mix well and refrigerate for a few hours.

title: beef 'n' cheese braid
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Soften 2 tablespoons butter; add to yeast mixture with 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt and egg; beat until smooth.
Add enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto a floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Combine the beef, cheese and basil; set aside.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground chuck with onion and garlic.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and spices; cook on slow heat for 2 hours.
Cook lasagne noodles.
Layer:
lasagne noodles, meat sauce, Mozzarella cheese, sharp cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Layer until all noodles are used.
Top with cheeses and oregano leaves.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms, break off caps.
Stuff mushrooms with mixture. Broil 7 to 10 minutes (watch, do not burn).

title: vegetable bean salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine yogurt and mayo.
Pour over mixture.
Cover and chill.
Sprinkle with cheese before serving.
Contains 115 calories and 3.7 fat per 3/4 cup serving.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage into bite-size pieces. Add water; cook until it starts boiling. Let boil for 5 minutes; drain off all the water. Add Velveeta cheese and cream of chicken soup (undiluted). Put in casserole dish; sprinkle buttered bread crumbs on top. Cook in oven at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: homemade paste
directions: Mix flour, sugar and alum together.
Add a small amount of the pint of cold water and stir well to make a paste, to prevent lumps in the finished paste.
Heat the remainder of the water to boiling point in a 2 qt. pan.
While stirring, slowly add the paste to the boiling water.
Cook until thick, stirring.
Paste will be thicker when cold.
Stir in oil of cloves.
Pour into a small bowl and cover with one thickness of cloth to prevent crusting.
When cold, put into sterilized jars with tight fitting lids.

title: baked hash brown potatoes
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine thawed hash browns, cheese, sour cream, 1 stick margarine, mushroom soup and onion.
Mix all together.
Pour in pan.
Spread evenly.
Sprinkle top with crushed corn flakes and pour remaining 1/2 stick melted margarine on top.
Cover with foil.
Remove foil the last 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peach pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar together until light
and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing after each. Combine flour, soda and salt in a separate bowl; set aside. Combine sour cream and peaches.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream-peach mixture and creamed butter-sugar ingredients.
Stir in extracts.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake for 70 to 80 minutes or until nicely browned and an inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Remove from pan to cooling rack.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: any occasion punch
directions: Mix together in punch bowl.
Add 1/2 gallon orange sherbet.

title: salmon patties
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients except flour and cooking oil.
Mix real good.
Add flour and mix until all flour is mixed in good.
Make into patties and fry about 2 minutes on each side.

title: nut rolls
directions: Cut margarine into flour. Mix together egg yolks, sour cream and flavoring. Add to flour and margarine. Mix well.

Dough will be very soft. Divide dough into 6 parts. Chill overnight in a glass container, not plastic. Sprinkle lots of sugar on board. Roll dough out to 9 inch circle. Cut 8, 23, 16 parts like a pie. Fill. Start rolling from wide side to point, placing point under on cookie sheet.

title: cheesy garlic bread
directions: Add garlic to margarine.
Simmer for 5 minutes to bring out flavor.
Brush bread with garlic/margarine mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese and oregano.
Broil until lightly browned.

title: peanut candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips in double boiler. Add the peanut butter, then add
peanuts. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Put in refrigerator until set.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix bread crumbs with milk and egg. Add this to other ingredients and form into loaves. Pour catsup over loaves after placing them in baking dish. Do not cover. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Brown meat and add salt, pepper, onion, celery, bell pepper tops, pimento and parsley.
Cook until done.
Add rice and mix well.
Boil peppers 5 minutes.
Let cool a little and stuff with mixture; place in greased baking dish.
Bake for 20 minutes or until peppers are done.
Place one slice of cheese over each pepper and bake until melted.

title: poppy seed loaves
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer, mixing poppy seed last.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in greased loaf pans.
Fill pans a little over half full.

title: southern fried goulash
directions: Brown beef in frying pan.
Stir in onion, green pepper and seasonings and cook until browned.
Drain off most of the fat. Pour in tomato sauce and simmer mixture while pasta is cooking. Prepare macaroni or noodles according to package directions. Drain.
Pour in sauce and mix well.
Serve while hot.
Parmesan cheese may be sprinkled over the top, if desired.

title: date pinwheels
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients until thick. Add the nuts when mix is cool.
Mix the flour and baking soda.
Put aside.
Beat together the brown sugar, Crisco, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla. Add the date mixture and the flour mixture together.
Roll out dough to 1/2-inch thick.
Now spread the date-nut mix over all of the dough mix.
Now roll it up into a roll like jelly roll and put in wax paper. Store in refrigerator for a day.

title: delicious date bars
directions: Beat eggs and sugar; mix well.
Add shortening.
Add dates and nuts.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; mix well. Spread in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in a moderate oven at 325° for 35 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: hershey brownies
directions: Blend butter and sugar together until creamy.
Add eggs,
one at a time, mixing well after each.
Add the can of Hershey's syrup and the flour, mixing well.
Pour into greased 12-inch by 20-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend the cream cheese with the green pepper and green onion ends.
Blend the corned beef in the cream cheese, pepper and onions.
Mix well and form into a ball.
Wrap cheese ball in chopped pecans or slices of beef.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: jessie cakes
directions: Cream butter with cocoa and blend in other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mexicali bean bake
directions: Cook beef, onion and green pepper in 10-inch skillet until beef loses redness; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients except cheese.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top; bake 10 more minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy oven potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes.
Put in plastic bag with seasonings, oil and melted butter.
Shake, coating potatoes well with oil mixture. Pour potatoes, seasonings, oil and butter out into Pam-sprayed casserole dish (2-quart). Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix ingredients; boil wings for 1/2 to 1 hour. Let soak in liquid for 4 hours or overnight. Bake or broil until hot. These wings become less sticky as they cool.

title: blender chocolate pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender, including oleo.
Do not melt oleo, just set out and let soften.
Blend on whip until smooth. Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: rum cherry nut cake
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, oil, rum and water.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Into 10-inch tube pan, pour melted margarine.
Sprinkle with cherries, nuts and brown sugar.
Pour in batter.
Bake in 325° oven 45 to 60 minutes.
When done, immediately remove cake from oven and pan, turning upside down on cake plate.

title: brown sugar bars
directions: Mix together the eggs and brown sugar.
Allow to sit so brown sugar has a chance to dissolve.
Then add the rest of the ingredients; mix by hand.
Bake at 350° in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 minutes.
Cool; then sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut.

title: baked beans 2
directions: Combine all the ingredients except for bacon.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish and top with bacon strips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy tortilla soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine ingredients.
Simmer all together (the longer the better).
To serve, place in bowls over broken tortilla chips, cubed Monterey Jack cheese, cubed avocados or any spicy ingredients will be good served in the bowl with soup. (Sliced olives are good.)

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Slowly dissolve sugar and water.
Add strawberries and bring mixture to a boil; boil for 15 minutes.
Shake, but do not stir. Remove from heat; skim and pour into shallow pans.
Shake pans while mixture cools.
Let stand overnight.
Can while cold.
These are very good frozen; they retain the fresh flavor.

title: chocolate snowballs
directions: Combine chocolate and coconut.
Spread on wax paper.
Then roll scoops of ice cream in warm chocolate mixture.
Serve at once.

title: mississippi mud cookies
directions: Add sugar and cocoa to saucepan; stir well.
Add milk and mix thoroughly.
Put on stove and boil 1 to 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Take off stove and add butter, vanilla and peanut butter, then add oatmeal and stir.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Allow to cool and harden.
